im \"Miss Apple,\" and the first thing she said was \"No, call me, Ethel.\" She explains that she is here to call her by her first name because sometimes when people call her \"Miss Ethel,\" she doesn\'t answer. She says that if they call each other \"by our first names,\" it means that they are connected, and that they have \"a different way of knowing each other.\" She says she knows her students and her grandchildren by their first names, and she encourages listeners to visit her \"like grandma Ethel.\"',NULL,NULL),(61281,209,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/8ms5hm/Turn_Out_July_26bjaj1.mp3','2023-08-03 21:36:19',143961989,'2024-01-04 09:31:12',NULL,'The dance space is a place where people come to dance. We\'ve got a special day planned for you, and it\'s a day to celebrate the life and legacy of the great woman Ethel Bruno.\n\nShe passed away on July 24th, and we\'re celebrating her legacy today with a special program. First up is a live broadcast with Inica Hamilton, who introduces us to Ethel. Ethel was born in Harlem and began her career as a dancer at age three. She went on to appear on Ken Murrays show and after accompanying a buddy to the cab, held an audition. She dedicated her life in Montreal to the art of hoofing. Ethel joins us and tells us all about her life.\n\nShe grew up in Harlem, and her favorite thing to do was to call people by their first names. She calls people by the names of their grandchildren, and they all know her that way. She says that she is like a grandmother to her kids. She tells us that her first name is Miss Swing, and she\'s had many beautiful names. Her first name was Mr. Swing, but she became Miss Swing after her partner died in Vietnam. She was Miss Swing everywhere she went.',NULL,NULL),(61282,209,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/ci289y/turn_out_19th_july8rijm.mp3','2023-07-25 21:04:03',143961989,'2024-01-04 09:10:37',NULL,'I\'m Inica Hamilton and this is Turn Out on CIIT 89.5. We\'re back on the air to talk about the lates