am. He is also listening to Kaleidoscope on the Sentinels marvelous Kaleidoscope',NULL,NULL),(61322,81,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/07/24/The Sentinel’s Marvellous Kaleidoscope - July 24, 2023 at 15:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-07-24 15:00:00',86507648,'2024-01-03 13:53:07',NULL,'In this installment of the Sentinels Marvelous Kaleidoscope, we learn more about the music being played, the origins of the music, and the artists who will be performing at the upcoming festival, the Hillside Festival. We also learn that Owen Pallet will be playing at the festival, and that Paragon of Order will perform on the same day. We learn that the festival is being held at the Guelph lake island, which is on the southern tip of Lake Ontario, Canada, and we learn that it is the first festival of its kind in Canada.',NULL,NULL),(61323,81,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/07/17/The Sentinel’s Marvellous Kaleidoscope - July 17, 2023 at 15:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-07-17 15:00:00',86507648,'2024-01-03 13:12:29',NULL,'In this chapter, Nicholas Cooper, the guardian overseer of the Underground Sound Lab, speaks about the diversity of music being produced in the U.S. and its contributions to the world. He notes that the majority are produced by people of color, and that many of these people are dismissed as \"uncredited contributions\" to the popular music sphere.\n\nHe also thanks the Black Independent Producer community for their contributions to underground music. The session begins with a new track from Elkan, a Canadian band that has just released an album called The Isolator. The track Ordinary Girl is one of the tracks on the album, and it is very effervescent. The other tracks in the session are from Edzuyu and her band, Grimaldas, and Kristian North. The first track is from their latest album, Hot Latch, which they have just released in a box.',NULL,NULL),(61324,82,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/07/31/Big Sis Radio - July 31, 2023 at 17:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-07-3