ee-Hub Community Bike Center at the Guelph Tool-Library, which will offer free access to repair space and services. The host also discusses the release of a new song by the band, Good Time, which has some swearing in it. He also discusses some of the other tracks on the album, including Intergalactic-Gore Wars, Subterfuge, and Seven Kingdoms',NULL,NULL),(61575,122,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/07/13/Forever Deaf - July 13, 2023 at 22:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-07-13 22:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-30 20:47:05',NULL,'This is a short introductory program by the founder of ED Video, a Guelph-based organization that provides training in the use of professional equipment and facilities for the production of short films, music, and art. The program begins with the launch of the ED Video website. The main goal of the program is to introduce listeners to the organization, its members, and the music that they can hear on the program. The first song that the founder plays is \"Fast as a Shark\" from Inferverdeath, the first song he ever played on the show. The second song is \"To Those Who Have Hurt\" from Restless and Wild.',NULL,NULL),(61576,140,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/08/05/Caribbean Anthology - August 5, 2023 at 17:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-08-05 17:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-30 20:34:25',NULL,'The second half of this program opens with Dr. Jarndyce welcoming the audience to the second part of the program. He tells them about the many great events taking place in and around the city of Toronto during the weekend. He also tells them that there are also great music acts performing during the festival. He then goes on to talk about the Kingdom of Carnival, which is a big festival happening in the city. It also has a lot of other great entertainment acts performing. The show closes with a big announcement about the upcoming Shine All Stars concert, which will be happening in both Toronto and New York.',NULL,NULL),(61577,140,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/08/05/Caribbean Anthology - August 5, 2023 at 16:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-08-05 16:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-30 20:17:30',NULL,'In this program, the host of the Campus Community Radio program at the university of Guelph introduces a new volunteer opportunity for the university\'s Media and Communications department. The university offers a wide range of media-related opportunities, including hosting a local radio show, producing music and live events, and creating public service announcements and ads. If you have an interest in music production or videography, the university is always looking for you to help. In addition, the University offers a variety of other volunteer opportunities. For example, if you\'re interested in music, you can host a local music show or contribute as a music editor.\n\nOr you can help produce live events and live music. Or, you might be interested in engineering one of the University\'s in-studio live streams, looking up the university on YouTube and helping document other local projects. No experience is necessary, but we\'ll help you develop skills. Whenever you want to volunteer, email us at vfcu.ca.',NULL,NULL),(61578,140,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/07/22/Caribbean Anthology - July 22, 2023 at 17:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-07-22 17:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-30 19:09:25',NULL,'On this week\'s episode of the Skol.house, we learn about the upcoming 13th annual Allora Riverfest. The festival will take place at Bissell Park from August 18 to August 20. We learn that there will also be music at the main stage, and that there is a need for artists to be part of the spotlight. If you\'re interested in being a part of this spotlight, you have to be a musician that has already recorded some music and has stage tracks. This is because this means that they already have a lot of artists that are serious about their craft.',NULL,NULL),(61579,143,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/08/05/Mach Vibe Radio - August 5, 2023 at 21:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-08-05 21:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-30 18:48:26',NULL,'This is a very brief introduction to the world of food. It\'s a short, introductory scene that describes how food is an important part of community life and provides a framework for understanding how food can be used to improve the lives of people in the community. The scene ends with a description of the food that is available for people to take home for their meals. The food is described as \"equality, dignified, and nourishing\" .',NULL,NULL),(61580,139,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/08/05/Bel Araby with CAWA - August 5, 2023 at 15:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-08-05 15:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-30 18:33:13',NULL,'This week on the Bridge Show, we catch up with the cast and crew of the science fiction show, Tails. Here\'s a little background info: the show is a science fiction radio show that airs every Thursday morning on CFRU and is hosted by a guy named Phil.\n\nHe\'s also a writer, and he\'s the guy who wrote the first book in the series, The Mysteries of Night. Phil is a friend of Phil\'s, and Phil is psyched to have him back. Phil and his wife are getting ready to leave for their vacation in Europe. Phil says goodbye to his wife, who he calls \"my friend, farewell.\"',NULL,NULL),(61581,145,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/07/30/Visions fugitives - July 30, 2023 at 09:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-07-30 09:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-30 18:10:11',NULL,'In this short program, Christopher Curry introduces himself as the \"Visions fugitives\" of the show he co-hosts with Fangwei. He explains that he and Fangwei are going to play music that is meant to be heard in different seasons. One week they\'ll play music from the past week, and the next week they will play music inspired by a specific theme.\n\nIn this case, the theme will be music from Arnold Schoenberg. The music that we hear today is a short piece by another one of Schoenberg\'s former associates, Ernst Krenek. The piece is called \"Three Merry Marches\" Opus 34. We\'ll hear another Opus number from here on out, though. The Opus number that we\'ll listen to is from another of Krenke\'s other former associates. He\'s called \"Opus 71\" and he\'s a composer by the name of Alexander Skriabbin.\n\nThe work that we listen to today is by the same artist. The performer is Vladimir Ashkenazi. This is also by Alexander Shriabin. We learn that this is the same guy who played the \"De Poem\" in the last program. The show ends with a sad announcement: there was a notable loss in the music world this week. It was a Japanese conductor named Yuzoto Toyama who died four days ago.',NULL,NULL),(61582,141,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/08/05/Alternativa Latinoamericana - August 5, 2023 at 19:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-08-05 19:00:00',86507648,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(61583,146,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/07/30/The Kookoo Bananas Variety Hour - July 30, 2023 at 10:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-07-30 10:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-30 17:09:13',NULL,'This week\'s show is called \"Awakening Up\" and focuses on organ donation. If you\'re looking for something to do, check out Be A Donor\'s new website. Be a donor, and you\'ll get a new set of lungs. And if you want to hear more music, head over to the Sound Waves Summer Concert Series at the Skull House. Every Saturday from July 1st through September 2nd from 3pm - 9pm, the sound of music will fill the air. You can also get tickets to the concerts for free by entering the word \"Sound Waves\" in the code on the CFRU.\n\ncom slash page. Sounds like a great summer day. This program opens with a warm welcome from the host of the show. The show starts off by playing some music from the 2019 edition of the Hillside Festival. The first song we hear is from a song called \"Ikusak\" from the 2017 album, \"Shelter As We Go\" by the artists Tangle. The festival\'s main theme this year is \"Stories\" and the first song that we hear about is from one of these artists.\n\nThe host says that being able to talk to some of the artists is a good way to hear their stories and to describe why they do what they do. He wants to continue playing music while the show is still going on. He also wants to play some more music later on in the program.',NULL,'The Corus is giving away free tickets to all summer long on their web site'),(61584,142,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/08/05/Tiempo de Mujeres - August 5, 2023 at 20:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-08-05 20:00:00',86507648,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(61585,144,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/07/30/The Underground - July 30, 2023 at 00:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-07-30 00:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-30 16:45:02',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(61586,140,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/07/22/Caribbean Anthology - July 22, 2023 at 16:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-07-22 16:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-30 16:31:22',NULL,'The Ontario Pirate Festival will take place in Guelph, Ontario on August 5th and August 6th. The festival will feature sword fighting, aerial work, music, and a marketplace of over forty vendors. The music will be provided by the likes of Robby Khan, who will be performing a song called \"Drinking with Icon and smoke shop.\n\n\" The festival is free to the public. Dr. Deaf, the founder of the festival, joins us to tell us about the festival. He tells us that it has been a crazy summer for the festival and that they are having a few shows. He says that one of them is going to be a show with Carol Brown, Jade Faith, and Leroy Gibbons. The show will be happening at the Royal city Studios. The founder is happy that the festival is happening in his hometown and that he can talk to people of Guelph about it.',NULL,NULL),(61587,143,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/07/29/Mach Vibe Radio - July 29, 2023 at 22:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-07-29 22:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-30 16:24:59',NULL,'The program opens with a brief history of the National Film Board and the importance of storytelling in Canada. The program then moves to a discussion of the roles that storytelling can play in Canadian history and culture. The audience is then introduced to some of the featured actors, including Larry O\'Brien, Fred O\'Ioi, Donald Trump, and the late, great Black American actress, Viola Black.',NULL,NULL),(61588,139,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/07/22/Bel Araby with CAWA - July 22, 2023 at 15:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-07-22 15:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-30 15:34:35',NULL,'This is the first of a series of live shows on the \"green screen dream machine\" where bands can perform in front of \"alternate backdrops\" transporting them to \"the wildest performance spaces\" .\n\nIf you\'re a musician and would like to be a part of this live show, get in touch with us at info@curriculum.ca. In this show, we\'re joined by an unknown guest, who introduces himself as \"new guest\" and tells us that he\'ll be doing a \"live interview\" with us today. We\'ll find out more about him later, but in the meantime, here\'s a little sample of what he\'s saying: \"We will be doing an interview with our old guest today.\n\n\" We\'re not quite sure what to make of this: \"Let\'s go!\" or \"We\'ll do a live interview\" or \"let\'s do a go!\" .',NULL,NULL),(61589,145,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/07/30/Visions fugitives - July 30, 2023 at 08:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-07-30 08:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-30 15:14:39',NULL,'The show is called \"Visions  Fugitives\" and it\'s co-hosted by Christopher Curry and Fangwei. The show has been going on for some time now and they\'ve been working on a bunch of ideas for the show.\n\nThe first thing that they decided to do was to focus on birds. Now that Fangwei\'s decided to stop doing this, they\'ll shift the focus to other animals. So, for instance, the show will focus on bats. And we\'re not just talking about bats, because there are lots of other animals that also go into hibernation during the summer.',NULL,NULL),(61590,141,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/08/05/Alternativa Latinoamericana - August 5, 2023 at 18:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-08-05 18:00:00',86507648,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(61591,146,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/07/16/The Kookoo Bananas Variety Hour - July 16, 2023 at 10:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-07-16 10:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-30 14:54:34',NULL,'This week on the Cuckoo-Bananas Variety Hour , we hear a little bit about the show\'s mission to \"inspire women\'s stories\" and about the program\'s partnership with the Spanish-speaking community, Pimpo-de-Mimuno.\n\nWe also learn that if you have a business, event, or initiative you\'d like to promote on the program, we can help you with the ad-buying process. If you\'re interested in having a public service announcement run on the show, please contact us at outreach@curriculum.ca. This week\'s episode is called \"Father\'s Day\" and it\'s a special edition of the program. We hear the song, \"You Can Count on Me,\" from the show \"My Two Dads,\" sung by Greg \"Agavendo\" Avagon. The song features a solo saxophone and is a great way to start a show. The whole gang is gathered in the studio to listen to the show. We learn that Father\'s day is coming up and that the gang has been waiting for it for a long time.\n\nThe gang decides to play some songs and tell their listeners what a great gift they got for their father. The first song they\'ll play is a song called \"Super Fun Happy Wake-Up Song,\" written by Jay Cherko. The show ends with a little announcement that \"Gregory Pepper and his troubles from his Black-Metal demo tape\"',NULL,'The first song from a guy named Jay Cherko is about a new baby named Olive'),(61592,142,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/07/29/Tiempo de Mujeres - July 29, 2023 at 20:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-07-29 20:00:00',86507648,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(61593,144,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/07/29/The Underground - July 29, 2023 at 23:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-07-29 23:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-30 14:26:46',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(61594,140,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/07/15/Caribbean Anthology - July 15, 2023 at 17:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-07-15 17:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-30 14:14:43',NULL,'Dr. Def thanks everyone for coming out to the first show and says that they\'re going to have another big one on August 19th. He thanks all of the crew and says they\'ve been working hard to make sure the show is a success. He also thanks Odie Tracey for helping out as well.\n\nThe show is all about bringing in the best of the best from the city. It\'ll be all about the music scene in the city, not just the city\'s music scene. He says if you\'re into EDM, rock, and roll, then this is the night for you. He\'s also psyched to announce that the show will feature four of the hottest acts in the music world, including Rasi and Kruma from One Trinity. They\'ll also be introducing some new acts to the city: Voss, who\'s bringing back the hip hop vibe, and Drew, who will be there representing all the females. Dr.Def says that if anyone missed the last show, it was definitely worth it.',NULL,NULL),(61595,143,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/07/29/Mach Vibe Radio - July 29, 2023 at 21:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-07-29 21:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-30 13:54:12',NULL,'We\'re back with a new episode of \"My vibe radio\" . We start off by saying that this is the first time we\'ve heard a song like this in a long time.\n\nThis is a little weird, but we\'re psyched to hear it. We also find out that the guy who\'s hosting this show is a guy named \"Yardy\" , who is kind of a nerd, but also a little crazy. He\'s got a new song out for you, and it\'s called \"The One and Only 93.3 FM Baby.\" We find out who Yardy is, and then we find out why he\'s the guy hosting the show. We learn that Yardy\'s been sick for a',NULL,NULL),(61596,139,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/07/15/Bel Araby with CAWA - July 15, 2023 at 15:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-07-15 15:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-30 13:29:58',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(61597,145,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/07/23/Visions fugitives - July 23, 2023 at 09:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-07-23 09:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-30 13:07:50',NULL,'The show opens with a description of Visions Fugitives, a program co-produced by Christopher Curry and Fangwei. The two of them discuss the music they have just listened to. They decide to revisit Mozart\'s Opus 17 and conclude with some of Shostakovich\'s earlier works, including his famous \"24 Preludes\" and \"Opus 34.\" They conclude by listening to a recording by Bill Linwood of Horbu, a work written by Christopher Butterfield in 2001.',NULL,NULL),(61598,141,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/07/22/Alternativa Latinoamericana - July 22, 2023 at 19:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-07-22 19:00:00',86507648,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(61599,146,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/07/09/The Kookoo Bananas Variety Hour - July 9, 2023 at 10:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-07-09 10:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-30 12:53:12',NULL,'This is the second episode of the animated program, which takes place in the home of the Flying Bananas. It features a song called \"Fuzzy Logic,\" which is a concept introduced by the song\'s composer, Jerry Paper. The song describes the ability of a machine to \"program something into a computer that is not a yes nor a no but a maybe.\" The song also features a bunch of animals and bears in a party. The animated program concludes with the song \"A Bunch of Bears.\"',NULL,'Rowan is a \"router for the computer\" because he knows that his task is not as difficult as the \"enorm'),(61600,142,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/07/22/Tiempo de Mujeres - July 22, 2023 at 20:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-07-22 20:00:00',86507648,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(61601,144,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/07/23/The Underground - July 23, 2023 at 00:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-07-23 00:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-30 12:25:46',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(61602,140,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/07/15/Caribbean Anthology - July 15, 2023 at 16:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-07-15 16:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-30 12:13:27',NULL,'Dr. Def returns to the Caribbean Anthology to deliver a short message to the crew and to announce the upcoming events. He also mentions that the upcoming event, Spotlight 4, will be held on August 19th. He adds that he will be returning with several other crew members, including: Voice of Gru, Sidney Morris, and Mr. Voss. He mentions that they have also added a new crew member, V\'s .',NULL,NULL),(61603,143,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/07/22/Mach Vibe Radio - July 22, 2023 at 22:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-07-22 22:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-30 11:48:11',NULL,'In this episode, we hear from Doug Blackwood, the host of the show \"Seems Like Old Times\" on CFRU 92.3. He\'s looking for his son, EZ, and he wants to know how he\'s feeling. He tells his son to dance and to converse.\n\nHe wants to help him find the lyrics to a song called \"Sounded Out,\" which is about a family who\'s trying to find its way in the world. The song is called \"Mach Vibre.\" It\'s a reference to a famous quote from Shakespeare\'s \"Julius Caesar,\" in which Caesar warns his friend that if he doesn\'t speak the language, he\'ll lose his friends. For example, if you\'re trying to get your friends to sing along to the song \"You\'re Listening to Mach Vib,\" they\'ll all be jealous. But if they can\'t sing along, they\'re going to lose their friends. This is a great idea, because it means they can start a conversation.',NULL,NULL),(61604,145,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/07/23/Visions fugitives - July 23, 2023 at 08:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-07-23 08:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-30 11:30:26',NULL,'Fangwei and Christopher host a music show called \"Vigilence Fu-Give\", in which one of them picks a piece of music and the other picks a response from Fangwei. The music selection is eclectic, and the responses to the music must be tied to themes explored in the music. This week Fangwei will respond to one of Christopher\'s pieces about bats, and he will interpret the theme of \"hibernatory.\n\n\" Bats, he says, are the only animals that have mastered the art of living in the air; they physically extended the air from the earth\'s surface. Fangwei has also found a piece called \"Ascension\" by the Chinese composer Leiliang, which seems to be a fitting response to the bat-inspired music. The pieces are also from a collection called \"Miglieu,\" which is a \"miscellaneous, not milieu,\" but a \"midieu.\" The musicians on Ascension are listed as \"various artists.\" The music on \"Respectively Ascension\" is also from Miglieu, but the artists on \"Winged Creatures\" are not listed. So, we\'ve heard two works from Leiliang.',NULL,NULL),(61605,141,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/07/22/Alternativa Latinoamericana - July 22, 2023 at 18:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-07-22 18:00:00',86507648,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(61606,142,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/07/15/Tiempo de Mujeres - July 15, 2023 at 20:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-07-15 20:00:00',86507648,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(61607,144,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/07/22/The Underground - July 22, 2023 at 23:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-07-22 23:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-30 11:05:40',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(61608,143,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/07/22/Mach Vibe Radio - July 22, 2023 at 21:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-07-22 21:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-30 10:47:19',NULL,'This week, we\'re talking about the fact that only 31% of the people in the province of Ontario have registered to donate their organ and tissue. That means that on average, every three days, one person dies because an organ isn\'t available to save him or her. If you were to donate your organs and tissue, you\'d save eight lives and improve the lives of 75 people. Sign up to be an organ donor at BeAorDon.ca. Then tune in every Wednesday morning to The Stillness & Dancing on CFRU. From now until July 30, the outdoors will be transformed into a festival.',NULL,NULL),(61609,145,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/07/16/Visions fugitives - July 16, 2023 at 09:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-07-16 09:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-30 10:29:50',NULL,'The show is also available on Soundcloud. The show\'s co-host, Christopher Curry, opens the show by introducing us to the show. He explains that the show is called \"Viveence Fugitive\" and that he and Fangwei are performing music that they have selected for the spotlight.\n\nThe music will be selected by one of the two performers. One of the performers will pick a piece of music that is centered around a theme, and the other will choose a response piece to the music that was played before. The first piece will be a piece from Arnold Schoenberg. The other will be by another composer who was associated with Schoenberg. This is a short piece by another person. It is called Drei Lustig / March f/r Blasser / Orkester / Opus 34. The third piece is a piece by Ernst Krennik. The piece is called Three merry marches for wind orchestra. The Opus 34 piece is performed by the Baden-Baden Southwest Wind Orchestra. Now the show will continue with Opus numbering spotlight.\n\nHe says that he has invoked the names Schoenberg and Shreiber in the show, and that there is no way he could do this without tying in numerology. He\'s going to play an Opus 71 work. The performer is Vladimir Ashkenazi. The work is called De Poem and is performed in two parts. The second part is a work by Alexander Skriabbin. The program ends with an announcement about a recent death in the music world. It',NULL,NULL),(61610,141,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/07/15/Alternativa Latinoamericana - July 15, 2023 at 19:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-07-15 19:00:00',86507648,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(61611,144,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/07/16/The Underground - July 16, 2023 at 00:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-07-16 00:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-30 10:07:54',NULL,'Three people have been shot in the state of Georgia. The sheriff says that he\'s trying to track down Andrew Longmore, who\'s a suspect in the shooting. There\'s also a $10,000 reward offered for information leading to Longmore\'s arrest. Meanwhile, in Venezuela, opposition leader Maria Carina Machado has said that some community groups attacked her and her entourage. A lot of people have gotten out of the way for her, but one of them was her son Morty. The narrator says that the only thing that\'s known is that Morty is cute, and then he goes on to say that his mother should \"put your back and stop attacking me\" .',NULL,NULL),(61612,143,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/07/15/Mach Vibe Radio - July 15, 2023 at 22:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-07-15 22:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-30 09:46:36',NULL,'The festival is wrapping up, but the sun is still shining, and the vibe of the place is still high. The music is still loud, the lights still flicker, and everyone\'s still hanging out with friends. Everyone\'s doing their best to make it seem like the festival is a success, but there\'s one problem: the festival isn\'t about the music, it\'s about how much money the festival will make.',NULL,NULL),(61613,145,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/07/16/Visions fugitives - July 16, 2023 at 08:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-07-16 08:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-30 09:34:27',NULL,'In this episode of All World Wide at Once, the narrator explains that he is the voice of another show he co-hosts with Fangwei, called Visions Fugitives. The two of them have been working on a show called 17 Opus, where they will each choose a piece of music and respond to it with another piece. The pieces chosen by one of them will be connected to the previous week\'s work. This week, however, they will focus on other animals, specifically bats.',NULL,NULL),(61614,141,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/07/15/Alternativa Latinoamericana - July 15, 2023 at 18:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-07-15 18:0