 Plus, the Russian government has been spying on the United States, and the Russians have been trying to help Donald Trump get elected president.',NULL,NULL),(61619,143,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/07/08/Mach Vibe Radio - July 8, 2023 at 22:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-07-08 22:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-30 07:55:48',NULL,'In this second half of the first half, the gang is introduced, and the lyrics are given by the song\'s lead singer, Canadian Yardy, who introduces himself as \"Donnie Darko\" . We learn that he is a drunk, and that he lives in Barstow, California, where he runs a bar and sells illegal drugs. The song ends with one of the gang\'s most famous lines: \"Education then, beyond everything else, is an equalizer of conditions.\" This is a quote from Horace Mann\'s 1848 work, Education, which, according to Yardy\'s lyrics, \"educates,\" meaning \"gives to\" and \"instructions.\"',NULL,NULL),(61620,145,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/07/09/Visions fugitives - July 9, 2023 at 08:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-07-09 08:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-30 07:11:49',NULL,'The Visual Fugitive is a new classical music show co-hosted by Christopher Curry and Fangwei. Each week, one person will choose a piece of music and the other person will respond to the piece with his or her own selections.\n\nThe show will be a new one, and the narrator notes that this is a brand new show. He also notes that the show is a bit different than the previous ones, since it is a series of one-week performances. The first piece is a Cyber Bird Concerto by Takashi Yoshimitsu. The concerto was inspired by his sister who was dying and wished that she could one day be a bird again in her own life. The other piece is performed by Sugawa on the Saxophone.',NULL,NULL),(61621,144,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/07/08/The Underground - July 8, 2023 at 23:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-07-08 23:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-30 06:48:36',NULL,'The Underground is a short program about how to do things in the most relaxed way possible. It\'s all about how easy it is to do everything in a way that\'s more relaxed and less stressful. This program is all about learning how to be a good, clean, and organized person.',NULL,NULL),(61622,153,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/07/30/Backtracks - July 30, 2023 at 22:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-07-30 22:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-30 06:31:28',NULL,'This is a rebroadcast of a February show called \"Changes\" that was originally aired in February of last year. The show\'s host, Eileen, is going through a big change right now and needs to get some sleep. She wants to start a listeners corner on the show and invite listeners to send her their stories, ideas, thoughts, and themes. She\'ll give them a shout out and she\'ll send them two emails. The first show will be called \"Moby Grape\" and the last will be \"Doug Hell\" .\n\nIt\'ll be a juicy music sandwich. Welcome back to the show with Host Eileen. Backtracks, a program dedicated to reviving forgotten tracks, B sides, and great \"dickers\" to lights of the glorious 60\'s and 70\'s. Lately, though, he\'s been throwing in some new material and a bit of mainstream material. He says he usually works from a theme, which is like, \"Starting and stopping going off in new direction, or just spinning your wheels.\n\n\" He says that he loves Canada and that people can change and move in any direction they want. The only constant is death and taxes, which, according to him, are the only things that can stay the same. He\'s going to stitch together a \"loosely woven cloth\" of a show. He just did a show with Doug Hell, Hamilton, and a bunch of other guys and he\'ll play something from the show',NULL,NULL),(61623,153,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/07/23/Backtracks - July 23, 2023 at 22:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-07-23 22:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-30 05:14:12',NULL,'This week, Sarah Willow from the local community radio station, CFRU, gives a shout-out to all the awesome people who work at the station.\n\nShe also mentions that there\'s a special event coming up on the station on July 25th. This is a fund-raising night for Art Not Shame, a new non-profit organization that\'s trying to open a community arts hub in Guelph. The event will include music, art making, tarot reading, and a silent art auction. If you are a music fan, we recommend checking out Silence Guelph, a brand new music venue in 2023. Sounds is offering low-cost studio space to creatives in town.',NULL,NULL),(61624,153,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/07/16/Backtracks - July 16, 2023 at 22:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-07-16 22:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-30 04:52:52',NULL,'This is a rebroadcast of the first episode of Backtracks, a program that focuses on reviving lost music. The program\'s host, Eileen, says that he\'s going through a big change in his life and needs to get some sleep.\n\nHe wants to start a listeners\' corner at Backtracks so that he can get his listeners\' stories, thoughts, and theme ideas. He\'s got a show coming up next Sunday with some fresh material. So, back to Backtracks. Backtracks\'s a program dedicated to reviving forgotten tracks, rarities, and great Dick-to-Lights from the 60s. Sometimes it\'s more mainstream material, and sometimes it just happens to be a theme. This week\'s show is called \"Changes\" from Moby Grape\'s self-titled album from 1967. It\'s about how people change and how people can move on. People can change their style, move their gender, move on, get a new job, do the new crowd, change your age, etc.\n\nThe only constants in life is death and taxes. So back to the show. Back to the listeners: Backtracks has been rebroadcasting some of its earlier episodes. The first show was called \"Change\" from \"Moby Grape\" and it was about how changes happen in the world. The second show was titled \"It\'s A Bear And A Web Of His Power\" and the third show was named \"Angels, Change Off',NULL,NULL),(61625,152,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/07/30/Through the Looking Glass - July 30, 2023 at 21:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-07-30 21:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-30 04:29:55',NULL,'Alice and Charlotte start their journey through the \"looking glass\" and follow the tracks on the show. The first track is \"Noble Oak\" from the \"When it finds you and evening star\" album. The second track is Wolves Gather. The third track is called \"I am a rocket ship from La cruella and gravity\" and the fourth track is titled \"Everyone is dead except us and Hulk .\n\n. if you\'re looking for the playlist it\'s posted on the Looking Glass website under the program page sometime next few weeks. Alice says he\'s been a lazy music correspondent in the past couple of weeks so he wants to treat his listeners with two songs tonight. He says he saw \"the incredible\" Patricia Vonn yesterday and she made him howl. He tells them that for 33 years she has been his partner in crime with Robert LaRoche, who is also part of a band named The Size. Robert has released an album called \"1000\" and before that \"the gins\" from \"It\'s a life with effigy\" with an introduction from our German music reporter Melanie. He hopes his listeners will join him again next Sunday when he continues his \"journey through the Looking glass\" with new music.',NULL,NULL),(61626,154,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/07/31/This Night Wounds Time - July 31, 2023 at 01:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-07-31 01:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-30 04:11:41',NULL,'This week\'s show is called \"Off the Beat,\" and it\'s all about music. It\'s about music from Corriente province in Argentina, where a lot of the music is made. It sounds like a mix of electronica, folk, and Latin American music. The first song is called Chamame de Los Estaros, which means \"I am in a crisis. I am in the middle of a tragedy. This is a character study, not a celebration. If you speak Spanish, this will be a \"character study\" not a \"celebration.\"',NULL,NULL),(61627,150,'https://archive.cfru.