NULL,NULL),(61632,149,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/07/23/La Buena Onda - July 23, 2023 at 17:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-07-23 17:00:00',86507648,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(61633,152,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/07/16/Through the Looking Glass - July 16, 2023 at 21:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-07-16 21:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-30 01:10:58',NULL,'The show opens with Alice, who introduces herself as \"Alice.\" She tells us that she\'s going to travel through the \"Looking Glass\" with her friend and fellow musician, Dan Mangan, in order to listen to music. They start by going through some of the tracks from Brian Morgan\'s \"Curve of the Earth\" and \"All Mother and Warning signs,\" before moving on to \"Depths of Black\" from \"About the Future,\" which has been posted on the Looking Glass\'s website. They\'ll also go through some other tracks from the album \"Being Somewhere and Just know It\" . The band is called \"Apples,\" and the song is \"Depth of Black.\" They\'re also going to go through a different direction this time, since it\'s their German music correspondent, Melanie,\'s birthday weekend. The next song is from the band \"Snootsify your life\" , a cover of Talking Heads\' \"Burning Down the House.\n\n\" The show\'s next artist is the band Greg Clark and \"The Mad Farks,\" who have been listening to \"Conscience Pilot\" from Army of the Devils and \"Penn and Bray\" from Arcade with Joel Shrug. The show closes with a track by \"Ivy,\" a track from the 25th Anniversary of Apartment Life .',NULL,NULL),(61634,154,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/07/30/This Night Wounds Time - July 30, 2023 at 23:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-07-30 23:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-30 00:51:14',NULL,'On this edition of This Night Wound\'s Time, the host of the local CFRU 93.3 FM show, the Christopher Curry, explains that the show will shift its focus from presenting music that is too \"off-center\" to focusing on music from different regions of the world. He explains that he is going to start the show by playing some music from the new release collection of music by the Taishi Sori Trio on the show. The title of the album is \"Continuing,\" which means \"to continue.\" The show will also include some of the music from San Juan, the state of Puerto Rico.',NULL,NULL),(61635,150,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/07/23/Zombie Jamboree - July 23, 2023 at 19:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-07-23 19:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-30 00:29:21',NULL,'The first hour of the Zombie Jamboree is over, and it\'s time to go home. The students at the school have been listening to some great music, and they\'re psyched to hear some new music from around the world.\n\nThey\'re all psyched for the next day\'s Zombie Jamboree. Back to our story. The music is really hot, and the students are psyched for it. They play a song called \"Doppelganger\" that\'s translated from Arabic and sounds a lot like \"Repression equals cheese and cauliflower\" . They also play some other songs that sound like they came straight out of the summer heat. The school has a zombie music festival, and this one\'s going to be especially hot.\n\nThere are two songs that really capture the vibe of the festival. The first is a mashup of Turkish and Turkish music that sounds like they\'ve been mixing it up for a long time. The second is a song by Badia Buriz that sounds just like \"The Limits of Control\" , which is a really cool song. The third song is \"The Zombie Wind Down\" and the kids are psyched to',NULL,NULL),(61636,149,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/07/23/La Buena Onda - July 23, 2023 at 16:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-07-23 16:00:00',86507648,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(61637,152,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/07/09/Through the Looking Glass - July 9, 2023 at 21:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-07-09 21:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-30 00:07:04',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(61638,154,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/07/24/This Night Wounds Time - July 24, 2023 at 01:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-07-24 01:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-29 23:10:44',NULL,'This week on the CFRU Radio show, the hosts discuss the music of a band called Asterius. The band is from San Juan, a province in the interior of Argentina, which borders Chile.\n\nThey\'re a \"stoner band\" from the desert, as they like to say. The album they\'re listening to is called Horace, which means \"after the Egyptian gods.\" They\'ll hear a track called \"The Journey\" in English, which they think sounds like a Journey song. The show is also going to be listening to music by Oleksander Zuzaki, a musician from Ukraine. He\'s an artist in San Juan named Not So Evil. The first song they\'ll listen to is an EP from the band called Solar Drone. The second song is from an album called Historia de Una Esperanza, which sounds like \"Stories of a Kind.\" The third song is called Sobra Tierra nuestros Desierto and it sounds like it\'s going to translate into English. The program ends with a shout-out to the host, Christopher Curry, who\'s hosting the program. This is a geographical section of the program, which is meant to be a sort of mini-series of spotlights on different artists from different parts of the country.\n\nThis week, they are spotlighting a musician named Carlos Rivera who\'d been working as a percussionist for a local band called Rivero Hure. The song is about a guy named Roxane who',NULL,NULL),(61639,150,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/07/23/Zombie Jamboree - July 23, 2023 at 18:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-07-23 18:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-29 22:51:29',NULL,'The band is in the middle of a big set when they hear the sound of a crowd outside. They come back onstage and start another big set. This time, they\'re doing a little dance party. This one\'s called \"Sound Waves\" and it\'s hosted by the local rock band, the Skull House.\n\nWe\'ll find out more about the band later. The band starts off with a bunch of music from Africa, and then they play a song called \"Hot Passing Clouds\" and a song from Spain called \"Head in the Clouds\" . Then they play some more music from the US, and they start off with some music from Olela, a country in the south of Spain. Sounds like a lot of music to us. Then the band plays some more stuff, and we\'re back to the dance floor.',NULL,NULL),(61640,149,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/07/16/La Buena Onda - July 16, 2023 at 17:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-07-16 17:00:00',86507648,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(61641,154,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/07/24/This Night Wounds Time - July 24, 2023 at 00:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-07-24 00:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-29 22:33:28',NULL,'This week, the show opens with a description of the geography of the world. The show\'s host, Christopher Curry, is the creator of the \"Geographic Spotlight\" series, which is a series of segments within a show that analyze the world in terms of its geography. The first segment in the series is called \"Discovering Russia,\" and it involves playing music from all of the federal subjects of Russia, the largest country on the planet by area. The purpose of the segments is to explore the various types of federal subjects. The second segment is \"Canada,\" and the third is \"China,\" which is the third largest country by territory after Russia and Canada.\n\nThe fourth is \"The United States of American,\" which includes the 50 states plus the District of Columbia, plus five territories, including Puerto Rico and US Virgin Islands. The fifth segment is Brazil, the sixth is Australia, the seventh is India, and the eighth is the smallest country on earth, the tiny island of Lahshadwe',NULL,NULL),(61642,150,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/07/16/Zombie Jamboree - July 16, 2023 at 19:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-07-16 19:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-29 22:11:28',NULL,'Back to the first hour of the second hour. This is the hour where the band recognizes World Population Day. They\'re going to encourage people to go out and talk to the strangers around them. They start off with a song called Etika.\n\nThen they go into a whole different part of the French Diaspora on a bayou drive. The song is Bayou Drive open sloppy close parentheses, like Chenier\'s. Then we go back to the original song. It\'s called Bon Appetit. Sounds like it\'s about a Cajun meal. Then it gets back to French. It gets a little bit more French now as it was back in the day. Then the group switches over to a French song called Stereo Total. It sounds a bit like it was originally by Serge Gainbourg. Then Bertrand Belline sings Su La Coule.\n\nThen Gotopo sings Fuerza Nata. Then Alcawa sings Two in a Row. Then there\'s a band called Loom that\'s from Alberta. Then Bruce Coburn sings When The Spirit Walks In the Room. It is the last song of the night. The band will continue to play the next Sunday at 6:00pm. Then Sarah Willow will play some more music.',NULL,NULL),(61643,149,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/07/16/La Buena Onda - July 16, 2023 at 16:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-07-16 16:00:00',86507648,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(61644,154,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/07/23/This Night Wounds Time - July 23, 2023 at 23:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-07-23 23:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-29 21:51:32',NULL,'The show starts with a description of the purpose of the show, which is to feature music that is \"off-center,\" or off-center in nature. The show will then shift to the geographical \"spotlight series entry\" of the night. Instead of playing music all over the map, the show will play music from one province of the country, where it will end with the city that the show is based in, Buenos Aires. This means that they will be playing music from the province that they\'re based in. They\'ll also be playing some music from Louise Campbell, a Montreal artist, who has just released a new album on the label Redshift called Sources.\n\nThe track on the album, \"People of the Sea,\" was written in the days before the Pandemic in 2019, right before the