hat they should go to their local RBC branch to ask why they shouldn\'t be supporting climate change.\n\nHe also tells them that there is a march coming up that day in Toronto, and they have a QR code that can be used to find where the food is and where to RSVP. Finally, he gives a shout out to Morgan and says that he and his friends are here to celebrate water. He has a pile on his skateboard and would like anyone to take a small amount of tobacco to offer to the river to say thanks. He says that they also have food and water, and then there is pizza. Before he leaves, he announces that they will be wrapping up their Summer Year of skeeming series. They will also be starting a workshop on digital security.',NULL,NULL),(62350,86,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/08/28/The Deep House Project - August 28, 2023 at 22:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-08-28 22:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-18 21:06:19',NULL,'The Deep House Project returns to its old stomping grounds for its 15th annual Community Book Sale. The sale runs from September 20 th -24 th and all proceeds benefit the library. The show starts off with a classic track from Algeman, who has released his latest cowboy track. There are also some newer tracks from Pavzo, Superduper, and others. The program closes out with Sweet Leads, a song about warmer weather, which is one of the most popular songs on the show.',NULL,NULL),(62351,87,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/08/28/Back in the USSR - August 28, 2023 at 23:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-08-28 23:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-18 20:50:46',NULL,'In this week\'s program, the German Foreign Minister, Frank-Walter Steinmeier, praises the leadership of the Communist Party in the former Soviet Union. He also discusses the BRICS countries, which he describes as \"fast-growing economies.\" He says that the countries have joined together to create an alternative to the World Bank and the International Monetary Fund.\n\nThe BRICS countries were created in 2009 and have since been working together to form a new economic system. But the process of creating this new system has been accelerated by the United States and the European Union seizing Russian assets and placing unprecedented sanctions on Russia in response to Russia\'s invasion of Ukraine in 2022. That means that one-third or one-fifth of the world\'s population is under direct Western sanctions.',NULL,NULL),(62352,82,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/08/28/Big Sis Radio - August 28, 2023 at 17:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-08-28 17:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-18 20:29:54',NULL,'On this episode of Big Sister Radio, the host, Arlo, welcomes listeners to the program and tells them that he\'s going to play some new music. He\'s got a new track from Bully, a new song from Goodnight Sunrise, and an updated version of a song from Mac DeMarco\'s new album. He also tells listeners about a new policy in Canada that means that all cosmetic products tested on animals are banned. He hopes that this will be an influential change in other countries who still allow animal testing.',NULL,NULL),(62353,79,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/08/28/Breezy Breakfast Radio - August 28, 2023 at 10:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-08-28 10:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-18 20:07:31',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(62354,79,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/08/28/Breezy Breakfast Radio - August 28, 2023 at 09:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-08-28 09:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-18 19:15:06',NULL,'This week\'s program is called \"The Breezy Breakfast\" and it\'s all about the health care system in Guelph. It\'s hosted by CFRU 98.3 FM and it starts off with a question: \"What is the State of Our Healthcare System in Guelph?\n\n\" This week, we hear from a woman named Melissa Skinner, the Vice President of Patient Services at the General Hospital. She\'ll tell us all about how the hospital plans to build a new hospital and how the community plays a role in funding the new hospital. She also tells us how many people are stuck in the hospital purgatory, waiting for long-term-care beds. We also learn that there are many emergency room visits and ambulance wait times. All in all, the program concludes with a Q&A with the moderator.\n\nPhil welcomes us to the program and thanks us for listening. Before we get started, Phil says that this is the ninth month in the Islamic calendar and that it is a time to pray, reflect, and be a community. He also acknowledges that Guelph is home to the ancestral homeland',NULL,NULL),(62355,84,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/08/28/Blues Around the Block - August 28, 2023 at 20:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-08-28 20:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-18 17:07:20',NULL,'Mac Dee is back on the show with a new song, this time it\'s \"Blues Around the Block\" and he\'s here to tell us that you can listen to the show on CFRU\'s nine3.3 FM station in Guelph, Ontario. He\'s also here to let us know that he has some new songs to share. First up is \"Down Child\" from Downchild\'s 13th album, \"Lucky 13,\" and \"Do Drop In\" from his \"Aquaman\" album in 2023. Next is \"Thor and the thundercats\" from their \"You\'re a',NULL,NULL),(62356,85,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/08/28/Ripcord Radio - August 28, 2023 at 21:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-08-28 21:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-18 16:54:56',NULL,'This is the second episode of the \"Ripcord Radio\" program, and it\'s about as good as it gets. It\'s all about the music, and this time around, the music is coming from all over the world. This is a mix of old and new music from all around the world, including some new music that\'s coming up in a few minutes.\n\nThe first band we hear is from Illinois, and they\'re called Braid. They have a song called \"Idolescent Hobo\" from their 1996 album \"Easy Instructions For Complex Machinery\". The band also has a song from their classic album \"Red Light\" called \"AJJ\" and they have a track called \"Disposable Everything\" from this year\'s \"Druse Everything\". And finally, we hear \"Easy Money\" from a