bout his trip to the Caribbean. The second part is a description of the cities and towns he passed through. The host describes Cornwall as a \"kind of an embarrassment\" , and Trois Riviere as \"the worst part of not kept up\" . He also describes the cost of living in Canada as \"so expensive to live\" and the fact that \"Toronto\" is the most expensive city in the country.',NULL,NULL),(62614,163,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/8dtt7h/September_9th_2023_Critic_s_Circle5yy84.mp3','2023-09-09 14:11:09',143961989,'2023-12-15 04:54:18',NULL,'The program begins with Phil Taylor, the host of a local talk show in Stratford, Ontario. He tells listeners that he\'s there to promote a play called Queen Mev. He\'s also going to show a movie with Daniel Garber, who\'s going to give a review and then he\'ll give an interview. Phil also tells listeners about Lynn Slotkin and her review of the play. Phil and Lynn chat about the weather and theater attendance. Lynn says that the weather\'s not affecting theater attendance, because people are prepared. Phil says that\'s true, and that shows that people are committed to the theater.',NULL,NULL),(62616,163,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/fzz2hj/September_2nd_2023_Critic_s_Circlealk3b.mp3','2023-09-09 14:10:44',143961989,'2023-12-15 04:33:19',NULL,'Phil Taylor hosts this week\'s episode of The Circle. The show opens with an interview with Daniel Slaskin at the movies, followed by a review of the latest play by Lynn Slakins.\n\nLynn has a guest on the show, Ken McDonald, a set designer who has designed sets for many theaters and opera companies across Canada and the U.S. Ken\'s latest work is for Frankenstein at the Stratford festival. He tells the story of how he went from art to design when his friend, Don Shipley, needed a set for a dinner party at the Belcro theatre. It was like a Judy Garland and Mickey Rooney thing.',NULL,NULL),(62617,163,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/9tacmz/August_26th_2023_Critic_s_Circleav1ri.mp3','2023-09-