,(62634,219,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/gejdiq/ES230906.mp3','2023-09-08 00:44:10',139183631,'2023-10-28 11:48:51',NULL,'James Bailey is host of CIUT 89.5 FM\'s Electric Sense. This week he\'ll be playing two different trios, one of which is Bill Gilliam, the great piano player about town. He\'ll also play something called Cicada Musings, a collection of music from the Cicadas.',NULL,'James Bailey is host of CIUT 89.5 FM\'s Electric Sense. This week'),(62635,212,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/a6xy6i/IvyFull.mp3','2023-09-08 02:05:00',282398531,'2023-12-14 20:45:18',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(62636,218,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/x96fm5/The_Taylor_Report_September_48z07q.mp3','2023-09-08 18:11:10',143961989,'2023-12-14 20:32:27',NULL,'Phil Taylor and Phil Conlon talk about how the U.S has dropped tons of bombs on places like Libya, Syria, and Serbia. They also talk about Tony Lea, the head of the Chicago Labor Council, and his union\'s contract dispute.',NULL,NULL),(62637,218,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/ervrpa/tylor_aug_28aw026.mp3','2023-09-08 18:09:34',143961989,'2023-12-14 19:11:35',NULL,'Phil Taylor is on the air with Phil Conlon trying to find a way to get a microphone. They are talking to a reporter named Sandra Farias who has been reporting from South America for many years. She, too, has lived in Chile and Argentina. She is also a correspondent. She has written about the situation in both countries. They discuss the recent unrest in Argentina. They also discuss the right-wing movement in the country. They talk to the reporter, who has lived and worked in South America.',NULL,NULL),(62638,218,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/qptkci/taylor_report_aug_217prji.mp3','2023-09-08 18:08:26',143961989,'2023-12-14 18:50:22',NULL,'This is the second of two parts in which the host discusses the recent violence against the Eritrean community in Toronto. The first part deals with the idea of a \"pogrom,\" a term used to describe a situation in which people are forcibly removed from their homes.\n\nThe host explains that the perpetrators of the violence are not responsible for the violence, but rather they are planning an attack on the Eritrean Canadian community. He tells the audience that the Eritrean Canadians are the \"frontline\" for human rights defenders in Canada. He explains that this is because they have the right to hold their events, even though they are older than Eritrea. This Wednesday, as part of the Toronto International Festival, a man wearing blue shirts is carrying sticks.',NULL,NULL),(62639,257,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/ra5wmn/September_7_2023_Psychedelic_Stoner_Rockba6kq.mp3','2023-09-08 16:21:23',287962512,'2023-12-14 18:26:17',NULL,'In this program, Ken Stauer continues his program of psychedelic rock. The station needs your help in reaching its goal of $100,000, so if you\'ve not yet donated, please visit the station\'s web site and give. Also, the station needs some help recruiting board members. If you can help, come to the next meeting of the board of directors and discuss how the station can be improved.',NULL,NULL),(62640,289,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/t4fwyb/The_Next_Stop_115aw9lw.mp3','2023-09-06 19:47:23',270598152,'2023-12-14 17:07:33',NULL,'This week\'s blue super moon will be featured in the program, as it is the second full blue moon in a month. The program will begin with the music from 2001\'s Space Odyssey, which is performed by the Berlin Philharmonia and Herbert vonKaryan. Next up is the music of the psychedelic rock band Kino, followed by the songs of The Kinks, The Doors, and more.',NULL,NULL),(62641,292,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/7ms784/September_8_2023_The_Cool_Side_of_the_Pillow_1_a51se.mp3','2023-09-08 19:36:37',287962512,'2023-12-14 16:48:04',NULL,'The narrator opens with a poem about \"finding the way between old and harders\" . The poem is about being in the present moment, not being too far ahead. It\'s about being where you are, not where you want to be. In the poem, we see that the narrator and his friend Lydia are both living in the past, but they\'re also living in a dream right now. The narrator, in the meantime, is trying to communicate to us that there\'s no order in the world, and that things are just as they are.',NULL,NULL),(62642,1551,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/xwimbr/SEPTEMBER7.mp3','2023-09-09 17:59:16',431961989,'2023-12-14 16:29:19',NULL,'In this edition of the host\'s show, we get back into the swing of things with a mix of music from the day. First off, we\'ve got some classic Tod Terry music. Then we get some new music from Taquena, Nathan Barato, Paranoid Jack, Atiras, and more. Next up is some music from UFG, who are celebrating their 25th anniversary this year. We also get some details about the upcoming Better Days reunion.',NULL,NULL),(62643,78,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/08/Morning Soul Shake-Up! - September 8, 2023 at 08:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-08 08:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-14 16:05:51',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(62644,78,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/07/Morning Soul Shake-Up! - September 7, 2023 at 08:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-07 08:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-14 15:07:52',NULL,'This is a special edition of Morning Soul Shake Up, a program that airs on CFRU FM and CIOIFM in Guelph and on Nahawk 91.5 in Hamilton every morning. The program is a mix of soul music and R&B. It starts out with a bang and then moves on to something more serious. It\'s a show about life on a college campus. There\'s no place like home, and there\'s lots of great food on campus. This is the program for students, parents, and anyone else who wants to be a part of the community. There are lots of',NULL,NULL),(62645,80,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/09/CFRU Playlist - September 9, 2023 at 18:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-09 18:00:00',86507648,'2023-09-10 02:46:52',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(62646,81,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/06/The Sentinel’s Marvellous Kaleidoscope - September 6, 2023 at 17:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-06 17:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-14 14:44:39',NULL,'The next time you hear a local musician perform, check out the new CFRU website where you can find out all about the university\'s music program, volunteer opportunities, and even how to make a donation to the university. This program is from the September 16th edition of the Guelph Jazz Fest. It was performed by the duo of Esmarie and Ajay. Before they play, they dedicate the set to Ajay, who they met in Turkey. They\'ve been hanging out at the festival all weekend.',NULL,NULL),(62647,80,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/08/CFRU Playlist - September 8, 2023 at 20:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-08 20:00:00',86638720,'2023-09-10 02:47:04',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(62648,80,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/08/CFRU Playlist - September 8, 2023 at 12:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-08 12:00:00',86638720,'2023-09-10 02:47:09',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(62649,90,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/07/Bridging The Social Distance - September 7, 2023 at 12:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-07 12:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-14 14:30:42',NULL,'This show is a re-broadcast of an earlier episode that Jenny Mitchell recorded for CFRU. This is an interview with Dave and Cormac of the band, Joyful Joyful. They are both from Peterborough, and they are both excited to be here. Dave is the joyful half, and Cormac is the other half. They\'ll be hoping that listeners will tune in to hear the origin story. If you have a way to describe the past, Jenny invites you to do so.',NULL,NULL),(62650,97,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/07/Wild Combination - September 7, 2023 at 01:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-07 01:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-14 14:05:52',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(62651,97,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/07/Wild Combination - September 7, 2023 at 00:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-07 00:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-14 13:43:16',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(62652,105,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/06/B Siide Radio - September 6, 2023 at 19:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-06 19:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-14 13:24:24',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(62653,106,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/06/Trail Mix - September 6, 2023 at 20:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-06 20:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-14 13:07:03',NULL,'We start off this week\'s show with a review of the upcoming 2022 Jazz Festival in Guelph, Ontario. We hear from Sam Shalabi, Land of Kush, which will be performed on its entirety at the festival. We also hear from Joshua Lerner, Natural Information Society, and Douglas T. Elly, Yes I am Lonely, and another new piece from Bill Orkus called Music for Guitars. Then we hear from Juan Deeb, Bill Orkut, and more new music. We finish off the show by playing a song from Eric Chenot\'s \"Mountain of Doom\" CD.',NULL,NULL),(62654,102,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/06/End Credits - September 6, 2023 at 15:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-06 15:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-14 12:52:15',NULL,'This episode of the End Credits, a local talk show hosted by Adam Donaldson, is a conversation between Adam and Tim Phillips, a member of the Hells Angels.\n\nAdam says that he was hanging out with his gang while they were on their break. He says that they just wanted to terrorize people on their motorcycles. They like to go to the clubhouse and shoot some pool and play some darts. Then, they tear around town and yell at one another in the morning. They know that Tim is quiet and that he is one of the most feared members of the gang. Adam also says that the show is a weekly movie review show and that this week it will be a hardcore coming of age dramedy called You Are Not Invited to my Bat Mitzvah.',NULL,NULL),(62655,112,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/07/FoodFarm Talk - September 7, 2023 at 10:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-07 10:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-14 12:27:56',NULL,'In this episode of the FoodFarm Talk Podcast, host Jordan Sloggett talks with Graham Hill about his work with Food for Life, a charity and non-profit based out of Guelph, Ontario. The purpose of the organization is to rescue food, lives, and their vision to have everyone have access to healthier food. Jordan also mentions that Eggscape is a charitable organization that brings food and farming education to classrooms and students in Ontario. If you would like to become a part of the Eggscape family, you can visit the organization\'s website or go to the members section of their Facebook page.',NULL,NULL),(62656,107,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/06/Tone Zone - September 6, 2023 at 21:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-06 21:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-14 12:10:37',NULL,'The Tone Zone starts off this week by paying tribute to Paul \"Peewee\" Herman, who recently passed away. This week, they start off by playing some songs from Sinead OConnor\'s second album, \"1990s I Do not want what I haven\'t got\" .\n\nThey also start off with Mandinka\'s debut album \"The Lion and the cobra\" , which was a huge hit in Canada in 1987. The next song is from a band called \"The Ramblers,\" who never released an album. This song was originally recorded on a compilation back in 1986. They have a newer album out called \"I am not there anymore,\" and they\'re playing another song called \"Peach Kelly pop and doo-wah Diddy\" from her self-titled debut from 2010. They start the set with The Beach Boys song \"Don\'t worry baby,\" and Lady Grey\'s song \"I Am not there Anymore\" ). The next band is \"Mully Grub,\" who has a new album called \"Traitoral\" and a song called Animal Teeth.\n\nThe next is \"Heart of Darkness\" from their album \"A List of things to say,\" and the next song \"Tin ear and dress up with me\" is from their \"Cadastral Maps\" album. The last song is \"Everyone is my friend\" from \"The Catalyst,\" which was the first song from \"A list of things\" ; it was released last year',NULL,NULL),(62657,111,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/07/Tales from the Bridge - September 7, 2023 at 09:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-07 09:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-14 11:52:42',NULL,'The guys talk about their summer reading plans. They also talk about the books they\'re reading for the month of July. If you\'re new to the Tales from the Bridges, please subscribe to the show and let us know if you like it. And, if you\'d just like to be notified of any new guests on the show, or have any suggestions for reading that would please you, please let them know. Also, if they want to hang out after the show to check in on what\'s up with Marty, they can hang out at the bridge until the end.',NULL,NULL),(62658,113,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/07/Android’s Dungeon - September 7, 2023 at 13:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-07 13:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-14 11:31:55',NULL,'The host begins by saying that it\'s late September and early October. He was off at his cottage at this very time of year, not last year, and the temperature was similar to what was, it had been recently.\n\nThis weekend it looks like it\'ll be low single digits with rain. He says fall is the best season of the year because it is patrician in its taste and because it has cooler nights and warmer days. He adds that he doesn\'t like the polar vortex, but that\'s the reason fall is superior to spring. He goes on to say that the host is going to split the show into two parts: one for the tabletop stuff and one for each of the games. He\'ll also play some music, which is supposed to be a somber track from the album \"Beyond the Gates.\" The two tracks are a mix of \"Mount Shrine\" and \"Alfaxone.\" The host says the two tracks will be different, but they\'re both very talented artists.\n\nHe also says that he\'s going to save one of the most interesting ones for last because he\'ll talk about a game called \"My Friendly Neighbor.\" This is a survival horror game that was recently released. The underground dude says it had him hooked right away.',NULL,NULL),(62659,110,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/07/Here Today - September 7, 2023 at 07:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-07 07:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-14 11:10:55',NULL,'Aaron Badgley is back on the CFRU 98.3FM Morning Show with Rob Proust, and he and Rob are psyched to have a new artist on the show. He\'ll be playing a show with the Canadian band Church of Trees. Before that, he plays a song from a British artist called Daughters Of The Industrialists. Then he plays another song from another British artist named Deborah Fajalkova. He also plays a new single from another Canadian artist named Milo.\n\nThis is called Gone Forever, and it came out September 1. Aaron has been writing for the magazine Spill for a long time, so he\'s been writing about this song for a while, but it\'s the first song he ever wrote for Spill. It was called Summer is Gone. He doesn\'t think he\'ll ever write about it again, but he loves it. He thinks it was the best song he\'d ever written for a magazine. He plays this new song from Milo before he plays the new one from Bobby Bazzini.\n\nHe says he thinks he should play this new one before the old one. The other artists on the program include: Ringo Starr, Dolly Parton, George Harrison, and the James Clark Institute. Aaron says that he thinks the James will take over his show soon to promote their new album.',NULL,NULL),(62660,116,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/07/T.K.O. - September 7, 2023 at 16:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-07 16:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-14 10:51:36',NULL,'On this special edition of TKO, Janan, the co-host of the show, gives her listeners an update on the latest happenings in mixed martial arts. She also explains that she is in the middle of sending a voice message to a friend, and she was sitting in her bag.',NULL,NULL),(62661,115,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/07/RadiOPIRG - September 7, 2023 at 15:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-07 15:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-14 10:26:36',NULL,'The Feeling of Community is Universal and So are the Gestures That Build It. A few Kind Words, a Smile or Wave hello are the First Steps to Building a Community where Everyone feels they belong . Omorowa, the volunteer coordinator for the OPRG, and her co-worker, Mandy, explain the organization to listeners of the program. They have come to live at the university for the move-in-day, and they are looking forward to welcoming back students. Their program is all about the radical politics of the organization, and their goal is to help people understand the policies and politics of their own country.',NULL,NULL),(62662,123,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/08/Thanks for Listening :) - September 8, 2023 at 09:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-08 09:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-14 10:08:08',NULL,'The show opens with a tribute to Richard Laviolettte, a friend of Laviolette\'s who recently passed away. The tribute will be a \"long, varied, and big discography\" . The song list includes \"Ocean goats and bats\" , \"Richard and the Glitter Bombs\" and \"Aging Recycling Plant.\" After the tribute, the show moves on to \"Your Body Your Love\" and Liza Bucket\'s \"Sincerely.\" The group will conclude with \"Your Love, Sincerely,\" \"Aging Plant,\" and \"Your Beautiful Body.\"',NULL,NULL),(62663,118,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/07/Open Sources Guelph - September 7, 2023 at 17:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-07 17:00:00',86507648,'2023-10-30 20:05:59',NULL,'On this episode of the CFRU Political and Current Affair Discussion Show, Adam A Donaldson of the Guelph Politico and host of the Open Source Open Air program announces that the Eden Mills Writers\' Festival will be held on September 10, 2019. The festival will bring the best of Canadian writing to the region. Adam also announces that he has won the Endurance Award at City Hall for surviving 44 hours of public meetings. The program also discusses the city\'s new transportation system, cashless payment, and the March for Children, an anti-LGBT movement that is getting louder. The show also discusses news from the past week, including Stephen Clark\'s sudden resignation, the naming of Paul Calandra as the new Minister of Municipal Affairs and Housing, and a new trending hashtag, \"ResignedDougFord.\" The show then turns to the Ford administration\'s controversial Greenbelt plan, which has caused the resignation of Stephen Clark. In addition, the government has appointed John Mutton, a former mayor\'s development services company partner, as a new member of its cabinet. Mutton\'s lobbying firm has also made an appearance in the new cabinet. The government has also announced a new consultation process for the Greenbelt, which means that the government is not consulting with the public. The new government has not yet announced that it will halt the process, but rather that it is going to review all of its plans and come up with a final decision. Adam says that this government is \"almost masochistic\" and that',NULL,'The Eden Mills Writers’ Festival will be held on September 10th, 2019'),(62664,119,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/07/Turtle Island Underground - September 7, 2023 at 18:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-07 18:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-14 09:52:50',NULL,'The Underground\'s guest host, Marci Angeles, introduces himself as a two spirit, an artist, musician, and journalist. He\'s currently recording a song from his project, The Hand. The song is called Love on Fleet and it\'s a tribute to \'80s goth bands like The Glove, The Cure, and The Cure\'s \"New Wave.\" Marci also has a side project, called Lace, which is a kind of \"goth rock\" project. Marci plays two songs from his albums, \"Water and Skin\" and \"My Skin Crawlz.\" The first song is \"Dumb Gums,\" which is about a stalker, and the second song is a song about his \"spirituality for protection.\n\n\" Marcie also talks about his favorite song, \"Vault of Heaven,\" from Pixi\'S Lost Album. He also has two other favorite songs, \"Red Version,\" from a band named Ghostwood, and \"Miss Connection,\" from the band Filmschool. He talks about the upcoming IMAX release, \"The XID,\" and about his love for Chris Corner.',NULL,NULL),(62665,124,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/08/Planet Groove - September 8, 2023 at 10:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-08 10:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-14 09:09:16',NULL,'The show opens with a description of the music on the air. It\'s called \"Planet Groove\" and it\'s a kind of funky blues jam session. The guys are there to \"fertilize your soul\" and \"give it some love\" . The first song is \"Funky the Jam Baby Shake\" by the rock band \"The Rock Hunters\" and then \"My Blue Veins\" by Broken Boy Soldiers . Then they play \"Wings Letting Go\" by The Rock Hunters and \"Funk the Jam baby shake\" by \"Wham\" , which is a reference to the wig.',NULL,NULL),(62666,120,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/07/The Crooked Beat - September 7, 2023 at 20:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-07 20:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-14 08:44:26',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(62667,120,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/07/The Crooked Beat - September 7, 2023 at 19:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-07 19:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-14 08:29:45',NULL,'This is the first hour of a two-hour special edition of the program. It\'s called \"The Crooked Beat\" and it\'s hosted by \"Nicky Dread\" and \"Dread\" . The show starts off with some music from Zion Train, then moves to Earthcry, a new project from the Los Angeles-based group.\n\nThen, it turns to the music of \"Gannon,\" \"The Dub Chronicles,\" and \"Kruma\" , all of whom are new artists. The first song is \"Family,\" a song about the family of a young man named Raphael. When they get to the second song, \"Until It\'ll Gone,\" they\'ll hear music from \"Takana Zion,\" \"Pablo,\" \"Stinging Ray,\" \"Ganymede,\" \"Zion Heart,\" and the \"dub Chronicles,\" who\'ve just released an album called \"Love is Magic.\" The show closes with a big shout-out to \"Ded,\" who has been playing the show for 40 years.',NULL,NULL),(62668,122,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/08/Forever Deaf - September 8, 2023 at 01:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-08 01:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-14 08:07:15',NULL,'The host is at the end of the show and he\'s psyched to be there. He\'s got some new music coming up, and he announces that Destruction will be touring with Razor Crisis in Europe in November. Sadis has a new album coming out, called The Sickness, and they\'re called Forever Deaf. They\'ve also got a new song called Back to the Future. The Underground Guy is psyched to hear Kudetah, Agent Orange, and ChargeGBH play, too. He also announces that the host will be leaving with some new material, including Dying Fetus and Creeping Death.',NULL,NULL),(62669,122,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/08/Forever Deaf - September 8, 2023 at 00:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-08 00:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-14 07:09:41',NULL,'This is the second in a series of three interviews with the CFRU Community Radio and Media Center. The first is with a guy who works at the station, who describes the station as a \"source of alternative media\" . The second interview is with the man who works on the station\'s outreach team, who explains that the station needs people like him to \"be connected to community\" and to \"celebrate community.\n\n\" The man also explains how he can get involved with the station. He\'s looking for people to help set up events and festivals, to record public service announcements, and to write short scripts for ads. He also wants people to listen to the station every day. The man is psyched about all of this.',NULL,NULL),(62670,128,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/08/Walkuman Style - September 8, 2023 at 18:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-08 18:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-14 06:49:55',NULL,'A community celebration called \"Praise the Ward\" will take place in the Two Rivers district on Saturday, September 23, from 10am until 10pm. To celebrate the Ward\'s unique culture and people, DJ Glibb has created a \"Chill Study\" mixtape that will be played throughout the day. The full list of the songs will be found at the end of this post, but the link to the DJ\'s Soundcloud page is at the bottom of this page.',NULL,NULL),(62671,122,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/07/Forever Deaf - September 7, 2023 at 23:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-07 23:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-14 06:32:43',NULL,'In this program, we learn about some of the music being played in the various stages of the various music festivals taking place in Guelph. We also learn about Alice Coopers recent comments about the trans community and what he thinks of the idea of \"gender identity\" as a fad. He also says that if you have a six-year-old kid who wants to play music, it\'s not appropriate for him to express his feelings. Alice also says she finds it wrong when a six year-old has no idea what he wants to hear.',NULL,NULL),(62672,126,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/08/Viejoteca - September 8, 2023 at 14:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-08 14:00:00',86507648,'2023-09-10 02:49:36',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(62673,129,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/08/Digital Statik - September 8, 2023 at 19:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-08 19:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-14 06:17:15',NULL,'This program is an American Sign Language (ASL) radio show hosted by DJ Julz, a Canadian EDM artist. The show is hosted by Julz and he is joined on the call by a poet named Poetic the Poet, who is a friend of Julz\'s. The poet tells Julz that he has always wanted to be a part of the music scene and that he appreciates the opportunity to be on the show. Julz introduces the song High Beam by Left Lane, who he says is an \"amazing artist\" from London, Canada. The song is about driving through his city, and he says that he once lived downtown three days a week.',NULL,NULL),(62674,127,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/08/LiYghTE FM - September 8, 2023 at 16:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-08 16:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-14 05:57:11',NULL,'DJ Double D is disappointed with his host, who works in a grocery store and is \"emotionally distant\" from his friends. He\'s also heard that the DJ is trying to \"change the entire universe\" through a love \"revolution\" and that he\'s \"trying to change the whole world\" through that love revolution.\n\nThis is a little shocking to us, since we\'ve never heard of \"Love Revolution\" before. We\'re not sure if this is a compliment or not, but we\'re going to give it anyway. The DJ takes us on a tour through some of the latest music from Canada. The first song is a dance track called \"Mother Tongues\" by a Canadian band called Mother Tongues. The second is a song called \"Give Thanks\" by an artist named Aja Manet, who is a jazz musician. The third song is another dance track, this one called \"Release Love in a vicious Way\" by another Canadian artist named Prologue.\n\nThe fourth song is \"Give thanks\" by the artist. It\'s a really good song, and the DJ thinks that it\'s just \"dedicated, deliberate, and precise without being lame\" . This guy is a \"genius\" and will be a \"part of the love-revolution\" , we\'ll see.',NULL,NULL),(62675,122,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/07/Forever Deaf - September 7, 2023 at 22:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-07 22:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-14 05:10:12',NULL,'Welcome to the forever deaf show. This is a band from El Paso Texas. From F period,U period,C period,K period,Y period,O period.U period. EP. The band\'s name is Circa Arcana and they\'re from the El Paso,Texas from the F,U,C,K,Y,O periods.\n\nThere\'s something called Switch-Blains and Fist fights. Before that, an accept from Too-Mean-to-Die album. There was a thing called Not-My Problem. Connor starts off the show with Saxon from Power and Glory. Then he gets right to the news item of the week. He\'s leaving the band, Razor, Retta-Johnson,Retta-Retta Ripperson as he left. He says he wishes them well and he wishes the band well and Sharif will kill it. He then plays a song called Crossed, which is a song that was originally written by the band.\n\nIt\'s called Razor from the cycle of contempt. This song is called Scaventhsies. It was named after a fossil that was discovered in Luxembourg. It is named after Viacoma, the ancient kind of a brittle star. Then Connor plays two more songs from the album. One is from Orbit Culture and the other is from Native howl.',NULL,NULL),(62676,126,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/08/Viejoteca - September 8, 2023 at 13:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-08 13:00:00',86638720,'2023-09-10 02:49:58',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(62677,132,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/08/Global Rare Grooves - September 8, 2023 at 21:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-08 21:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-14 04:51:10',NULL,'In this final monologue, Wilde pleads with Evesa to \"open your mind,\" and to \"be your only truth.\" He says that if he wants his freedom, he must \"die, vie.\" In the end, Wilde promises that he will do his best for Evesa and that he was \"best for either one\" of them.\n\nHe says he knows that he is \"depressed,\" but he promises to change. He promises to God, to himself, and to his family that he \"is on Feliz.\" He promises that if flavor lies, \"head cheese and cheek,\" and \"to keep your family feed.\" He resolves to \"cook the rich today.\" This is the final part of Wilde\'s final soliloquy, and he promises that \"days gonna be different.\"',NULL,NULL),(62678,139,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/09/Bel Araby with CAWA - September 9, 2023 at 15:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-09 15:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-14 04:31:44',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(62679,136,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/09/A Dog’s Breakfast - September 9, 2023 at 10:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-09 10:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-14 04:16:28',NULL,'The show opens with a description of the play, \"Liv and Braden\", which will be performed by the group Tragedy and Music. The play is a contemporary tragedy that focuses on the relationship between two families, the family of a murdered woman and the family who live in a small town in the Midwest.\n\nThe show ends with the announcement that the play will be presented at the small town\'s Little Theatre. A Dog\'s Breakfast is the title of the program that will be airing on the CFRU radio station this week. The program\'s host, Apostrophe, and his partner, Ajay, are at the station to discuss the upcoming Guelph Jazz Festival. The festival will take place from September 17 to September 23 and will feature many of the festival\'s well-known artists. This year, the festival will also host a five-day Colloquium that will bring together the best of the Guelph jazz scene.',NULL,NULL),(62680,135,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/08/Folk Roots Radio - September 8, 2023 at 17:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-08 17:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-14 03:09:14',NULL,'On this week\'s episode of the program, we\'re joined by Janice Hall, Ray Johnson, and Ian MacDonald. The show starts off by playing a bunch of music from the past week, including a few new releases from artists like Justin Rutledge, Skydigger\'s, and Matt Zaddy.\n\nIf you missed the previous show, you can check it out on your favorite podcasting platform. We start off this way, with Justin with Lioness, from his tenth album Something Easy. We also had a great conversation with Justin on this show, and if you missed it, you\'ll find it wherever you listen to podcasts. In the meantime, we play some music from last week, too, including songs from Bruce Coburn\'s Us All, Andy Mays\' On Come to Senses from Your Light, and six songs from Hide\'s Skydogs.\n\nThen we check out some new tracks from William Prince\'s Stand In the Joy, and from Noah McCuron\'s Point of Light. Then there\'s a Chicago-style blues group called Please Help. And finally, there is a song from Michael Brown\'s Getting Together. This song is about love, and it goes something like this: One thing I couldn\'t deny, need a love, need love to set free. Oh, oh, something is getting up, it\'s not being up. You can hear it on the program on CFRU-FM 93.3. We then hear',NULL,NULL),(62681,138,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/09/Sound Magic - September 9, 2023 at 14:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-09 14:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-14 02:51:04',NULL,'The program begins with music by two composers who are prominent in German Romanticism. Paul Greiner, a Jewish composer, was a member of the German avant-garde who wrote a concerto for the Bush Quartet in the early 20th century. He was also a prominent composer during the period of the so-called \"Second World War\" when the Nazis occupied Germany. He wrote a piece for the Munich Philharmonic Orchestra in which he wrote a slow, fast, and rhythmically complex piece. The program ends with music from another prominent German composer, the late Boris Blachh, who lived from 1903 until 1975.\n\nBlachha did not go into \"ultra-modernism\" and lived a conservative life. He composed mostly unplayed works, including works for the orchestra. The overture to \"Hamlet\" on the program is from 1940, and it is a symphonic poem with the Symphony Radio Orchestra of Berlin conducting. The tone poem is from Hamlet, which, according to the program notes, is \"an orchestral tone poem\" .',NULL,NULL),(62682,138,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/09/Sound Magic - September 9, 2023 at 13:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-09 13:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-14 02:29:40',NULL,'The program opens with a discussion of a composer named Max Rege who died in 1916. He was a prolific composer, but never quite got his symphony together. He also wrote some of his most difficult and difficult organ music. The program then moves on to a work by another composer named J.\n\nR. Weinberger who lived from 1896 until 1967. The program ends with an overview of the other composers on the program. The first is by a composer called Max Reger who was a very well-known organist. The second is by another well-loved composer, J. R. Weinberge. The third is a piece by another Vienna composer, Emil Biron. The group then moves to some other works by other Vienna composers, including a piece written by Ewen Linde.',NULL,NULL),(62683,143,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/09/Mach Vibe Radio - September 9, 2023 at 21:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-09 21:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-14 01:10:26',NULL,'The show starts off by thanking everyone involved with the bike event. Then, the show moves on to a bit of music. It\'s a bit more about music and its effect on people. It starts off with a guy named Analogue, who\'s the brains behind the whole thing. He\'s also the guy who plays the drums. The guy is named Keon, and he\'s here to thank everybody for coming to the event. He also thanks everyone for supporting 93.3 FM as well. Then he gets to the heart of the matter.\n\nHe tells everyone to check out the Cfru.ca website and listen to all of their shows and stuff. Yeah, it\'s awesome. So thanks again, guys. Let\'s get started. Okay. We\'ve got some more music. This time it\'ll be a song called Ditch Ditch Ditch. The song is all about the power of the heart and mind to help us rise above these sad times. It ends with a little face-kissing. This is the first song Analogue has played in a long time. The first song is about Ditch Ditch, the power to rise above the pain.\n\nThe second song is a little bit about the Mandela Effect. The Mandela Effect is that no matter what happens in the future, people will always remember it. It doesn\'t matter what the script is, it can never be corrupted forever. Back to the main point',NULL,NULL),(62684,140,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/09/Caribbean Anthology - September 9, 2023 at 17:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-09 17:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-14 00:49:07',NULL,'The Kidney Walk is a Canadian initiative to raise money to improve the lives of kidney patients. The event is being held in Guelph on October 1, and everyone is invited to join. The host of the program, Doug Blackwit, has been a part of the community for over 25 years. The program is a mix of old and new music, featuring interviews and news about the community. Each week, he presents great old radio shows from the 1930\'s to the 50\'s with music stories to match.\n\nThe show is now on Sundays at 2pm on the station. The narrator welcomes listeners to the program and introduces them to Tragedy Anne. They are going to perform at the Little Theatre on September 22nd at 7pm with Josh Gabriel, Harpist, and Upright Bass. Tickets are $25 and free for children under 12. For tickets go to TragedyAnne Music.com.',NULL,NULL),(62685,138,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/09/Sound Magic - September 9, 2023 at 12:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-09 12:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-14 00:28:43',NULL,'The program opens with a three hour program of recorded classical concerts. The first concert is a German program, which consists largely of German or German-speaking works. The program begins with a symphony by a Vienna-born composer named Martin Scharber, who lived from 1907 until 1919. He is considered one of Vienna\'s great trained composers, and his first symphony was recorded in 1938. The second symphony is a work by another Vienna trained composer named Herbert Baskin, who was born in Vienna and studied at the Vienna School of Music. The third symphony is by another Austrian composer named Emil Beck, who is not well known.',NULL,NULL),(62686,140,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/09/Caribbean Anthology - September 9, 2023 at 16:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-09 16:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-14 00:08:44',NULL,'In this edition of the Curriculumthology Show, the hosts discuss a new show that they\'re putting on today. It\'s called \"The House of Reggae 4\" and it\'s all about the music. The show is hosted by the guys from 93.3 FM and they\'ve got a special guest on the show named Tasha T, who\'s a long-time musician and singer.\n\nThe hosts also mention that they were able to get the post for the show because of a problem with the censors on CFRU. The guys have found a way to reword some of their content so that it can be heard on different platforms, like 93.3FM, the station, or on Roger\'s channel 948 . They\'re learning a lot about how to get their content out there.',NULL,NULL),(62688,1437,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/08/Democracy Now - September 8, 2023 at 11:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-08 11:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-13 23:12:32',NULL,'The Democracy Now team discusses a number of recent developments in the world of sports, including a strike by players in Spain, the World Cup\'s Me Too moment in Spanish sports, decriminalization of abortion in Mexico, and the dire conditions in the Fulton County jail in Atlanta, where Trump and 18 of his co-conspirators are being held',NULL,NULL),(62689,1344,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/09/Beautiful Druid - September 9, 2023 at 09:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-09 09:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-13 22:49:24',NULL,'Beautiful Druid is a live music show that takes place at the university. It is hosted by Alden Hadwen, a Canadian singer songwriter. The show\'s theme is \"places that we long to visit.\" The first song in the program is by Ian Tyson and Sylvia, a duo of Canadian singer- songwriters.\n\nThe second song is by Kenny Chesney, from his album \"When the Sun goes Down.\" The third song is from Taj Mahal, a famous blues musician. The fourth is from Ian and Sylvia and is about a girl longing to visit the rodeos. The fifth song is about inviting someone to visit a place. Alden plays songs about longing for places. The first is from Katie Lang, from her album \"Shadowland.\n\n\" The second is from Harry Belafontes \"Essentials\" album. The third is from Sylvia and Ian, from their \"greatest hits\" album, \"Un Canadian Run.\" The fourth song is called \"Island in the Sun.\" The fifth is from Gordon Lightfoot, from \"Did She Mention my Name.\" The sixth song is a Canadian folk song called \"Uncanadian run.\" The seventh song is an English folk song about exile.',NULL,NULL),(62691,1437,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/07/Democracy Now - September 7, 2023 at 11:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-07 11:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-13 22:31:31',NULL,'In this chapter, the State Department describes the humanitarian crisis that it has seen in the past eighteen months in Ukraine and in the Democratic republic of the Congo. The State Department says that in the last eighteen months, the humanitarian situation has \"deteriorated to an alarming degree. In addition, the situation in the eastern Congo has reached an alarming level.',NULL,NULL),(62693,1491,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/08/Industry Tactics - September 8, 2023 at 23:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-08 23:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-13 22:07:55',NULL,'On this edition of Industry Tactics, Malvina, Ben, and Jeff discuss Disorientation Week, which is coming up at the University of G. The week will include screenings, workshops and other activities designed to engage students and community members in political, social and economic justice. OPRQ, the U. G. Graduate Coalition, and the Guelph Chamber of Commerce are all excited to participate in Disorientation week.\n\nThe three organizations also have a new show called \"Here Today\" on CFRU 92.3. This show is a little different than the other shows because it\'s a bit of a pop-up shop. It focuses on new music from emerging and established artists, as opposed to the traditional pop music that\'s heard on most shows. The show also has a lot of news and commentary about the world around us. For example, the Responsible Gaming Council has sent out a message about gambling and how it can ruin your life.\n\nOn this show, we\'re also going to hear some music from a project called The Orchestra ofFuturist Noise. This is a collaboration between Keisha, Mike Patton, Pauline Oliveros and