ng to the Gryphons and the Special Olympics Facebook page.',NULL,NULL),(62697,1615,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/07/Off the Beaten Track - September 7, 2023 at 21:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-07 21:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-13 19:56:33',NULL,'This is the first of a two-part series on experimental pop music. The first part is comprised of a selection of music from various artists including Space Motion, Joni Void, Tom VR, and others. The second part consists of a live performance by the artist Romare. In this first part of the series, we learn that the music is experimental and that its themes aim to keep life playful and less predictable. The music, however, is familiar and predictable, and so the listeners are left with the impression that the listener has no interest in the music.',NULL,NULL),(62698,1620,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/08/Hellfire Radio - September 8, 2023 at 15:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-08 15:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-13 19:12:44',NULL,'This is the first show of the new school year. The show begins with the host of the show explaining that he is a student at the university and that he has been invited to play some music in front of some new students. He also says that he was late for the show, but it was a good thing that they had some new music to play while he was getting ready to go to class. He reminds students that they should always remember to listen to new music when it is available.',NULL,NULL),(62708,196,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/4d7m8k/September_10_2023_Across_the_Univrese8pv5k.mp3','2023-09-11 00:11:15',431961989,'2023-12-13 18:52:14',NULL,'Ken Stowar is back on the air and ready to deliver another three-hour program. He reminds listeners that they can listen to the show via the link provided at the end of the program. They can also get the entire program by clicking on the link and then going to the program\'s home page at the link.\n\nKen gives a brief rundown of the songs he played during the show. The first song is Kill Emile, which is from the album Safe Passage. The second song is Dilla, from Gitkin, the third is Iliad 22, from Sababa 5, the fourth is Doorsteps, from Cormac, the fifth is Wake Up, from Old People, and the sixth is Something for Bird, from following.',NULL,'Clayton Book talks with listeners about his commitment to give back to the community'),(62709,206,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/fxnwpc/September_2_2023_Minx_Sessions7375w.mp3','2023-09-11 00:15:15',287962512,'2023-12-13 17:11:23',NULL,'The show opens with a warm welcome from the host, who introduces the listeners to a number of local artists who will be playing live tonight. The first artist to be announced is a Detroit-based DJ/producer named Jeff Mills, who\'s a pioneer in the field of Detroit techno. Mills is a pioneer because he\'s taken all the best of Detroit and remixed it for his label, AXIS. Mills co-produced the first record by Tony Allen, which will be one of four new releases tonight on the show. The other two releases are by a local artist named Blake Reyes, and a label called scissor and thread, which is a good one to check out if you haven\'t already.',NULL,NULL),(62710,206,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/u5hsxr/August_26_2023_Minx_Sessions7bjvz.mp3','2023-09-11 00:14:25',287962512,'2023-12-13 16:48:39',NULL,'Imogen and Richard join Christian on the Ciut 89.5 frequency to discuss the latest music. Christian says he\'s been looking forward to this show for a long time. He\'s excited to be able to share some of his latest discoveries with Imogen. Christian introduces the track Mobit Love, which he\'ll be playing later on. He says it\'s based on the concept of love and that love is a very important thing.',NULL,NULL),(62711,206,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/uvafjx/August_19_2023_Minx_Sessions6mqqk.mp3','2023-09-11 00:13:17',287962512,'2023-12-13 16:29:36',NULL,'Welcome to another Minx Sessions, this time with a whole bunch of new music from some really awesome artists. The fi