638720,'2023-12-12 04:31:31',NULL,'The narrator introduces himself as Ted Preset, a Maryland man who grew up in a small farming town called Chatham, Ontario during the Depression. His parents moved there when he was a child, and he remembers that there were only a few hundred people in the town when he left in 1946. The narrator\'s family moved to the town of Lockstock in 1913, after the family heard about a good farming land nearby. His grandfather owned a gristmill there, and the family decided to move to the area. The family consisted of three sons and three daughters, who all decided to farm or become farmers.',NULL,NULL),(62831,97,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/14/Wild Combination - September 14, 2023 at 01:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-14 01:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-12 04:08:32',NULL,'The two young men, Malvina and Ben, are hanging out in the studio of the college\'s public radio station, CFRU-FM 93.3. They\'re talking about a new line of clothing that they\'re selling. They also have a new program called \"Let\'s Get lost,\" which they hope will bring listeners back to the station.\n\nThey explain that the program is all about music, jazz, and old favorites. They say they hope listeners will listen to the program because it\'s good music. But they also tell listeners that the station has a great online presence, too, with easy-to-use features like a live broadcast stream, a weekly music chart, and a second live stream featuring local music. They even have a donation button that listeners can use to make a donation.',NULL,NULL),(62832,97,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/14/Wild Combination - September 14, 2023 at 00:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-14 00:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-12 03:04:42',NULL,'In this short video, the Media Center at the College of Staten Island describes how it\'s not easy to live in this time, so if you\'re interested in watching the video, like, comment, and subscribe. The only way to get involved is to become a member of the College and become a Cyberlicious Castle Everyday member.',NULL,NULL),(62833,111,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/14/Tales from the Bridge - September 14, 2023 at 09:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-14 09:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-12 02:51:05',NULL,'In this episode, Sam and Sam\'s friend, Kevin, host a program called \"Tales from the Bridge.\" In this program, they discuss their summer reading and their thoughts on science fiction and science fact. They also discuss the Fan Expo they attended in Toronto. Before they delve into science fiction or science fact, Sam wants to apologize to the people in Waukesha, Wisconsin, who have been listening to the program.',NULL,NULL),(62834,110,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/14/Here Today - September 14, 2023 at 07:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-14 07:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-12 02:30:04',NULL,'Aaron Badgley is back on the CFRU FM 93.3 show with some new music for the listeners. He\'s got a special guest on the show that\'s from Ireland, his daughter Linda. Aaron has been to a ton of shows in Ireland, so he thought it would be cool to do a music show to wrap up the summer. He asks Aaron if he\'s ever seen individual members of bands like in Stafford Pub. Aaron says he has. Then Aaron introduces us to another band that he actually saw in Toronto, the Mary-Wallipers. They\'ve been playing in the suburbs of Toronto for a long time, and now they\'re hitting the big city.\n\nAaron and his daughter have been to see them eight times, and they\'ll be back in December. The show starts off with a band called Smashed Glass. Aaron plays the whole song and then tells us that they just heard the other band, Spider-Bite, play a song called \"Smashed Glass\" and then they talk about how amazing the band is.',NULL,NULL),(62835,112,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/14/FoodFarm Talk - September 14, 2023 at 10:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-14 10:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-12 02:11:16',NULL,'In this episode of the FoodFocus Podcast, Mike shares some of the stories of how new products are coming to market. The first story is a grandmother\'s cookie recipe, which would have made it onto store shelves if it had been made into a cookie. The second story is the story of a young man who is working on a new food product and has no idea how to market it. The third story is about a woman who is pregnant with her first child. The fourth story is of a man who has a new baby, but he doesn\'t know what to do with it.',NULL,NULL),(62836,113,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/14/Android’s Dungeon - September 14, 2023 at 13:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-14 13:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-12 01:11:46',NULL,'The narrator opens the show by saying that he\'s Jack, and he and his friend, Joel, are normally joined by another person. The narrator says that he has been abandoned by his listeners, and that it\'s a weird experience to be alone. He says that the show will continue to be interesting and that he will try to grind some more episodes, but that generally the show works best when there is some dialogue.\n\nIn other words, if there is no dialogue, the show is not really called \"Android\'s Dungeon.\" The narrator describes his hometown, Guelph, as \"a city split between... two selves.\" He says it has a \"split personality disorder\" and that the city is divided into \"four or five cities, combined into one.\" He describes the city as a \"zone beast\" and a \"south end slash.\" He adds that he doesn\'t call it a \"student ghetto,\" which is a way of saying that there\'s lots of student housing in the city. But, he says, \"there was... this very integrated... sense of... students and the... university and... the town.\" He also says that Guelph is \"a weird city\" and \"not without its problems.\"',NULL,NULL),(62837,116,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/14/T.K.O. - September 14, 2023 at 16:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-14 16:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-12 00:51:05',NULL,'The show opens with a description of the show and its host, Janan. She is a graduate student at the university where the show is produced. She and the other students discuss mixed martial arts, or MMA, and other sports. They also discuss notable fighters and discuss the issues surrounding the role of combat in the sport.\n\nThey discuss how they got into the sport and where they are today. The show concludes with an update on the weather. The weather is getting colder, but it\'s not the end of the world yet. There are a lot of COVID cases, which is a type of blood poisoning, and there are other illnesses, like the cold and the flu. Everyone should take care of themselves, and especially if they have a cold or a flu-like illness. The other thing to keep in mind is that there has been an increase in the number of common colds and other respiratory illnesses. It\'s hard for people to get used to the cold, so everyone should try to stay healthy. Okay, now we\'re going to talk about combat sports, and our host, who is also a student, discusses how he is super hyped for today\'s fight.\n\nHe says that right before he started recording the fight, he read a news update that had him feeling like a rock star. He\'s going to tell everyone on the show about it.',NULL,NULL),(62838,115,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/14/RadiOPIRG - September 14, 2023 at 15:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-14 15:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-12 00:26:04',NULL,'This week\'s program is titled \"Night Flyer\" and it is a continuation of the program \"Nightflyer\" by Allison Russell, which aired on CFRU 92. This program is a public service announcement about the upcoming week of public awareness about the dangers of climate change. The program is hosted by the irrepressible Omorowa, who is a student at the university and a frequent guest on the program. She and the other students discuss the various threats to the environment and the importance of keeping an eye on them.\n\nThe show also includes a recording of Sarah Mueller, the founder of the bird-safe Guelph group, speaking with the program\'s RadiopiRG. She is a graduate student studying bird ecology. Sarah is one of the founders of the group, which is formed during the pandemic of 1918 when there was no bird population. The group was formed like during the Pandemic when there were no bird populations. It is nice to have people who share the same interests in bird conservation.',NULL,NULL),(62839,118,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/14/Open Sources Guelph - September 14, 2023 at 17:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-14 17:00:00',86638720,'2023-10-30 19:53:50',NULL,'The CFRU political and current affairs show airs every Thursday at 5:00PM as the host discusses the latest news from the Guelph area. The show also discusses the recent Conservative Party of Canada policy convention in Quebec City. The convention passed many conservative resolutions, but the most important resolutions are those that directly attack the Trudeau administration. The Trudeau government is spending a lot of money on defense, and the government seems to be trying to teach Canadians how to eat insects. The government is pushing bugs, which is the same kind of conspiracy theory that the Trudeaus and the Berniers are trying to propagate in the United States. The scandal surrounding the leak of information about the government\'s lobbying activities is also a big issue for the Conservative Party in Canada. Some of the people on the governing board are made up of people who support corporations that have significant investments in Canada',NULL,'CFRU\'s political and current affairs show airs every Thursday at 5:00PM'),(62840,120,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/14/The Crooked Beat - September 14, 2023 at 19:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-14 19:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-12 00:07:38',NULL,'This week on the show, Nicky Dread introduces us to a bunch of new music from Bristol England, including some of the most popular names in the West Indies.\n\nHe\'s also got some music from the new album from Human Rights, called Reggae Strong. It\'ll be released this Sunday at a party in Toronto. There\'s a block party at the party too, and we\'ll hear more about it later on. The show starts off with some music by Mafia from Germany, followed by some more music from Saralulugo from Germany. Then it\'s time for some more of the songs from the reggae albums from around the world. The first song is from a new album called Flowers, which is from VP Records.\n\nThe second track is from another new album, called Mandala Sound, and King Joe is also on the album. The third track is a song called Healer from another reggae album called Resonators. Then there\'s some more from Mad Professor Mix, some from Black Roots and some from producer Kaya Street, and finally the last song is Dub Chasm, who\'s on the',NULL,NULL),(62841,119,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/14/Turtle Island Underground - September 14, 2023 at 18:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-14 18:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-11 23:50:59',NULL,'This week\'s edition of the Turtle Island Underground takes a weirder turn, with host Mac introducing the show\'s guests. First up is the first album from a singer-songwriter from the Inu tribe, called Kainan. It\'s called Kair, and it sounds like it\'s just going to get worse.\n\nThe rest of the show is a mix of some of the best new music out there, including a few tracks from a new album by a Canadian artist named Zoon. The show ends with an artist introduction interview with two spirit Apache musician, writer, and journalist Marcis. Marci is an artist, journalist, and musician from the southern part of New Mexico. He\'s also just been named a cultural advisor for an organization. Marcis tells us that his main focus is his music, journalism and panels. He recently closed an exhibit with his mom, which was the first time he\'s been able to do this work with his mother.',NULL,NULL),(62842,1437,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/14/Democracy Now - September 14, 2023 at 11:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-14 11:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-11 23:09:48',NULL,'Amy Goodman reports that the death toll from the recent floods in Libya has risen to 20,000. The prime minister of Libya refuses to accept international aid, saying that the country does not need it. Meanwhile, the head of the United Nations human rights office has called on the two rival Libyan governments to work together in order to ensure access to aid.',NULL,NULL),(62845,158,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/mp989h/RR_sep_12bok2n.mp3','2023-09-15 17:59:54',143961989,'2023-12-11 22:50:27',NULL,'The Radical Reverend Show continues its conversation about the intersection of religion and politics with two guests: Lynn Adamson, a Quaker leader and social justice activist, and Michael Polanyi , an environmentalist and Unitarian activist. The guests discuss how faith can be used in the struggle for a more just society.',NULL,NULL),(62846,170,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/k6c832/Ruby_Slippers_Sept_15_mp3_-_2023-09-11_905_PM76h9x.mp3','2023-09-15 22:46:09',111378520,'2023-12-11 22:28:57',NULL,'The next artist on the show is DWI, who is a member of the band Zoo Life. He has released an album called Zoo Life, which contains a mix of self-operato and self-reflection.\n\nHe also has a live recording of Motorus from a mixtape called We Are Time. The rest of the show consists of a mix from various other artists, including Sleepy Driver, Lion Eats, DWI, Elk City, Indifferent Monkey and Wilfred Kosev. The show is available on the website of the Canadian Independent Television Union, under the show\'s page on the Podbean for downloads. The next band on the program is Indifferent Monkeys, who have released a new album called Love and Peace On The Big Blue.\n\nThey also have a live CD. The CD contains a live version of the title track. The band has also released a collection of tracks from the CD called When Angels Kill, which includes Fifth Angel. The gig for Black Rose and Church of Trees is tomorrow night. The listeners can enter a contest to win tickets to the show.',NULL,NULL),(62853,187,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/iv26s6/DREAMING_-_EPISODE_SEPTEMBER_15_2023bl8t6.mp3','2023-09-15 23:02:00',140857085,'2023-12-11 19:08:13',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(62856,257,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/twe9v7/September_14_2023_Psychedelic_Stoner_Rock9cizx.mp3','2023-09-15 17:08:02',287962512,'2023-12-11 17:06:20',NULL,'This week on Psychedelic And Stoner Rock, host Ken Stauer celebrates the two-year anniversary of the first edition of the program. He asks listeners to send him a copy of their favorite Psychedelic and/or Stoner-Rock playlist to Ken. Stauer recommends that listeners listen to the first show of the show and then go to the link on the Psychedelic And/Or-Stoner Rock webpage and listen to this program.',NULL,NULL),(62857,216,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/pwca6y/091523.mp3','2023-09-16 02:18:56',287962512,'2023-12-11 16:47:13',NULL,'The Big Raw Takeover, Selector Sunshine, Illegal Soul, and the Dungeons-o-Lids are all at the Jingle Bell Run booth, and they are all there to support the local community radio station, CIUT FM. The boys are there to challenge Sly, Roddy, and Dolly. The guys are psyched to be there, but they\'re also bummed because Kalliopi is not with them, and she\'s not with us.',NULL,NULL),(62858,292,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/7zkn7n/September_15_2023_The_Cool_Side_of_the_Pillow8bmmi.mp3','2023-09-15 19:03:27',287962512,'2023-12-11 16:27:06',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(62859,78,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/15/Morning Soul Shake-Up! - September 15, 2023 at 08:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-15 08:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-11 16:06:27',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(62860,120,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/14/The Crooked Beat - September 14, 2023 at 20:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-14 20:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-11 15:04:26',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(62861,122,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/15/Forever Deaf - September 1