onsulting.\n\nShe has over 20 years experience in the fields of education, development, and coaching adults. She is also the chair of the Come As You are Alliance, a wellness non-profit. She earned her master of science degree in human resource training and development. She\'s an associate certified coach from International Coach Federation, a certified professional coach, an ICF certified coach, and an ICF/IPAC certified coach. Her personal philosophy is',NULL,NULL),(63502,99,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/20/The Stillness & The Dancing - September 20, 2023 at 10:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-20 10:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-09 13:07:53',NULL,'In this program, Owen discusses the release of a new album by Glasis entitled \"Rebirth of a Kind from the Original Idea.\" The tracks on the album contain \"relics of the original works that respond and respond in different ways.\" Some of the tracks contain \"moments of original works,\" while others are unrecognizable. The album is available on Bandcamp and Owen encourages listeners to listen and \"dive into\" the music.\n\nHe also mentions that this is the first piece he has ever listened to that he has memorized. The music then shifts to the Illuvian Orchestra\'s \"Wichiters and Consensus Reality,\" which Owen calls \"The Light.\" The title of this program comes from a poem by poet Tessellia, which Owen says is \"the first poem I have ever memorized as part of an adult reawakening with poetry.\" Eno\'s latest album, \"The Turning Year,\" was released last year and Owen had not heard it before.',NULL,'A new release from a new member of the scattered ambient experimental family'),(63503,99,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/20/The Stillness & The Dancing - September 20, 2023 at 09:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-20 09:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-09 12:49:16',NULL,'The program opens with a selection of new music from the web. The first track is from a band called the Balloonist, who put out a record called \"The Stillness and The Dancing\" last year. The band describes the album as being \"a tape worn and glide above the English countryside, an Arcadia that has never existed within the minds mind\" . The music is described as \"fog and sun bleached recollections of childhood\" , and \"autumn chill of impending adolescent\". The music ends with a release from another band called Lightning White Bison, who released an album called \"Taroquecis Trace\" last summer.\n\nThe album describes an artist residency on a Norwegian island called Skolmer. The narrator describes the project as \"observation and gathering of signals of sound and additional solar signifiers\" and \"obstinate drones and textures\". The narrator notes that there is something about the residencies that makes them so unique. Then there is a piano track from Sun Rain, a release by Curtis who is an artist friend of Curtis\'s.',NULL,'A curated series of ambient music and art that is a curated . series of curated music and . art that are '),(63513,100,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/20/We Know Some Stuff + CFRU playlist - September 20, 2023 at 12:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-20 12:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-09 12:27:44',NULL,'This week on the show, Amora Wah runs a show called SoPerg on CFRU\'s 93.3FM. She tells listeners that only 31% of the people in the province have signed up for organ and tissue donation. She encourages listeners to take the time to sign up and to share their wishes with their family after they have died. If you\'re interested in becoming a donor, you can go to BeDonAor.ca and fill out the form. The narrator invites listeners to tune in to the show every Wednesday at 1pm to hear more of his guests.\n\nOn this week\'s show, Gowan is introduced and introduces his guest, Brian Choi, an account manager for People\'sGroup. Brian says that summer is coming to an end and it\'s time to enjoy it. He walks his dog every morning at 6.37 am and every time he goes outside he feels the cold outside',NULL,NULL),(63514,1437,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/20/Democracy Now - September 20, 2023 at 11:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-20 11:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-09 12:12:54',NULL,'This program opens with a description of the situation between India and Canada. The Canadian Prime Minister, Justin Trudeau, has accused the Indian government agents of assassinating an important Canadian Sikh leader in June. The situation is growing between Canada, India, and the United States. The case of Julian Assange, the founder of WikiLeaks, is also a hot topic. The president of Colombia has called on the American government to free him. The vice president of the United State, Joe Biden, has also called for the release of Julian. We\'re also going to hear from the president of Brazil',NULL,NULL),(63524,195,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/g9su64/Dementia13Radio_23_09_19.mp3','2023-09-20 19:37:52',287962512,'2023-12-09 11:48:13',NULL,'In this special edition of Dementia 13, we hear the voice of the man behind Dementia 13 on the famous CIUTFM program, Dementia 13. He tells us that he\'s here to tell us about the music of the psychedelic era. He explains that he likes to play music from the period, especially from the early 70s, and then he tells us about some of the artists who were involved in the music.\n\nThe first artist he mentions is the singer of Steppenwolf, who was one of the most popular artists of the era. The next song he plays is a song by the musician Neil Merriweather, who played with a band called the Rockets. The last song he performs is a tribute to the band the Wimple-Winch, who he says were one of those bands that really stuck out in his opinion.',NULL,NULL),(63535,102,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/20/End Credits - September 20, 2023 at 15:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-20 15:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-09 11:10:50',NULL,'On this episode, Adam A Donaldson and Peter Wesley Salmon discuss the recent protests in Ottawa. The show is an entertainment program that airs on the campus of the Canadian Film and Television Academy. The program is a weekly program that reviews new releases and gives recommendations for theaters and VOD outlets in Canada. Adam also discusses the recent theatrical release of the animated princess to kitchen-er.',NULL,NULL),(63536,1464,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/20/Gryphon And Special Olympics Sports Show - September 20, 2023 at 16:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-20 16:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-09 10:51:25',NULL,'The show starts off with the co-host of the show introducing himself as \"Boss Taylor\" and then proceeds to introduce the host as \"Leonard Squosin.\" The show then shifts to a song and a segment. The song is called \"Hit Record,\" and the segment is short.\n\nThe interview with the coach of the Gryphon womens basketball team begins. The coach, Megan Reed, tells the listeners how she got involved with basketball and why she wanted to become a coach. Her father, a basketball coach, instilled in her a love of the game and she began playing every day. She also began attending basketball camps as a counselor when she was 16. She enjoys watching other people learn new skills and being able to help others.',NULL,NULL),(63555,105,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/20/B Siide Radio - September 20, 2023 at 19:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-20 19:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-09 10:24:13',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(63556,106,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/20/Trail Mix - September 20, 2023 at 20:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-20 20:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-09 10:07:05',NULL,'The show opens with a description of the music on the show. It is a mix of music from various artists who will be performing at the upcoming 2022 Guelph Jazz festival.\n\nThe show then moves on to a new set of artists, including the Smile, Nuri\'s Dorpa band, Bill Orkut\'s band, and more. The first artist is Sam Shalabi, who will perform his own set of music. The second artist is Land of Enigma, a Montreal based band. The third artist is Aha, an album that will be performed on its entirety at the festival. Before that, the show heard Marilyn Lerner, Rampersod, Joshua Abrams, and the National Natural information Society perform. The fourth artist is Douglas T. Ely with Yes I am Lonely, an original song. The fifth artist is the Sadies.\n\nThe sixth artist is Nuri, his band, with Juan Deebs. The seventh artist is The Smile, with his band. There is a new music piece from Bill Otkut, called Music for Guitars. The Smile has a new song called We Dont Know What tomorrow Brings. And the eighth artist is Abigail Lapel with a song called What if I said New Brunswicks Motherhood in there with Sadie and Abigail. The last artist is Eric Chenot, who is also playing at the 2022 festival.',NULL,NULL),(63566,107,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/20/Tone Zone - September 20, 2023 at 21:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-20 21:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-09 09:48:04',NULL,'The guys talk about some of the stupid things they\'ve done in their life. They talk about a new edition of the Breeders\'s \"Last Splash\" coming out this Friday. They also talk about British bands releasing new albums. The guys play a song called \"Stems of a Niece\" from The Clientel\'s new album I am not there anymore. And they play another song from British band Slowdive\'s brand new album \"Everything is Alive\" on the \"Tone Zone\" with Matt. They invite you to come back next Wednesday and listen to the show.',NULL,NULL),(63576,289,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/5jd7ak/The_Next_Stop_1179582e.mp3','2023-09-21 04:57:00',269735877,'2023-12-09 09:28:24',NULL,'The next stop on the program is Cient 89.5 FM, where we hear music from the film, Days of Heaven. The first track is Harvest from the score by Ennio Morritone. Next up is Madvillain and the Dooms with Great Day. Then there\'s Akai Solo with the SOM, Manilla with VST, Kim Mi with It Raining, and last but not least, Bebe with Bebe.',NULL,NULL),(63577,97,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/21/Wild Combination - September 21, 2023 at 00:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-21 00:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-09 09:04:48',NULL,'The CFRU radio station is a wonderful, eclectic, and volunteer-run station. The station also has a web presence, and listeners can find all of their shows, as well as all of the station\'s news and information, all in one place.',NULL,NULL),(63587,97,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/21/Wild Combination - September 21, 2023 at 01:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-21 01:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-09 08:47:39',NULL,'The new radio and media center offers a variety of media focused volunteer opportunities. We are looking for anyone interested in audio and/or video production. We always look for anyone with a interest in music production. If you are fascinated by and music is your thing, you can become a producer editor for one of the current shows. You can help with live and studio events, or assist with the production of advertising and promos.\n\nWe can help you develop skills with our industry-standard audio and video equipment. Whenever you want to start, email us at rcfu.ca. You might be interested in punk rock, and join us on Monday nights for Ripcord, a local punk rock station. We\'ll be listening to some deep cuts and classic artists, some \"whacks and ends\" and you might learn something or two. You\'re welcome to tune in and listen.',NULL,NULL),(63616,219,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/j4vp9i/ES230920.mp3','2023-09-21 14:02:22',138339353,'2023-10-28 11:39:25',NULL,'James Bailey plays a piece by Margaret Maria, or as she was known back then, Margaret Obolovska. Emma Rush plays something played by Emma Rush and it\'s from a release called A Dream of Color. You\'re going to hear a thing called Cloud Chamber by Cora and then something else from, oh, Hard Rubber Orchestra. And then we\'ll have some James Rolfe to finish it off.',NULL,'James Bailey plays a piece by Margaret Maria. Emma Rush plays something played by Emma Rush'),(63617,78,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/21/Morning Soul Shake-Up! - September 21, 2023 at 08:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-21 08:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-09 08:25:21',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(63618,110,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/21/Here Today - September 21, 2023 at 07:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-21 07:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-09 08:11:16',NULL,'On this episode of Here Today, Aaron Badgley welcomes listeners to the show and introduces them to several new artists. The first artist is a band called Forsaken Keep from Victoria, British Columbia. The band\'s new album is called \"The Wonders of Earth And Sky\" and is loosely based on the book \"The Shadow Of The Torturer\" by Gene Wolf, who is a well-known horror writer.\n\nThe second artist is \"Church of Trees\" from Toronto, Canada. They just performed with the \"Elmo Combos\" in Toronto. The third artist is Hannah Georges from Vancouver, Canada, who has been nominated for many Juno Awards. She has a brand-new album out called \"If I Said I Did\'t Care/I\'d be Lying\" and she\'s been playing music since she was 12 years old. The fourth artist is Jen Kay Wilson, a classically trained pianist from Toronto. She is a visual artist, a musician, and a composer.\n\nHer latest album is \"Infinity Plus One\" and it is described as \"beautiful\" and \"beautifully beautiful\". The fifth artist is David Francine from Scotland, who was born and grew up in Canada. The show closes with a shout out to Hannah Georges and George Hannahs.',NULL,NULL),(63623,182,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/xygup7/Sept_20_202385gtg.mp3','2023-09-21 15:56:04',144696423,'2023-12-09 07:08:27',NULL,'This week on No Beat Radio, Minash hosts a show called \"Altered Realities,\" which focuses on the theme of \"altered realities.\" The show includes new releases by Ishmael Butler, Woke Up In A Dream featuring Lily, and Armden Hammer.\n\nThe show also features the first song from an upcoming release by Matthew Edward Barnes, called \"The Reality is Depth under my voice is Warning.\" Minash welcomes listeners to the show and introduces himself as Manesh, the host and programmer of the show. He explains that the music on the show is eclectic and that they include music from Chad Van Galen, Jessica Moss, Blurt, Captain of None, Jet, and many more artists. The music on this week\'s show is described in greater detail.',NULL,NULL),(63629,111,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/21/Tales from the Bridge - September 21, 2023 at 09:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-21 09:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-09 06:51:07',NULL,'The narrator and the other hosts of the show introduce themselves and explain the purpose of the program. The first purpose is to introduce listeners to the science fiction author, Andy Weir, who will be on the show. The second purpose is for listeners to learn more about the author, who is a self-proclaimed space nerd. The third purpose is also to introduce the show to the audience. The show starts with a description of the author and his career.\n\nThe author has published several science fiction novels, including The Martian, which was made into a movie starring Matt Damon. His latest novel, called The Martian: Project Hail Mary is being adapted into a new movie directed by the same director who directed the Spider-verse films. The book is also a Hugo Award Finalist and a favorite science fiction book of the narrator.',NULL,NULL),(63630,112,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/21/FoodFarm Talk - September 21, 2023 at 10:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-21 10:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-09 06:27:21',NULL,'The first person we meet in this interview is Mike Smith, the coordinator of the Guelph-Center for Urban Organic Agriculture. He\'s the guy who runs the university\'s gardens and teaches students how to grow and harvest their own food. Mike\'s been at the university for two years now, and he\'s worked in the agriculture industry for about 20 years now. He started out as a summer student at the University, but then he got a job managing a vegetable farm for a couple of years. He then went back to the University to teach and mentor students.',NULL,NULL),(63640,189,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/vgpfhh/VFTC_SteveSep20bb1dpx.mp3','2023-09-21 16:33:07',278830080,'2023-12-09 06:10:37',NULL,'The show starts off with a great introduction from the master of the show, who introduces himself as \"Crypt Master Sean.\" He says that he\'s been playing music on the show for over a year now. One of his guests is Steve, who he says is a Brit and loves music.\n\nHe adds that he was a kid who used to watch pop shows on British Television. The show is full of music from all over the world. The first song is from the Beatles, who came out with \"Day Tripper\" in December of 1965. The next three songs are from Canadian bands, and the last one is a song from the US It\'s called \"Chalk Eyes\" by Kim Carnes. The next song is a British song called \"Ichi Ku Park\" by the Small Faces. It was originally released in Canada early in 68. It features a recording device called \"phasing.\"',NULL,NULL),(63641,90,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/21/Bridging The Social Distance - September 21, 2023 at 12:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-21 12:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-09 05:10:48',NULL,'In this episode, Jenny Mitchell rebroadcasts one of her earlier episodes. This time, she talks with Matthew Forbes, the owner of Saturday Seed Co in Guelph. Matthew tells her that he\'s always had a passion for growing things. He says that he loves looking at seeds, and that he just wants to know why something looks the way it does. He explains that he became a barber because he loves to look at things and wonder about them.',NULL,NULL),(63642,1437,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/21/Democracy Now - September 21, 2023 at 11:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-21 11:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-09 04:49:54',NULL,'Amy Goodman brings us the latest news from New York. She tells us that the United Nations is holding a series of peace summits this week to discuss the war in Palestine and the conflict in the Ukraine.\n\nShe says that the military occupation of both countries is different, but there is a \"different attitude\" among the world powers. The U.S back coup against Chile was 50 years ago, and the blockade of Cuba and Venezuela has had the same type response. It\'s the United States that is the one that imposed the blockade. Amy Goodman is back with more news. She reports that the U.N\'s Secretary-General Antonio Guterres warned that humanity has opened the \"gates of hell\" as',NULL,NULL),(63652,113,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/21/Android’s Dungeon - September 21, 2023 at 13:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-21 13:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-09 04:28:07',NULL,'The next morning, I\'m back on the streets of',NULL,NULL),(63653,3686,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/21/Volunteer Playlist - September 21, 2023 at 14:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-21 14:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-09 04:07:51',NULL,'This week, the U. G. Graduate Coalition, OPIC Wealth, and the Guelph chapter of the Brotherhood are excited to announce that Disorientation Week will be held at the University of G.C. on September 18th through the 21st, 2023. The week will include a wide variety of events and activities to bring people together around shared values.\n\nGet involved by visiting www.operuelph.Org. Get the latest updates on Disorientation. Follow the organization on Instagram at @OPERG Guelph, @GRIFENS G.R.Y.P.H.O.N.S 3913, and @UofG.C-C- C. For more info about Disorientation, check out the official DisorientationWeek webpage. On October 14th and 15th, the Guelph Studio Tour will be taking place. Forty three local artists will be opening their studios or exhibiting their work in an exhibition space.',NULL,NULL),(63654,8658,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2022/09/01/Night Beach - September 1, 2022 at 21:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2022-09-01 21:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-09 03:47:50',NULL,'Th