ow to get involved in the community, check out our new YouTube Channel.',NULL,NULL),(63678,8658,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2022/03/10/Night Beach - March 10, 2022 at 21:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2022-03-10 21:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-08 14:27:11',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(63688,205,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/3jc6r2/September_21st_2023_Music_at_High_Noona2zqk.mp3','2023-09-21 20:19:19',287962512,'2023-12-08 14:05:55',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(63689,115,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/21/RadiOPIRG - September 21, 2023 at 15:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-21 15:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-08 13:46:04',NULL,'This week, the program\'s host, Radiopirg, continues his work with the OCHA and another organization called Birdsafe Guelph, which supports students in their studies of bird ecology. The program also includes an interview with Sarah Mueller of the organization, who is a student at the university studying bird ecology and sparrow ecology. Sarah is one of the group\'s founders, and they\'re a student group.',NULL,NULL),(63690,116,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/21/T.K.O. - September 21, 2023 at 16:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-21 16:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-08 13:32:36',NULL,'This is a very brief interview with \"Janan,\" the co-host of \"The TKO Show\" on CFRU 93.3 FM. She is a student at the university and she and her co-hosts talk about mixed martial arts, also known as \"MMA\" and \"combat sports.\" They also discuss the \"issues\" surrounding the world of combat sports. She tells the listeners that she has begun to \"try to so many things\" and that out of nowhere, she just \"gets this.\"',NULL,NULL),(63694,175,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/a8estv/September_14th_2023_No_Man_s_Land6jiw0.mp3','2023-09-21 22:29:40',287962512,'2023-12-08 13:05:01',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(63695,167,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/ympkk3/September_15th_2023_Funky_Fridaysb7w7x.mp3','2023-09-21 22:35:00',431961989,'2023-12-08 12:53:53',NULL,'Funky Fridays is a new program on the CIUT. We\'ve brought in a new host, Mr. Pete. He\'s a musician who\'s been around for a while, but he\'s still new to music.\n\nHe plays some classic funk and soul tracks, like this one from 1975. It\'s called Miss Brown by the Chambers Brothers. This is one of the brothers who were in the psychedelic rock band The Chambers Brothers back in the day. The brothers have been fighting for the rights to their records and for black artists who are underpaid for their work. A lot of their records were stolen and they had to raise money on a GoFundMe campaign to get them back. Leon Chambers is a vocal artist who has been vocalizing for a lot of black artists underpaid. He was assaulted at a Blues festival in 2013 when he dedicated his song to Trayvon Martin.\n\nHe still lives in California. The other tracks on the Funky Fridays program are from the late 60s and early 70s. They\'re all great artists. Charles Walker is featured on the first two tracks. The Dynamites is a band that was formed in the mid-\'70s. Charles Wheat was also featured on one of their albums. Lonnie Smith is also featured.',NULL,NULL),(63698,161,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/p9kdgs/VientoSur-September23th-2023.mp3','2023-09-21 22:47:56',80578171,'2023-12-08 12:30:58',NULL,'Welcome to the show. We\'ve got a new host, Marco Lopez, who\'s just had the chance to hear some great music. He\'ll bring some new music from the station, including some of the best music from Chile. He brings in some of his favorites, like Angelo and Alturas, and some new stuff from the American band Metallica. He also brings in two covers, one of the songs from the war in Afghanistan and the other of the song from the band Metallica, Nothing Else Matters. The show ends with a song by a band called Jubia de verano, which means \"summer rain.\"',NULL,NULL),(63703,206,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/n22bd7/September_16th_2023_The_Minx_Sessions91h7c.mp3','2023-09-21 22:25:36',287962512,'2023-12-08 12:07:56',NULL,'The first part of the show is from CIUT 89.4FM, a local Toronto-based station. It is a celebration of independent music and they are going to present some of the upcoming releases from some of these artists on their own labels.\n\nThe first track is from Philip Joanne Thiem, who is a member of the Parat collective and will be releasing a new album under that name in October. The second track is also from Philip, and it is a song called \"Tomorrow Comes the Harvest.\" The third track is a track called \"Robert,\" which is a new track from Basis. The fourth track is called \"Metamorphous,\" a track from the Tomorrow Comes The Harvest album with a Bass-In-Aid instrumental mix. The fifth track is \"Rising Water,\" a song from the upcoming album.',NULL,NULL),(63704,206,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/qj82d2/September_9th_2023_The_minx_Sessions8ykpq.mp3','2023-09-21 22:24:06',287962512,'2023-12-08 11:47:31',NULL,'In this episode of the \"Mikel Sessions\", we catch up with the man who is at the heart of the underground music scene in Canada, Kyle Hall. He\'s been working as a DJ for over a decade now, but he\'s always wanted to do something more ambitious, so he decided to open a club in his hometown, called CIUT, which stands for \"from the Toronto roots up.\" The club will feature some of the best underground music from all over the world, and it\'s going to be hosted by a dude named Mathias. Mathias is a guy who works for a major music label, and he',NULL,NULL),(63705,247,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/wvkewa/September_16th_2023_Calling_All_Blues83eat.mp3','2023-09-21 22:19:35',143961989,'2023-12-08 11:30:48',NULL,'The song is called \"Soul Brother,\" and it\'s a song by the brothers. The song doesn\'t have a title, but the song\'s title is \"All That\'s Left is This Song I Can\'t Keep Your Heart From Playing and Singing For the Singers\" . The brothers play a song from their new album \"Soul fuckin\' blues\" , and they\'re going to play it with Kenny and his son.\n\nThe family theme of the day is family, so they\'ll do a song called \"Absolute pleasure song\" from Daisy Brink\'s. The Campbell Brothers play another song from Daisy\'s album, and the guys from the Landreths play another one. The guys from \"The Campbell Brothers\" are awesome. They\'re awesome. And the landreth brothers are awesome, too.',NULL,NULL),(63706,247,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/eircxp/September_9th_2023_Calling_All_Bluesbhbqm.mp3','2023-09-21 22:19:00',143961989,'2023-12-08 11:14:41',NULL,'On this week\' edition of Calling All Blues, the host and producer of the show, Brooke Blackburn, takes us on a journey through the music of the late singer, songwriter, and record producer, Lamont Dozier. Dozier was a member of several Motown groups before being recruited by Barry Gordy and the Holland brothers to become a part of the group\'s chart-topping machine.\n\nAfter writing and producing for the label, Dozier left and resumed his own music career. The Holland brothers founded their own label, Invictus Records, and produced more number one hits. He was also a writer and composer for movie and music soundtracks. He taught at university, and was inducted in to the Rock & Roll Hall of fame in 1990. He wrote songs for movies and soundtracks. The show begins with three tracks that are from his early career with the Hollands, the Doziers, and the Motowns. The first song is Heat Wave, a song that he loves. The second song is called Chairman of The Board, a tribute to Canada\'s local singer, Harrison.\n\nThe third track is from Soul Train, a record of which the lead vocalist is Harrison. It is a live recording, which means that only the music and the music video are actually live. The fourth track is called Shine, a reworking of his early hits by Dozier in later years. The fifth track is a song called Martha Reeve and The Vandalas. The title song is from the early days of the Holland',NULL,NULL),(63707,186,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/tus267/September_14th_2023_Higher_Ground63cdl.mp3','2023-09-21 22:31:55',287962512,'2023-12-08 10:50:01',NULL,'The show opens with a description of the music on the upcoming Higher Ground show. The program begins with a list of upcoming shows, and then moves on to some more music.\n\nThe first show is called \"Song of the Ancestor\", and it\'s about the story of a young man named Joseph who is kidnapped and put to death. The next show is \"Joe Joe From Panveloff\" and the third is \"Tioga Pass\", an album by a drummer named Rocco Paladino. The fourth is \"Black Classical Music\" by Joss Peterson. The fifth is \"Pass\", a new album from the Lation jazz series, and the sixth is \"The Vom Volume\" by the Spiritual jazz series.\n\nThe seventh is \"Sounds of D. D. Sharp\", which is a song about a woman \"chasing honey\" . The eighth is \"Prophylactic Control\" by Gil Gamble, an artist from Love Touch Records. The ninth is \"Proof Control\", another show by Love Touch. The eleventh is \"Too Much Thursday\" by Oscar Jerome. The twelfth is \"Afro Cubism\" by USF Days, a project of Lorenzo Moreci and La Esso. The thirteenth is \"Slope\" by Lorenzo.',NULL,NULL),(63708,118,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/21/Open Sources Guelph - September 21, 2023 at 17:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-21 17:00:00',86638720,'2023-10-30 19:42:06',NULL,'The show begins with a welcome to the open source community from Adam A. Donaldson of the Guelph Politico and Scott Hertz of Guelph FM Donaldson. The show is hosted by Adam, who is the host of the CFRU 93.2 open source news program. The program covers the latest news from the region and around the globe. Adam and Scott discuss the recent events in the city. First, the Canadian government has announced that the Indian government has murdered a Canadian citizen, a Sikh man named Hardeep Nijar. This news has caused tensions with India, who has issued an international travel advisory for anyone from the Indian state visiting Canada. This has also brought up the frosty relationship between the two countries at the G20. The program also discusses the upcoming military cooperation summit being held in India. It is not clear if this summit will have any negative effects on Canada, but it will certainly have a chilling effect on other countries. The Canadian government is not in any hurry to cancel the summit. It has, however, shut down the business of the country\'s embassy in India after the failed trade talks with India. If this is the case, it is highly unusual, and it is a blow to the Canadian political system. The Canadians are demanding to know the exact nature of the killing, but the government does not have the means to give them the information they need. The killing seems to have been coordinated among a number of organizations, including some who had been trying to kill Hardeep for years. It',NULL,'New Open Source News Program is a blow to the Canadian political system'),(63709,119,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/21/Turtle Island Underground - September 21, 2023 at 18:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-21 18:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-08 10:30:34',NULL,'This episode is a toast episode and it is hosted by Dorothy Keiler, the founder of Turtle Island Underground and Dorothy\'s friend, and by Natasha Keiler , a musician and dancer from Albuquerque, a New Mexico city.\n\nThe two women are excited about the release of their latest album, \"The Third Kind.\" The music is influenced by a number of artists including Ixuma , the \"Oba Man\" , and the song \"I am Princeton.\" The song \"Sounds and Noise\" is one of the most popular tracks on the album. The album title was inspired by the alien sound of the album and the first song was called Sounds and noise. The songs \"Stay on the Path\" and \"Goodness Gracious\" were also influenced by artists from Canada. The last song is \"Black Man in White World.\"',NULL,NULL),(63728,120,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/21/The Crooked Beat - September 21, 2023 at 19:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-21 19:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-08 10:12:16',NULL,'On the second week of his show, Nicky Dread gives a brief introduction to the show, and then introduces himself. He explains that the show is called \"The Crooked Beat\" because it honors the many children, families and communities who have been forced to attend government-run, church-run residential schools. The show honors the over 150,000 children, survivors and families affected by forced attendance at these schools.\n\nHe notes that the music on the show speaks the truth about many critical issues, and he hopes that each of the listeners will act on the messages and take the messages to heart. He also remembers the death earlier this month of a singer named Karen Smith. He brings up a number of reissues of music from reggae records, including Lee Scratch Perry\'s \"Evil Tongues\" and \"Burning Spear\" from his self-titled 1980 album, \"Hail HIM, his Imperial Majesty,\" and \"Fall of Marcus,\" which was the title track of his earlier album Hail HIM. Also in the mix is a track called \"No One\" from Freddy McGregor\'s 1982 recording, \"Burning-Spear.\" The show closes with a new song by Maddy Simmons.',NULL,NULL),(63729,122,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/21/Forever Deaf - September 21, 2023 at 22:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-21 22:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-08 09:48:18',NULL,'The stage opens with a song called \"Sanguine\" by a Canadian band called Illyrian who play video games. The song is called \"Songer\" and refers to a mansion in the game Eternal Darkness. Then the song is \"Slippekit\" by The Who.\n\nAfter that, he plays \"Anvil, Legal at last\" and \"Get High\" from the Electric Sounds album. He then plays \"Jaded\" by the Canadian band Spirit Box. He also plays a song by the band Red Cane called \"Call of the Void\" and another by the group Devolver called \"Jewels of the Mall\" . The show ends with a single from the band Devolver.',NULL,NULL),(63730,8658,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/21/Night Beach - September 21, 2023 at 21:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-21 21:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-08 09:05:14',NULL,'If you\'re looking for a place to work on an art project, you\'ve come to the right place. But, you don\'t know where to start. You\'re not sure what\'s wrong with the project, and you need help getting started. That\'s why the makers at the Free Spirit are here. They\'re a non-profit community workshop that offers tools and equipment to anyone who wants to learn how to make things. We invite you to join us every Monday evening at 8pm at our new location, 700 York Road.',NULL,NULL),(63731,8658,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/21/Night Beach - September 21, 2023 at 20:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-21 20:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-08 08:44:54',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(63741,122,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/22/Forever Deaf - September 22, 2023 at 00:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-22 00:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-08 08:28:29',NULL,'It\'s the last show of the season, and the guys are psyched to be back on the air. They\'re psyched to see some of the bands that have been playing in the past few weeks.\n\nThe first song we hear is a cover of a classic by a band called Morbids Vision. Then we hear a new song by a new band called Raw To Eternal. Then the guys hear a song called Mercenary, which sounds a little bit like a cover band. Then it\'s back to the original music. The guys play a bunch of new stuff. First up is a song by the band called Cavalier Conspiracy. Then they play a song from the band\'s sub-ultur album, which is basically a band from the 80s.\n\nAnd then the guys play some new stuff, too. We\'re back with the guys, and they play some more new stuff from the last few weeks, too, including a new EP from Jason Ashcroft, a new album from KK, and a new track from a Texas band called HinaYana. The last song is a tribute to the Canadian Forces, called Cold.',NULL,NULL),(63742,122,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/21/Forever Deaf - September 21, 2023 at 23:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-21 23:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-08 07:10:54',NULL,'This is the second hour of the show. It\'s been a while since the last time we heard from the Crooked Beat, and he\'s got some news for you: Metaproducts has started blocking news from viewers.\n\nThis is a response to Bill 18, which was passed by the Conservative government. For those of you who don\'t know, Bill 18 was a piece of legislation that basically made it illegal for anyone in Canada to access any news from any source, including Facebook, Twitter, and Google. The Canadian government responded to this by passing the Canada First Act. This means that, for now, Canadians can\'t access the news from the University of Guelph. They\'ve also had to stop sharing their social media content on Facebook and Twitter. If you want to continue to support them, they encourage you to sign up for their newsletter at the university\'s website slash newsletter. The Guelph MP, Lloyd Longfield, is also involved in this fight. He\'s a member of Parliament, so he can make a real difference.\n\nSo, if you\'re in the Guelph area, you can contact him. And if you want more news about what\'s going on in the world, you should check out the All Grand Rivers Waterwalk, which is coming up in a couple of days. You can visit the waterwalk website to find out more about it. Here\'s the second track from the show: \"Walk with Titans\" from the Olympic release. Next',NULL,NULL),(63752,122,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/22/Forever Deaf - September 22, 2023 at 01:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-22 01:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-08 06:46:41',NULL,'This is the final edition of the Underground Rock Show, and it\'s time for Rafsan to come back. He\'s back with a bunch of new music from various underground acts. First up is Dying Fetus, who\'s touring with their new album. Then there\'s Gory Blister, who just released a new single. And then there are 200 stab wounds from masters of merbidity. And there are also some new songs from Enthios, Impergator, and others.\n\nAnd finally there\'ll be a bunch more music from Harper, who is 11 or 12 years old and is a member of Brand of Sacrifice. She\'s got a single out called weight of the world, which sounds like a really good song. And Job for a cowboy has released their fifth album, which is called the \"Agony seeping storm\" . So this is the last time we\'ll hear',NULL,NULL),(63776,180,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/jy5j2n/HOWL_SEPTEMBER_19_202366md6.mp3','2023-09-22 12:21:34',56689813,'2023-12-08 06:37:40',NULL,'This show is about to begin, and we\'re introduced to the host, a young Italian man named Valentino Assanza. We\'re also introduced to him by his first name, which is \"Assenza.\" He\'s a musician, and he\'s got a show on Hal895FM, a station owned by the University of the Toronto.\n\nIt\'s called the \"Halifax Open Mic\" and it\'s open to anyone who\'d like to give a shout-out to their work. If you\'re interested in submitting a poem for the September open mic, send it to him at hal at CIIT dot FM. By tomorrow, he\'ll put it all together for the open mic.',NULL,NULL),(63782,78,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/22/Morning Soul Shake-Up! - September 22, 2023 at 08:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-22 08:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-08 06:10:39',NULL,'The host is back on stage again, this time with his band. This time he\'s accompanied by his son, Dr. K., who\'s on his way to a meeting with the Brotherhood. He\'s trying to get into the Brotherhood\'s meeting hall, but they\'ve locked him out. The Underground Men are psyched to be able to do this for the first time, and the host promises to keep it up.',NULL,NULL),(63784,173,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/39e3zj/Club_Ned_Sept_24_2023_Podcast6ljsb.mp3','2023-09-22 14:10:08',536919770,'2023-12-08 05:11:35',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(63793,123,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/22/Thanks for Listening :) - September 22, 2023 at 09:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-22 09:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-08 04:54:57',NULL,'In this chapter, the host of Thanks for Listening opens by saying that he is happy to be back on the program after listening to some new music that was released recently.\n\nHe also says that he misses the music that is released by mitzki because there is too much music out there that is good, but that he feels like he has fallen off the wagon of music in the past few years because there are too many good things out there. He starts off the program with a song called \"Hold by Elcon\" and then goes on to play songs by Beverly Glenn, Eliza Niemi, and Dorothea pass. He then tells the listeners about a music event that is happening next Thursday, September 23rd at the Upbeat Guitar studio.\n\nHe says that there is also a live performance by Sled at the Ed video studio. The show starts at 3pm and tickets are $20, which is great. The rest of the program is about the new releases in the music library. The first song is from the album \"Trip 9\" by Terza. The second song is \"Bleitsister\" by Bilesister. The third song is called \"Cops Ain\'t Helping My Problems\" by the band \"Terza.\" The show ends with \"No Other\" by Beverly.',NULL,NULL),(63794,124,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/22/Planet Groove - September 22, 2023 at 10:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-22 10:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-08 04:31:41',NULL,'The first show of the week is called \"Planet Groove\" and it starts off with a song by the King Crimson and ends with some more music by the band. The show then turns to the next show, \"Sonic Freak Show\" which is all about the variety of music that is available on the CFRU campus. The program starts off by introducing us to the host of the show, who introduces himself as \"Hellen\" and then introduces us to some of the students who are involved in the program. The students include Eliza from Mauna, a Hawaiian woman who works at the university, and Jeff, a young man who works for the university and who loves the music and the people at the school.',NULL,NULL),(63804,1437,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/22/Democracy Now - September 22, 2023 at 11:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-22 11:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-08 03:13:35',NULL,'The House Speaker has dismissed his members for the weekend after a few Republicans rebelled against a spending bill that would have kept the government open for another year.\n\nThe speaker blames members of his own party for wanting to \"burn the place down.\" He says it is increasingly likely that the government will close on October 1st. The previous week, Democratic Congresswoman Ilhan Omar criticized Republicans for demanding cuts to social services. Now, Republicans have launched some of the largest cuts ever to health care. Housing assistance, food assistance, the postal office and nearly every other program is cut. The Pentagon says it will exempt its operations in Ukraine from a government shutdown.',NULL,NULL),(63805,3686,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/22/Volunteer Playlist - September 22, 2023 at 12:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-22 12:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-08 02:45:51',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(63815,126,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/22/Viejoteca - September 22, 2023 at 14:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-22 14:00:00',86507648,'2023-09-22 20:07:17',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(63816,126,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/22/Viejoteca - September 22, 2023 at 13:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-22 13:00:00',86507648,'2023-09-22 20:07:18',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(63821,170,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/b53pfe/Ruby_Slippers_Sept_22_mp3_-_2023-09-18_303_PM9wf7z.mp3','2023-09-22 21:26:28',111378520,'2023-12-08 01:09:41',NULL,'Carol Barrett and her band are back in the studio, and Carol tells us that the band that she\'s working with is called Swansi Sound.\n\nThey\'ve just released an album called Twentieth Century, and it\'s got some great tracks. The first track is called Black Rose Burning from Ad Penthouse and Become The Machine, and the second is called Run With the Kittens And Blaze of Glory and Swansi Sounds with I Made A Work of Art. The band is called Hotel Mira, and they\'re from Canada. They have a sad song called \"It\'s alright / About so sad\" from their album. The show will be posted on Carol Barrett\'s website. They also have a new track called Le Couleur, which is about the sound of Carol\'s work. The second track is a song called Night from a father and son duo from Argentina. The song is called Night and it is about a ghost. The third track is also called Night. The next show is coming up next week.',NULL,NULL),(63827,127,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/22/LiYghTE FM - September 22, 2023 at 16:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-22 16:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-08 00:54:23',NULL,'This week\'s show is called \"The Home of Love Revolution\" and it\'s hosted by DJ Double D of CFRU\'s Light FM. It\'s a weekly showcase of the best music from the local music scene. In this program, the DJ breaks down each song and gives each track a shout-out. The first song is Shame by Yeah Yeah, the second is The Forest Awake by St. Vincent and David Byrne, and the third is G by Bloody Hell by Nobody Cares. We also hear about Lunas\'s new single, Compensate, which is a year-end release from his label, Lucky Me Records',NULL,NULL),(63828,1620,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/22/Hellfire Radio - September 22, 2023 at 15:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-22 15:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-07 23:12:33',NULL,'The show begins with the announcement that Saxon has not yet arrived at the university, but that they will keep the \"ghosty and toasty\" rocking and locked. The show then turns to a song called \"Drag Me Out\" by a band called Hurst. The song is a metal song with a heavy dose of thrash and the band\'s name is \"dumb.\n\n\" The show\'s host, Leonard, explains that he was late for the show, but he was glad to have some new music to play while he was getting his breath. He tells Hurst about a time when he went to see Iron Maiden and missed the first half of the show because he was lost in the crowd. But now, he says, he is ready to meet Saxon.',NULL,NULL),(63838,187,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/dd6ra8/DREAMING_-_EPISODE_SEPTEMBER_22_202369fl6.mp3','2023-09-22 23:01:00',141001090,'2023-12-07 22:50:03',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(63839,128,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/22/Walkuman Style - September 22, 2023 at 18:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-22 18:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-07 22:25:34',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(63840,135,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/22/Folk Roots Radio - September 22, 2023 at 17:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-22 17:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-07 21:08:10',NULL,'This is the first episode of the new season of Folk Roots with Jan Hall and Ian. The first song on the show is from Maine-based singer songwriter Annie Gallop, followed by songs from Sophie Janna in the Netherlands, Brooklyn and Moira from Nova Scotia, and from Toronto-based artist Duran.\n\nThey wrap the show with a song by the duo of Moira and Claire, who wrote it while they were finishing their undergraduate degrees during the pandemic, and wish they could just leave college and go off to be spontaneous and exciting artists. The band also includes a song about the personal impact of the climate crisis on people living on low-lying coast communities by the Vancouver-based band The Fugitive\'s, a song called \"Edge of the Sea\" by the Canadian artist Dale Butler, and a song written by the Alberta-based country singer-songwriter, Kyle Mckinne. The show ends with the first single from the forthcoming release of The Ald Collective, which is called \"Stay Positive.\"',NULL,NULL),(63850,129,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/22/Digital Statik - September 22, 2023 at 19:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-22 19:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-07 20:49:01',NULL,'DJ Julz of Natural Static joins us on the 93.3FM studios to talk about the latest music. He\'s got some great news for you: he\'s the new host of the hottest Canadian hip hop show on the Planet. He introduces us to GNA, the new name of one of the stars of the',NULL,NULL),(63851,3686,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/22/Volunteer Playlist - September 22, 2023 at 20:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-22 20:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-07 20:25:48',NULL,'This is the second in a series of two shows about the life sciences. The first is called \"Life Slash in Covidencing\" and the second is \"Life Incovidencing.\" It\'s all about the science of life. This is a very brief description of the science. The program ends with a shout-out to the students who are involved in the research. If you\'re interested in learning more about the research, you can find it on the university\'s website.',NULL,NULL),(63861,216,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/d4f8dv/RAW092223.mp3','2023-09-23 02:25:07',287962512,'2023-12-07 20:07:08',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(63862,132,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/22/Global Rare Grooves - September 22, 2023 at 21:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-22 21:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-07 19:07:11',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(63863,1491,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/22/Industry Tactics - September 22, 2023 at 22:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-22 22:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-07 18:51:16',NULL,'The narrator welcomes everyone back to the Industry Tactics podcast. He\'s sad to hear that Bernard Pierce has died. He and Bernard have known each other for a long time, and they connected in many ways. Bernard gave the narrator a lot of money, a bicycle, and a bunch of poetry.\n\nThe narrator is happy to hear he has a book deal, too, because he loves everything Bernard represents. He also notes that this is a few months ago, so we can listen to it now. This is a New Orleans-centric show, so it\'s all about the music. Today the narrator chats with Aurora Neeland about her new book, the Monocle.',NULL,NULL),(63873,1491,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/22/Industry Tactics - September 22, 2023 at 23:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-22 23:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-07 18:26:17',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(63874,1627,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/23/Jitterbuggin - September 23, 2023 at 00:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-23 00:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-07 18:10:51',NULL,'The Jitter-Buggin is a rock-and-roll show hosted by Adrian J. Adrian starts off by describing the show as a \"rock and roll show\" if you haven\'t heard it before.\n\nHe tells us that it\'s four minutes past midnight. He\'s been up all night, so he\'s got a little extra time to set his time as if he were in the middle of the night. He gives us a brief history of the show, and then he starts playing some music. He says that tonight, he\'ll be playing some songs by a Canadian band called \"Daddy Long Legs\" . He also has a few songs from a Black Rock and Roll album called \"Savage Kicks Volume Two\" , which is \"black rock and roll\" but also \"soulful gospel groups\" kind of music. So this will be all \"God Bless America\" stuff. Then he gets into a lengthy discussion about the music he\'d like to play tonight.\n\nHe explains that he wants to play music more than talk because he doesn\'t know what\'s going to happen on the stage when he tries to play upstairs. He has three tracks back-to-back with a \"Triple Header\" : \"Let It Rock,\" \"Barrett Strong Money,\" and \"Blues Brother\" ). He then gives us some more information about the journey to Chicago: \"It\'s 106 mi to Chicago\" and \"can\'t',NULL,NULL),(63912,197,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/pxz2dk/phil_s_inn_sept_23_238tlhy.mp3','2023-09-23 23:23:47',287962512,'2023-12-07 17:09:54',NULL,'The guys talk about a new album by one of their favorite artists, a Montreal-based musician named Glenn Copeland. He\'s back with a new song called \"The Ones Ahead\" and he\'ll be playing at a party at the inn where he works. The party will also feature some great music. The guys are excited about the fact that they\'re playing a song by a man they barely know, a man named \"Jackie Washington\" . The guy doesn\'t know the guy, but he thinks he\'s just a delight.',NULL,NULL),(63913,79,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/23/Breezy Breakfast Radio - September 23, 2023 at 08:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-23 08:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-07 16:51:06',NULL,'The next question comes from Brian Scarrett, who wants to know if the province will respect the murals at the old prison. He\'s worried that the province doesn\'t respect the mural at the prison because it\'s part of the province\'s Indigenous heritage.\n\nMayor Qualters says that he\'s already spoken up about this at an event last night, and that he plans to continue to do so. He also says that if people want to protest at the office of the MPP, they\'re welcome to do it. He says that when this issue was brought up at the last meeting, it was all about the city and not about the province. Therefore, he says, the province should hold the city accountable for this as well. He thanks everyone for coming to the meeting, and says that Morgan told him that he always gets strength from people.',NULL,NULL),(63914,79,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/23/Breezy Breakfast Radio - September 23, 2023 at 07:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-23 07:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-07 16:32:06',NULL,'This morning\'s program opens with a \"land acknowledgement\" from the host, followed by a speech from MPP Mike Schreiner about the importance of good neighbors and reconciliation. He then goes on to discuss the Dish with one spoon treaty and the Two-row wampum treaty. He says that if Europeans want to come to Turtle Island and stay, they can do so, but if they want to go to the other side of the ocean, they have to reconcile with the native people.',NULL,NULL),(63915,136,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/23/A Dog’s Breakfast - September 23, 2023 at 10:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-23 10:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-07 15:08:44',NULL,'Food Equity With Dignity takes high-quality, fresh produce destined for landfill, transforms them into gourmet take-home meals for the Welkes Community. These delicious dinners are offered free, or by donation, and are offered to all members of the community. Drawing upon the creativity, skill, and ability of experienced cooks, and volunteers, Food offers an equitable and nourishing foodsource for community members.\n\nWelcome to the A-Dog\'s Breakfast, where DJ Apostrophe is the host. He\'s back from a long hiatus, and this time he\'s going to play some of his favorite music. He says it\'s been a while since he played at the breakfast, so he thought it would be fun to start out with some of the music he played when he wasn\'t there.\n\nFirst, he\'ll play Autoricha, which is a song by Leonard Cohen. Then he\'d play a song called \"Bird on Wire,\" which is also a song about Leonard Cohen, and finally he\'\'d do a song from the book \"A Dog\'s New Year,\" which was written by the Toronto based plesmer artists. He ends up going to the plesmers\' band because that\'s where he met his partner, Ajay, when they were married.',NULL,NULL),(63916,138,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/23/Sound Magic - September 23, 2023 at 14:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-23 14:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-07 14:46:38',NULL,'This week on the show, Mahin tells us about the upcoming studio tour and sale, and about the Alzheimer\'s society\'s music project. Mahin also tells us that Silence is looking for support to keep its mission alive. They\'re asking listeners to pledge $10 a month to help them continue their work. If you can\'t commit, you can still support the cause by signing up for a free one-year subscription to Silence\'s newsletter, which will include all the latest news and information.',NULL,NULL),(63917,138,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/23/Sound Magic - September 23, 2023 at 13:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-23 13:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-07 14:29:25',NULL,'The program continues with a discussion of Czech music, focusing on the symphonies of Joseph Bohuselav Furst. We learn that the symphonies are similar to those of Mahler, but that there is a distinct \"Czech folkish element\" that is not usually recognized in these works. The program then moves on to the first recording of the Opus 36 third symphony, which was composed in the 1890s. The music is complex, with themes returning in certain movements. It is also quite expansive, with a lot of \"deeper eddies\" in the music.',NULL,NULL),(63918,138,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/23/Sound Magic - September 23, 2023 at 12:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-23 12:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-07 14:09:20',NULL,'On this program, Doleschell introduces Sound Magic, a program of classical music that airs every Saturday afternoon at about noon. The program begins with a full-scale symphony, written by Antonin Dvorak. It is also a great example of the style of Czech music that was popular in the late nineteenth and early twentieth century.\n\nThe symphony is performed by the famous Czech Philharmonic Orchestra under the baton of Vclav TALICI. The orchestra also includes a recording of the eight-movement symphony, which was originally recorded on a disc in 1935. The other piece on the program is a concerto by another famous Czech composer named Michael Dolasch.',NULL,NULL),(63919,139,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/23/Bel Araby with CAWA - September 23, 2023 at 15:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-23 15:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-07 13:53:11',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(63920,140,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/23/Caribbean Anthology - September 23, 2023 at 17:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-23 17:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-07 13:37:08',NULL,'In this chapter, the host describes how he first fell in love with the music scene and how he\'s now a part of it. He tells us about the first house of reggae, which was hosted by Nicki Dred and Analog. The first time he saw a real fight was when the two men were playing.\n\nThe two of them thought they were going easy with the crowd, and the crowd started to fight, but they didn\'t give it to the crowd. So they decided not to throw double plates, which is a common practice in the underground. Nicki Dr\'d came back and beat Analog, who was dropping tunes. The next day, people were talking about the fight, and it was reported that Nicki beat Analog. This is the guy who also has a weekly show on the station, 93.3 The Crooked Beat, called \"House of Reggae.\" The host says that he was so happy to work with Dredd because he was such a great person.\n\nHe also says that the next House of Reggae event was a little different, with Nkrumah, Albino and Jinx playing. They played on the analog side of the stage, and then Corinja was there, too. It was an awesome party, and everyone was there. The third party was also a party, with Tariq, Doc, and Nkruma as the headliner.',NULL,NULL),(63921,142,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/23/Tiempo de Mujeres - September 23, 2023 at 20:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-23 20:00:00',86507648,'2023-09-24 04:07:19',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(63922,141,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/23/Alternativa Latinoamericana - September 23, 2023 at 19:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-23 19:00:00',86638720,'2023-09-24 04:07:20',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(63923,140,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/23/Caribbean Anthology - September 23, 2023 at 16:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-23 16:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-07 13:10:32',NULL,'The crew discusses the future of the show, which will be held in February and May, and then again in August and September. They\'ll also host a spotlight in the fall and a spotlight during the summer. The crew also thanks the audience once again for showing up to the show at Ross City Studios last Saturday. They also discuss their recent experience at the River Fest, which they attended with a bunch of other artists. They had a great time, though, and are psyched to be back for another one.',NULL,NULL),(63924,141,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/23/Alternativa Latinoamericana - September 23, 2023 at 18:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-23 18:00:00',86507648,'2023-09-24 04:07:21',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(63925,143,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/23/Mach Vibe Radio - September 23, 2023 at 22:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-23 22:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-07 12:46:51',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(63926,143,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/23/Mach Vibe Radio - September 23, 2023 at 21:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-23 21:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-07 12:26:26',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(63927,1344,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/23/Beautiful Druid - September 23, 2023 at 09:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-23 09:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-07 12:13:00',NULL,'The show opens with the introduction of the host, Alden Hadwen, and the program\'s theme. It is about visits, and this song by the band Great Big C is a good example of this theme. The show then plays some songs that relate to visits, including Alison Krause\'s album Too Many, Leonard Cohen\'s \"Farewell to My Love,\" and Catherine McClellan\'s song \"Waiting on My Love.\" The show ends with an interview with the artist, Elisa Druidpee, who has just released her latest album, Inukitart.',NULL,NULL),(63937,1551,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/46n45d/sept21moovin_online-audio-convertercom_avwe3.mp3','2023-09-24 06:35:06',257281924,'2023-12-07 11:51:14',NULL,'This is the first episode of The Right Direction, a new music program hosted by David James. The program starts off with some interviews with David for the info lost. The loft is followed by The Tunnel, The Live Light, Paradise Garage, and the list continues on. David then introduces the program, which will be live from NYC.\n\nNew York has been a hotbed for dance music for the last 40 years. They also have a guest mix from Dirty Birth, a label based out of the U.S., and a whole guest mix for us to listen to. They have a few more tracks from the 2R T label that will drop later on. The guests are Alicia Keys, Demir, Benny Blanco, Brock Edwards, Carl Leo, Dragged Smoke, Nathan Barato, Takina, and more.\n\nThey\'ve also heard some new music from New York artists, including Renee Le Vise , Marcus Visionary , and Ed Solo . David closes the program by introducing Kree, a Juno nominee from Montreal. He has a new release coming out soon.',NULL,NULL),(63938,101,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/24/Seems Like Old Times - September 24, 2023 at 15:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-24 15:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-07 11:31:59',NULL,'The opening scene takes place in the dining room of the Wirths\' home, where Mrs. Margaret is busy setting up the family dinner table. She is delighted to see her son\'s mother coming for dinner, and tells Mrs. Norton that she misses her family.\n\nShe says that her husband had no family, and she had never seen them since. Mrs. . Norton tells her that someone in the family has been injured in a car accident, and asks Mrs. Marie to come get her. She will be waiting for her husband at the house, and he will be back in an hour.',NULL,NULL),(63939,101,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/24/Seems Like Old Times - September 24, 2023 at 14:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-24 14:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-07 11:16:01',NULL,'The program begins with a description of the program and the music that will be played in the program. The music will include a number of albums by famous artists of the time. The program will also feature a doctor who relates a story of a grandfather who is a member of a quadriplegic family from an accident.\n\nThe grandfather was afraid that he would die before his grandson grew up. The doctor wrote letters to the grandfather about life and other subjects and the program will start at 254 today because the program is so long. The guavewellington senior\'s association is holding a dance at the evergreen community center on Saturday night. If you are interested in dancing, call the recreation staff at 5 to 1 9 8 or 3 to 7 5 6 or 9. A doctor will be on the program who will explain that people over age lose mental acuity.\n\nThe answer is no, the doctor says. A psychiatrist and a psychologist have determined that certain parts of the brain are more active as we age. The psychologist says that experience allows our brains to grow. He says that if we age, our brains are not affected. A team of researchers are looking at the experiences of young and old adults during the 1918 influenza pandemic. The study is being conducted at the University of Ottawa.',NULL,NULL),(63940,144,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/24/The Underground - September 24, 2023 at 00:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-24 00:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-07 10:47:44',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(63941,144,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/23/The Underground - September 23, 2023 at 23:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-23 23:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-07 10:30:34',NULL,'The Kidney Walk is an annual event in which thousands of people from across Canada walk together to demonstrate their strength against kidney disease. Die Out is a community workshop that offers tools, equipment, and mentorship to anyone who wants to learn how to make things. If you\'re looking for a place to start, Die Out has moved to a new location and hosts weekly maker meetings.',NULL,NULL),(63942,145,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/24/Visions fugitives - September 24, 2023 at 09:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-24 09:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-07 10:12:05',NULL,'Fangwei recommends two new works for the upcoming week: a song cycle and a poem set to music. The first is a collection of poetry by Neruda, and the second is a song set to a poem by a Hungarian composer named Varens Farzash in celebration of his son\'s first birthday. The song cycle is called Fruit Basket and the poem collection is called First Birthday. Fangwei also recommends a piano concerto that he thinks might be a musical solidarity piece across national borders. It is called The Piano Concerto For Left Hand, and it was written for Paul Wittgenstein who lost an arm in World War One.',NULL,NULL),(63943,145,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/24/Visions fugitives - September 24, 2023 at 08:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-24 08:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-07 09:56:24',NULL,'The show is called \"Visual Fugitive\" and it\'s hosted by Christopher Curry, Fangwei and the two of them. It\'s a classical music program. Each week, one of them will choose one piece of music to respond to another co-host\'s selections from the previous week\'s show. Each piece will be a response to something that is already part of the show, and each week will have a special theme. For example, each week Fangwei will play an oratorio, and this week he\'ll play a piece about the onion.\n\nThis will be his response to the previous show, so he\'s going to choose a piece that is related to the onion theme. This week, he chooses a piece called \"United Fruit Company\" by Mikis Tevidorakis. This is an orgy of poems by the poet, Pablo Neruda, translated into English',NULL,NULL),(63944,146,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/24/The Kookoo Bananas Variety Hour - September 24, 2023 at 10:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-24 10:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-08 15:49:54',NULL,'The gang is back in the classroom, and this time, it\'s a little more kid-friendly. We\'re introduced to the two boys, who are now in grades 3 and 7 respectively. They\'re talking about science, which is something that\'s totally new to them, and they\'re also talking about numbers, which are super important to them. The boys decide to play a game called \"What\'s the ABC?\" and guess what the answer is. Jake guesses that there are two people, two eyeballs, two ears, three tongues, three lips, three apples, three legs, three fingers, and four eyes. The guys are super bad at this one, but they\'ve figured out that there\'s one letter in the alphabet, so they\'ll try to guess the answer to \"F-sharp\" .','The radio show is on the radio at 6:30pm ET on Today. Today\'s show will focus on arithmetic and the language of numbers. The show will also feature an alien live in the studio. The full show airs on Today at 8:30am ET.','\'An Alien Live in the Studio\' on Today (Newsletter)'),(63945,148,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/24/Clan Na Gael - September 24, 2023 at 13:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-24 13:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-07 09:11:59',NULL,'The program opens with the narration of the program, which was recorded in 1777. The program begins with a historical overview of the music that was being played on the station at the time.\n\nThe first song on the program is from a CD entitled Daddy Boy and Ballot. The second song is a song for Myra from a Celtic CD called Mcgillory. The third song is from Lee\'s band from a Scottish/American CD called Bring It All Back home. The fourth song is an Irish/American song from a folk CD called We Will Go America. The fifth song is one by Dolly Pardon from a Scots/Irish CD called O Tisiki, N\'Na l. The sixth song is by Tom and Conrad from a Friday Night Live CD called Shabbat\'s cruc.',NULL,NULL),(63946,148,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/24/Clan Na Gael - September 24, 2023 at 12:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-24 12:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-07 08:52:14',NULL,'In this program, John Fahy, a Newfoundland musician, plays a selection of songs from his CD collection. He talks about the Rugby World Cup in France, which is taking place in that country. He also talks about a Canadian musician named J. P. Cormier, who is also a musician. He plays a song for the Terry Fox, a man whom he believes to be the greatest Canadian he has ever known. He performs a song called \"I\'m Going To Be Miles,\" which is dedicated to Miles.',NULL,NULL),(63947,149,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/24/La Buena Onda - September 24, 2023 at 16:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-24 16:00:00',86507648,'2023-09-24 22:07:56',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(63952,174,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/pzuksk/September_20_2023_Glo