.\n\nThis week, the program is looking back at some of the artists that have been part of the music scene in the area. We start out with the Glint album by Nick Frazier, who played drums. The band is composed of Eric Chenot, Douglas T. Heller, Brody West, Rob Clutton, and all the people that have played in other bands and in other projects. They\'ve all played in Drum Heller, which is a band that Scott used to play in. They hear the track Knifex 63 from Drum Heller and it\'s about seven years since it came out. Ken Oldcroft, a friend of Scott\'s who played guitar in the Ken Old Croft Convergence Ensemble, passed away recently.\n\nScott was able to host Ken on this program several times, and enjoyed every time he played live. The program is going to hear music from the Tangent section of the album by Wes Neal. The Tangent section is comprised of Wes, Big Time, Felter, and a guy named Gord Gurdina who is also from Vancouver. The group is also comprised of Mark Halias, Jerry, and Gurdina. The album is called Recoder, and it features the guys from the Convergence Ensemble. They also have a track from Joe Sorberas album My Misshape And Ear.',NULL,NULL),(64156,1591,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/26/New or Never - September 26, 2023 at 19:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-26 19:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-06 06:46:18',NULL,'The show starts off with a bang as the host, Adrian Hodritik, introduces eleven new tracks. The first is Thirson\'s music, which he describes as a mixture of studio recordings, film soundtracks, and collaborations.\n\nThe band he\'s playing with is called the Chanters, and it\'s based in Vancouver, British Columbia. They\'ve got a new label called Slash Off, and they\'ve just released their second album. The other tracks on the show are by Montauban , Matthew Halsand , As Japans Girls , Patrick Creif , Low Cut Connie , and Run With the Kittens . The show ends with the newest release by Run With The Kittens.',NULL,NULL),(64166,217,'https://mcdn.podbean