ts with a description of the music, which consists of four tracks from Magna Vault\'s new album, Stellar Gun.\n\nThe first track is \"Shell Stellar Gun,\" followed by \"5 AM,\" \"Deckhead,\" and \"Bullet Hell or Bullet.\" The second track is called \"I Am The Night,\" and it\'s a dark, dark, scary track. The third track is a \"classic perturbator,\" which is a joke about the fact that \"I am the night.\" The fourth track is the last track of the show, and it will be all you can hear from the band until next week.',NULL,NULL),(64179,109,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/27/Radia - September 27, 2023 at 00:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-27 00:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-06 04:03:50',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(64217,78,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/27/Morning Soul Shake-Up! - September 27, 2023 at 08:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-27 08:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-06 03:06:44',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(64218,80,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/27/CFRU Playlist - September 27, 2023 at 07:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-27 07:00:00',86507648,'2023-09-27 14:06:27',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(64220,159,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/g3rj36/CAREER_-_CareerBuzzCIUTfinalseptember2720236tj5u.mp3','2023-09-27 15:30:00',86370275,'2023-12-06 02:50:22',NULL,'In this episode, Maria shares her story of how she got into non-profit management. She started out as a sales associate in an art gallery and then went on to open her own art-consulting business.\n\nAfter discovering that she loved helping others, she made a career shift to helping non-profits raise money. Her first job was as the giving manager at a non-for-profit called the Children\'s Hospital. She then moved on to the assistant director position at a domestic violence shelter called the Reach Beyond Violence. Her last job was the director of development for the local chapter of the Domestic Violence Resource Center.',NULL,NULL),(64222,174,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/umvti9/September_27_2023_Global_Rhythmsbtnlg.mp3','2023-09-27 14:54:42',431961989,'2023-12-06 02:29:49',NULL,'The first hour of Ken Stowar\'s program is dedicated to the theme of \"Global Rhythms.\" Ken tells us that he\'s here to tell us about the music of the future. Every day, he hears his people fail. He hopes that someday, he\'ll be able to hear them all fail.',NULL,NULL),(64230,99,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/27/The Stillness & The Dancing - September 27, 2023 at 10:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-27 10:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-06 02:10:24',NULL,'The show starts off with a bunch of new music from Lost Tribe Sound, Glassbird, Skyphone, Tape Loop Orchestra, and more. Then we hear a little bit of music from Prairie Lines. This is one of his all-time favorites White Lab Recordings releases. The show is an eight-year anniversary show, and the show is all about music. He doesn\'t have the time to celebrate, but he does enjoy the music.\n\nThe tracks on the show are all from White Lab recordings. The album Eyes Down, Seaside Down is a favorite. The track Calm Landing is from another White Lab release, one of Caleb R. K. Williams\'s. Finally, there\'s a track from Eagle Stone Collective called Hindons. It seems like the band has been releasing a lot of music lately. The band has put out an insane amount of releases, but each one seems to have a different vibe.\n\nSo much good music in there. He hopes in some way he\'s been part of it. He\'s also got a little miniature of Lo-fi Melancholy on a track called Sweet Love that he put on tape. He hasn\'t heard from it in a while.',NULL,'Keep Hope Alive Music Festival takes place in Guelph from September 28 to October 1st'),(64231,99,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/27/The Stillness & The Dancing - September 27, 2023 at 09:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-27 09:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-06 01:07:00',NULL,'This is a very long and very emotional show, and the narrator is very weary. He tells us that he\'s doing a lot of traveling and is trying to wrap up all of his inner