mes to the day program the next Friday. Sarah comments that her day at the center was good. She also likes making the icing for the morning program and making the gingerbread for the afternoon program. Josh also says that he enjoyed making the cake for lunch. Sarah also says she enjoyed making icing for breakfast and making gingerbread for lunch the next day. Josh adds that he will be returning to work.',NULL,NULL),(64300,12585,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2020/08/10/CFRU Mobile Community Radio Show - August 10, 2020 at 13:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2020-08-10 13:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-05 12:27:30',NULL,'The gang gets back to the game, which is to say, they\'re playing board games. This time, it\'s a different game, but the same game.\n\nSo who\'s here today? It turns out that it was Nora, Adam, Holland, Talya, and Shelly. Sarah\'s off swimming with her mom, and she\'s going to play some board games with the gang. Sarah tells us that the last time she was at the park, she played a Harry Potter board game. But this time, she\'ll play a different board game, so it\'ll be Snakes and Nerves, Story and Trouble, and maybe a game called Operation. Okay, so what are your favorite board games? They\'re all different, but they all have the same thing in common: they\'ve got to play the same board game for a bunch of different reasons. One of them is that the game on her iPad is dying, so she needs to get a new one. She also tells us she likes to listen to music on her tablet, but she doesn\'t know which one.\n\nThen she asks if she can join in on the game. She\'ll kill the guy if he says anything. But she also asks if he\'s there when she gets back. And then she asks when he got back from the show.',NULL,NULL),(64301,12585,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2020/08/03/CFRU Mobile Community Radio Show - August 3, 2020 at 13:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2020-08-03 13:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-05 12:11:49',NULL,'On this episode, the Host returns to the Community of Hearts, where he is teac