estroyed people, and I, never, would be, one forever, to hurt something.\" The guy playing music is Omar Bigenough, who plays a Latin song called \"Deep Dance for a Jazz Soul.\" He also plays a song called, \"Rock.\" He has a cold, and wants to go get some rest.',NULL,NULL),(64668,189,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/s6durd/kellycrypt.mp3','2023-10-01 17:15:00',287451427,'2023-12-04 03:06:50',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(64669,206,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/fg7yt4/September_30th_2023_The_Minx_Sessions9tsb7.mp3','2023-10-01 15:34:46',287962512,'2023-12-04 02:49:17',NULL,'This episode opens with a warm welcome to the listeners of CIUT 89.1 and the show\'s host, Bongenig. He introduces the show as a special edition of Minx Sessions. He explains that he\'s been playing a lot of the new releases from an artist named Hanoi who\'s releasing his third album.\n\nHe\'s also been playing some of his other releases too, which are also on a modular label. The first track of the show is a track from the new album, called Scrambled Anthem, and it\'s a very, very good sounding track. The second track is a little bit different, called Soft Walls. It\'s the title track of another upcoming record by Philip Shmoop. The third track is another from Soft Walls, this time called Scramble Anthem. The fourth track is more of a synth-pop track, and the fifth track is the title of a new record by another artist named Shigori Rota.\n\nThe last track is from another forthcoming record, called Land of Plenty. It features Apparat. The sixth track is also from another upcoming release, called Rough Bites. The seventh track is an encore of the first track. This time, it\'ll be a full-length record called Rough bites, Scrambled anthems.',NULL,NULL),(64670,292,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/a7659n/September_29_2023_The_Cool_Side_of_the_Pillow7j6dh.mp3','2023-10-01 18:50:52',287962512,'2023-12-04 02:24:25',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(64671,101,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/01/Seems Like Old Times - O