t 46. This was a guy who used to play for a band named He',NULL,NULL),(65181,173,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/fxys6q/Club_Ned_Oct_8_2023_podcastbulwh.mp3','2023-10-06 11:11:23',530406921,'2023-12-02 11:48:26',NULL,'The program opens with a thank you note from the listeners for their donations during the fall campaign. The program then moves to Scaville, where they are about to play some music. The music is pretty heavy, so they\'re hoping some people will show up to hear some of it. It\'s Thanksgiving, which is kind of a big deal for Canadian listeners.',NULL,NULL),(65199,78,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/06/Morning Soul Shake-Up! - October 6, 2023 at 08:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-06 08:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-02 11:31:23',NULL,'The \"morning soul shake-up\" is a program hosted by CFRU, a public broadcasting institution in Canada. The program airs on 90 CFRU-AM every weekday between 8am and 9am. The host starts by saying that he\'s a \"comin\'\" with the girl, and she\'s listening to the program.\n\nHe tells her to wake up and to be quiet. He\'s going to find out what he can do with her. He says that he wants her to stop talking about her mother, and to stop playing with her baby. He calls her a baby, and tells her that she should get out of the house. He doesn\'t want to be a bad man, he says. He promises that if she tells her mother to leave the house, he\'ll let her stay. But if she wants to stay, she should put her mother in the house and stay there. She says that she tried her best, but she can\'t figure out who it is. She calls the doctor, and he says he has a lot of calls. The doctor says that if he finds out what\'s wrong, he will let the girl go. The girl says she\'ll go find it out.',NULL,NULL),(65204,167,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/w769xc/October_6th_2023_Funky_Fridaysbp8vd.mp3','2023-10-06 16:26:12',431961989,'2023-12-02 11:12:30',NULL,'Phil Upchurch, a Chicago jazz funk player, leads the way with a trio of songs. The first song is 