ople gotta move, triumph, never surrender.\" The show ends with \"Master versus apprentice,\" which seems to be a play on the word \"master\" in Greek mythology. \"Master',NULL,NULL),(65217,1437,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/06/Democracy Now - October 6, 2023 at 11:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-06 11:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-02 09:28:18',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(65218,3686,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/06/Volunteer Playlist - October 6, 2023 at 12:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-06 12:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-02 09:05:58',NULL,'On October 26, O-Perk will host a Producer\'s Night at the Hefner Studios at the Kitchener Public Library. The purpose of the evening is to introduce women, nonbinary, trans and gender expansive persons to the world of music production and recording. O-Perek will be joined by local musician, Shannon Lee, who will teach the basics of live sound. The event is free and open to all.',NULL,NULL),(65228,195,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/dc6gue/Dementia13RadioShow_23_10_03.mp3','2023-10-06 19:57:43',173991544,'2023-12-02 08:48:40',NULL,'The narrator starts this program by talking about how he\'s digging into his collection of music to find some of the stuff he hasn\'t heard before.\n\nHe starts with a song called \"Upon the Earth\" from a band called Manmade from Montreal in 1970. It turns into a band that\'s called Keep On Moving from another band called Jerry Mercer. Then Sarah Brum from Spain. Then Arthur Gee from Canada. Then another song called Plain Talk from a group called Arthur Gee. And then another song from Dr. Strange from Dublin. And finally, a song from the wimple with marmalade hair from the British psych band Spirits & Worms. Sounds like the group tanked after the band was pulled from an A&M store because they had a goat on the cover of their record.\n\nThe narrator hates when people treat animals badly. Then there\'s a song by a Canadian band called Cat from 1970. It\'s \"The Whole World Watching\" from \"A New Kind 