ermany. The show is going to go live on Mixcloud and on the Canadian International University\'s website under the name Ruby SlippersRadio.com.',NULL,NULL),(65243,127,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/06/LiYghTE FM - October 6, 2023 at 16:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-06 16:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-02 06:51:47',NULL,'On this edition of \"An informed society\", the host of a local CFRU 92.3/Liyhte FM station, DJ Double D, is joined by a panel of guests. The first speaker is a conservative political scientist named Jim Ross. The second speaker is an independent thinker named Craig Roberts. The third speaker is another political scientist, Jim Hall. The fourth speaker is the author of the new book \"The Shock Doctrine.\" The last speaker is Jim Hall, who gives a speech on the \"moral foundation\" of political leaders. He says that it is important to understand the moral foundation of a politician, as it will help us make more informed political decisions.',NULL,NULL),(65244,1620,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/06/Hellfire Radio - October 6, 2023 at 15:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-06 15:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-02 06:30:13',NULL,'The band announces that they\'re back, and they\'ve got a new song from France. They\'re psyched to have it from a band called Gros Soleil.\n\nThe band\'s not sure what to make of the first song, but the second one is even better. The first song is super good, and the second song is better than the first. The guys are psyched to hear more music from Canada. They also get a new track from Saxon, a.k.a. Sanji. This guy is a heavy metal chef. He\'s also a big fan of \"God rhythm Doom 23\" , which the band played on the previous show. He also plays a lot of metal albums, so he\'s very familiar with this band. They play a new metal track called \"Tris Tris Kelly\" . This is Canadian melodic metal. They have some new stuff coming up, too.',NULL,NULL),(65254,128,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/06/Walkuman Style - October 6, 2023 at 18:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-06 18:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-02 06:12:31',NULL,'Connex Ontario\'s mental health helpline is at 1-866-531-2626 to speak with a specialist. It\'s also available via the mentalhealthline.ca to chat with a mental health specialist or to send an anonymous message. Mac D is a local musician who works at the University of Guelph\'s community radio station.\n\nHe\'s been hanging around the university for a long time because he\'s had a blast. He started out working the equipment and producing shows, and then moved on to doing his own show. He still loves what he does. If you\'d like to learn more about what\'s going on at the university, Mac D invites you to visit the university\'s second floor and check out what the university has to offer.\n\nHe also tells you about the War-Amms, a charity that provides artificial limbs to people who have lost their limbs due to war. He tells you that the war-',NULL,NULL),(65255,135,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/06/Folk Roots Radio - October 6, 2023 at 17:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-06 17:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-02 05:09:24',NULL,'This week on the show, we hear from Paul Smith, Watt Macums, Amelia Baker, John McCuskers, Alison Russell, Peter Wan, and Kyle Weymouth. All of these artists have new music releases, and they want to thank the listeners for their support.\n\nSo they\'re starting this week by playing a song called \"Untanked Smith\" by Paul Smith. We also hear a song by Amelia Baker called \"Cinderwell\" and a song from John McCustker called \"Sprig of Time\" which features Island singer Heidi Talbot on the vocals. Then we hear \"All Woman Supported Solo\" by Annie and \"Co-It\" by Kyle Weymouth, which is a song about love and belonging. Next up is Peter Wan\'s song \"Birds Go Die out of Sight Go Home\" from his upcoming album.',NULL,NULL),(65265,129,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/06/Digital Statik - October 6, 2023 at 19:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-06 19:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-02 04:44:30',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(65266,3686,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/06/Volunteer Playlist - October 6, 2023 at 20:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-06 20:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-02 04:26:40',NULL,'In this program, we learn about the work of Community Food, a non-profit that takes high- quality produce and transforms it into delicious take-home meals for the wealthy. The meals are offered for free or for donation, and they help to divert raw ingredients and excess food from fields and farms and onto dinner table of families throughout the community. We also learn about Ritesh Das\'s new album, which is now available on all the major streaming services. He will perform at the Al Green Theatre on November 4. Also, there is a new edition of the Selector on the way, and if you\'d like to hear it, you can find it on the Soundcloud page.',NULL,NULL),(65276,216,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/vj5c9t/RAW100623.mp3','2023-10-07 02:08:43',287962512,'2023-12-02 04:08:46',NULL,'The narrator and his fellow contributors thank everyone who gave during the fall campaign. If you hadn\'t already, they still need your support to reach their goal of $100,000 and donate now at ciut.\n\nfm. The narrator introduces us to some of the artists who will be performing at the upcoming Nerds! festival, which is being held in Little Jamaica. He also introduces the audience to the Cultural Hotspot, which has free events for all ages in the city until the end. RiteshThas from Juno-nominated hip-hop artist Tabla is releasing his new album on streaming services. He will perform live at the Al Green Theatre on November 4.',NULL,NULL),(65277,132,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/06/Global Rare Grooves - October 6, 2023 at 21:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-06 21:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-02 03:46:36',NULL,'The show starts off with a song called Ain\'t no Sunshine by the Caribbean Kings. It\'ll be a cover of a classic song by Sly Stone. Then they hear another Canadian song called Snakeskin Garther from Manfred Mann. And then they hear a Canadian classic called Chocolate Candy. And finally we hear a track called Harvest Time off the Faroe Sanders album on Indian Navigation. It is recently reissued. So thanks again for listening and enjoying your Friday night.',NULL,NULL),(65278,1491,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/06/Industry Tactics - October 6, 2023 at 22:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-06 22:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-02 01:07:59',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(65288,1491,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/06/Industry Tactics - October 6, 2023 at 23:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-06 23:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-02 00:50:35',NULL,'The narrator asks the young artist about his approach to practice and discipline. He explains that he is more interested in the technical aspect of music than in the \"realness\" of the music. He is also interested in \"the commitment and sincerity of friendship and community\" as they are more important to him than the \"technical ability to realize\" .\n\nThe narrator explains that if he is playing music, he is not thinking about anything but playing music. If he is thinking about something, he will act on it. The music flows through him, and he is \"not really there\" when he plays, but he does know that people talk about it. He says that it is like the music \"flows through\" him.',NULL,NULL),(65289,1627,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/07/Jitterbuggin - October 7, 2023 at 00:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-07 00:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-02 00:32:12',NULL,'The host of Jitter-Bugging, Adrian Jaye is a new student at the university and he\'s coming to town to present his show. He\'s going to be in his basement for the next two weeks so he doesn\'t have to be on stage all the time.\n\nHe tells listeners that his show is a dance craze from the 40s to the early 50s. He plays soul, gospel, and original rock and roll music. He also plays some \"Bumblegrind\" stuff, which is a dirty term for anything that\'s made up of women. The music on this show is mostly from the 50\'s and 60\'s, but there are some songs from the 2000s and some from the 80s. If you\'re on the station and want to know more about the show, he\'ll give you a link to his website.',NULL,NULL),(65327,219,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/uvt9p9/ES231004.mp3','2023-10-07 14:03:33',138120969,'2023-10-29 06:09:54',NULL,'James Bailey: The music was by Toru Takamitsu, a Japanese composer. Christina Petroska-Kuliko has been honored with the 2023 Oscar Moravitz Award for Excellence in Music Performance. Micheline Coulombe-San-Marqueux is normally known as an electroacoustic composer.',NULL,'James Bailey: The music was by Toru Takamitsu, a Japanese composer'),(65332,187,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/7kr2d5/Dreaming_in_Stereo_-_October_6_2023_29djym.mp3','2023-10-07 15:45:53',110896202,'2023-12-02 00:09:02',NULL,'This program is a thank you note from the community station to all the listeners who have supported them during their fall campaign. The station is still in need of funds to reach its goal of $100,000, so please donate now. Alexandra, the station\'s program director, welcomes listeners to the program. She tells them that there are a lot of exciting announcements coming up, including a new group called U-komblond that is coming to town on October 11, and a new track by Hannah Georges called \"Dead Man and Post Data\" that will be coming out in the next week.',NULL,NULL),(65334,187,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/pxdr87/Dreaming_in_Stereo_-_Sept_29_28zjpz.mp3','2023-10-07 15:45:01',108124235,'2023-12-01 21:08:16',NULL,'The program starts off with a bang as Alexandra introduces herself to the listeners. She tells them that she\'s here until 7pm and they\'ve just heard a new track off of Arkells\' latest album called Laundry Pile. She also tells them to check out the program\'s playlist, which will be up shortly. Alexandra also introduces us to the next track, a new one from the Islands.\n\nThis one is called And ThatsWhyDolphinsLostTheirLegs. The band was on tour this week and they just released a new song called AndThatsWhy. They\'re on tour at the moment. Alexandra then introduces the rest of the program, which includes new music from Port Air Squirrel, Soccer Mommy, Aviv, Dragonette, and Post Data.',NULL,NULL),(65339,136,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/07/A Dog’s Breakfast - October 7, 2023 at 10:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-07 10:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-01 19:18:20',NULL,'It is a free, a free. It is free, free. Free, free-free. Free. Free-free-free, free, Free. free- free. free.free. free,free.free,free, Free, Free- free, FREE, free free, . free free. .Free, free .free . Free ..free free, the free of free. The free of the free is free. There is no free, there is no freedom, there can be no free. Everyone has the right to free.',NULL,NULL),(65340,1344,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/07/Beautiful Druid - October 7, 2023 at 09:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-07 09:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-01 18:47:19',NULL,'The first song to be played is by Eva Cassidy, who sings about the beauty of autumn. The second song is by Jesse Winchester, who is staying with a friend in New England, and the third is by Feist, who\'s singing about the birds. The fourth song is from Greg Brown, who has a song about preserving preserves. The fifth is from the Eastside Groove, who have a song called \"Fermented,\" which is about pickles. The sixth song is about Robert Frost, who wrote \"Where Are We?\" The seventh is from Joshua Redmond, who played the horn on his new album. The eighth song is called \"Fleas Stars on Alabama,\" which means \"Where are we?\"',NULL,NULL),(65350,14544,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/07/National Day for Truth and Reconciliation - October 7, 2023 at 12:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-07 12:00:00',86507648,'2023-10-07 18:08:06',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(65351,14544,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/07/National Day for Truth and Reconciliation -