e Box.\" The tour is over, and now we can hear about all the other artists on the tour. So, if you\'re a fan of music, check out this tour.',NULL,NULL),(65585,80,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/10/CFRU Playlist - October 10, 2023 at 06:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-10 06:00:00',86507648,'2023-10-10 12:06:29',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(65595,78,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/10/Morning Soul Shake-Up! - October 10, 2023 at 08:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-10 08:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-01 02:28:39',NULL,'On the 10th anniversary of the annual Guelph Comedy Festival, there\'s a lot of fun stuff for the whole family to enjoy. One of the fun things they\'re doing is putting on a clown show with Isaac Kessler and Ken Hall. The festival also has a ton of other events to look forward to, including a live reading of a Native American novel, a public screening of a First Nations film, and more.',NULL,NULL),(65605,280,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/hnfiug/Scotland_-_Tracks_From_Abroad_Ep_8377zcl.mp3','2023-10-10 15:28:15',84106400,'2023-11-30 23:13:05',NULL,'Seth Martosh is a student at the University of Toronto who is studying Middle Eastern music with Megan Traxell. Before the show, Seth tells us that he\'s thankful for living in Canada, where he can express his opinions and values.\n\nHe also says that Canada has a good relationship with the United States, which is good. Seth says that they\'re also going to hear a lot of Scottish music, as well. Seth also says they\'ll hear some Canadian music that\'s Scottish in nature. At the end, Seth says, you can hear Donovan\'s song, \"Herdy Gertie man,\" which he thinks is a really good song. Seth is from Glasgow, Scotland, and he says that he has lived in Scotland his whole life.',NULL,NULL),(65606,2653,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/10/Solipsistic Retreat - October 10, 2023 at 10:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-10 10:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-30 22:46:34',NULL,'This week\'s program is all about the Negative Approach. It\'s about how Paul and John are actually the same person. Paul thanks John for helping him find a cop, and John thanks Paul for helping with the music. They\'re both really into the music and the music is really good.',NULL,NULL),(65607,2653,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/10/Solipsistic Retreat - October 10, 2023 at 09:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-10 09:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-30 22:27:25',NULL,'The band begins by answering the question, \"What is the killing-joke?\" The first question is, \"Is it a comic?\" The second question is \"Is It an album from Batman?\" The third question is whether it is a 1980s album by the band \"The Killing Joke\" or a 2003 album by \"The Laughing Dudes.\n\n\" The band explains that they are not talking about the music, but about the people. The people matter. The band is about to go on a trip and they are about to hear a song from the band. They want to preface the song by saying that before they do anything, they need to hear the song. The first song is called \"Adolphes from a brighter sun\" and the second song is \"Disco Freaking Song.\" The song is about a band called \"The Ball-Bearers.\" They need to remember that it is October, it is Halloween, it\'s Thanksgiving, and it is fall. The song \"Phantom Pain\" is a beautiful song and the band is sorry that it reminded them of God. The cover of the song is a cover of a white rabbit, and they notice that the song changes the song\'s title',NULL,NULL),(65617,90,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/10/Bridging The Social Distance - October 10, 2023 at 12:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-10 12:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-30 22:08:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(65618,1437,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/10/Democracy Now - October 10, 2023 at 11:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-10 11:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-30 21:12:31',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(65623,155,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/tkx9an/DrMouth_CIUTshow_oct10_2023_fullshow.mp3','2023-10-10 19:44:00',287244608,'2023-11-30 20