om the band Solar Sails, who recently played a show.',NULL,NULL),(65840,78,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/12/Morning Soul Shake-Up! - October 12, 2023 at 08:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-12 08:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-30 05:11:50',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(65841,110,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/12/Here Today - October 12, 2023 at 07:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-12 07:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-07 07:05:34',NULL,'The show opens with a new song from Hotel Myra, who have just released an album called I am Not Myself. The band has been around for years and have been called Hotel Myra since they formed in 2007. Hotel Myra is a little weird, though, because they don\'t really know what the hell they\'re called. They\'ve never really been called by their real name, so they\'ve decided to call themselves Hotel Myra. We hear from Will Butler of Sisters Squares, and from Cassie Noble, who has just released her debut album. The show also hears from Sufjan, who\'s releasing an album dedicated to his partner who died.',NULL,'Hotel Myra (Sponsor), a new song from the band I am Not Myself '),(65851,219,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/7k5vxv/ES231011.mp3','2023-10-12 15:26:05',139135565,'2023-10-29 06:04:03',NULL,'James Bailey: This is CIUT 89.5 FM. Here in Toronto, on the grounds of the University of Toronto. And we come here every Wednesday at 11pm to give you some strange and unusual sounds. And so we thank him for guiding us to where we are now.',NULL,'James Bailey: This is CIUT 89.5 FM. Here in Toronto, on the grounds of the University of Toronto'),(65852,111,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/12/Tales from the Bridge - October 12, 2023 at 09:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-12 09:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-30 04:52:20',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(65853,112,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/12/FoodFarm Talk - October 12, 2023 at 10:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-12 10:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-30 04:36:36',NULL,'On this episode of the Food Talk podcast, Jordan talks 