food or water to enter the territory until Hamas releases its prisoners. After running out of food, the only power station in the territory ran out of fuel.',NULL,NULL),(65875,205,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/dmfzw6/October_12th_2023_Music_At_High_Noonaxr3h.mp3','2023-10-12 19:17:34',226698478,'2023-11-30 02:07:57',NULL,'This week\'s program starts off with a tribute to Neil Perry, who was one of the fathers of the underground music scene. The program then switches to a selection of music from the week, starting with the song Envy of None by Arlo Hannigan. Then it\'s Electric Meat\'s \"Torrid\" and Steppenwolf\'s song \"It\'ll Never Too Late\" and then the band \"Friends of Mine\" and \"The Zombies\" playing at the Queen Elizabeth Theatre on October 17. As the program opens up, Tadros introduces the listeners to the music and then he announces the draw for tickets to the show. He also gives a shout-out to the band Frank Zappa.',NULL,NULL),(65876,113,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/12/Android’s Dungeon - October 12, 2023 at 13:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-12 13:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-30 01:53:21',NULL,'The first part of the show is devoted to the definition of a \"geek\" and how it\'s different from a \"nerd\" . The first definition is that of someone who finds their passion and decides to share that passion with others.\n\nThe second definition is for someone who becomes an evangelist for something they\'ve seen, heard, or read about. So, if you\'re a musician and you find out that Miles Davis is a big influence on you, you can talk to someone about it and they\'ll tell you about it, too. Now, if someone says they\'re going to a jazz conference and they decide to listen to all of this music, you\'ll be a nerd because it\'ll consume all of your time. The third definition is a person who becomes a nerd when their past becomes the center of their personality, and they can\'t relate to the people around them.\n\nSo we get the idea that people are all \"geeks\" and \"nergs\" in this particular case. The only difference is that the first definition says something like, \"I\'m a geeky person if I really like music and can talk about it\" while the second definition says, \"It consumes your life\" and you can just go listen to the music and not feel like you\'ve been a part of something. So that\'s the definition. The guys are now able to go to the bank and listen to their show and see if they',NULL,NULL),(65877,13307,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/12/Eclectic Selections - October 12, 2023 at 14:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-12 14:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-30 01:30:05',NULL,'The show begins with a cover mini-theme, this time featuring a jazz vocalist named Patricia Barber. She sings a song called \"She\'s A Lady,\" and we learn that she\'s a \"traitor with respect\" .\n\nWe also learn that the song was originally written by Paul \"Anka\" Anka, but it wasn\'t recorded by him, so it was recorded by his daughter Nora. The song is called \"At My Window Sad And Lonely\" , and it\'s one of the first songs ever recorded by Woody Guthrie. We learn that Nora took his songs to Billy \"Bragg\" and \"Wicker\" and had them recorded. Then they recorded the lyrics by \"Woody\" himself, but never recorded it. The lyrics were recorded by \"Billy Bragg and Wilco\" and it was called At My window Sad and Lonely . So definitely an interpretation of Woody Guthrie\'s music. We then hear \"Yola Tango,\" a song by Johnny Cash, who played a song for Dean Martin that was a big hit for him.\n\nWe hear \"Cassandra Wilson,\" an excellent cover of \"The Weight by the band,\" and finally \"Dylan It Takes a Train to Cry,\" a cover of Dylan\'s \"Subterranean Music\" translated into Spanish by Gecko Turner. We end the show with \"Two Genius collaborating right there,\" Brian Eno and \"David Byrne,\" who wrote the song \"The River\" from \"Everything That Happens Will',NULL,NULL),(65887,115,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/12/RadiOPIRG - O