-10-13 10:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-29 17:08:54',NULL,'The Funky Funky Blues Dr. describes his show, called \"Planet Groove of Your Funky Funky Funky Blues Doctor.\" He tells us that he\'s here to \"spread some jam on the burnt toast baby.\" He says he\'ll play some rare live Stones from 1973.\n\nHe\'ll also play some status-quo, Brave Belt, and the Cream from the \'80s. He says that Ginger Baker was one of his favorite drummers, and a polarizing figure. Ginger was a drummer who was known for pulling a knife on the Jack Bruce organization. He also had a nasty personality. Ginger had a reputation for being a bad drummer, and he recently passed away. He\'s going to play a Rock And Roll Band from the \"brave belt.\" He also plays as a Chris Robinson Brotherhood from the Blues Fest. The Brotherhood is a band that was a big hit at the BluesFest in Kitchener last year. It\'s a band with a \"funky cosmic throwback sound.\" They play Mercury Blues Baby from David Lindley, El Reyo, and El Reno X.\n\nThey play as a Rare Bird from Mercury Blues. They also play as Elliot and Audio Kings from the KW BluesFest. Elliot and the Kings are a lap-pedal steel player who was once on \"The Late Show with David Letterman.\" Elliot and his band will be playing a show at Royal City Studios on October 25th. Then they play a cover of \"Rilesnake\" from the 1970 Peter Green album.',NULL,NULL),(65939,1437,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/13/Democracy Now - October 13, 2023 at 11:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-13 11:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-29 16:48:34',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(65940,3686,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/13/Volunteer Playlist - October 13, 2023 at 12:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-13 12:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-29 16:24:53',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(65945,170,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/eaanaa/Ruby_Slippers_Oct_13_mp3_-_2023-10-09_151_PM610v4.mp3','2023-10-13 18:14:15',111378520,'2023-11-29 16:11:12',NULL,'The program opens with a shout-out to all the listeners who have bee