ineer, tells the listeners that he is a coffee specialist and that since the shop opened in 2015, it has become a kind of coffee shop. He explains that before coffee could be representative of someone else, it had to represent someone else.\n\nHe adds that he likes round-ins, where all learners learn to reverse. The second part of this show is an introduction to the festival, which takes place in Brighton every August. The show introduces the listeners to the area, and the engineer explains that he and his friends are going to stand in the house, which is in the middle of the festival grounds. He says that the area is about four sections, but that this one is even bigger. The festival grounds are separated from the main part by fencing, so that no one can get in. He also explains that if the festival continues on, the area will also be separated from it. He believes that all of Brighton is connected.',NULL,NULL),(66513,180,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/48kpfz/HOWL_OCTOBER_17_202373qkf.mp3','2023-10-18 10:57:47',56737460,'2023-11-28 03:13:49',NULL,'This show is all about poetry. This is a lively conversation between two poets, Lynn Tate and John Lennon. The first half of the show is devoted to discussing Tate\'s \"You Break It\" and the second half to discussing \"You Buy It.\"',NULL,NULL),(66528,80,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/18/CFRU Playlist - October 18, 2023 at 07:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-18 07:00:00',86507648,'2023-10-18 14:06:28',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(66529,78,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/18/Morning Soul Shake-Up! - October 18, 2023 at 08:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-18 08:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-27 23:05:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(66534,174,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/7hpevg/October_18_2023_Global_Rhythms7x0pk.mp3','2023-10-18 14:35:01',431961989,'2023-11-27 22:50:37',NULL,'On this edition of the program, Ken Stauer, host and producer of the show, introduces the music and tells listeners about the artists featured on the prog