ong is from Nick\'s band, which is playing some new material. The first song is a new song from a band called Tomb Mold, who have just released their new album, The Enduring Spirit, and are also playing some brand new music. The next band is called Baffled-Brains, who were once a band known as the Brains. They have released a new record and are currently based in Vancouver. The band is releasing a new album called F Off 2020 on the 25th of this month, and the first song they\'re going to play is a song called Stoned',NULL,NULL),(66696,122,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/20/Forever Deaf - October 20, 2023 at 01:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-20 01:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-26 13:28:18',NULL,'The host returns to his regular Thursday night gig at the host\'s house. The show opens with a long monologue about how the world is full of different artists and how they all deserve to be heard. He mentions several of his own tracks, but particularly his new one, called \"Agony Sleeping Storm,\" which he describes as \"the greatest thing that you asked.\" He also mentions that he has found someone who will be going to his first \"Fragment Concert\" next week, and he\'s psyched to see him.',NULL,NULL),(66725,78,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/20/Morning Soul Shake-Up! - October 20, 2023 at 08:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-20 08:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-26 13:09:45',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(66735,123,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/20/Thanks for Listening :) - October 20, 2023 at 09:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-20 09:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-26 12:52:29',NULL,'The show opens with a description of the music on the program. It\'s all from the 1990s and 2000s. The first song that comes to mind is a song called \"I Cant Swim There\" from Johnny Flynn\'s and Robert McFarlane\'s \"Lost in the Cedar Wood\" album.\n\nThe narrator guesses what year it was released. He also guesses that it came out in 2019. The next song he guesses is \"Terza with Promise\" from Land of Taught\'s Terza album. He says that he\'s going to play more music in the next hour and a half. He starts off the show off with \"Claming Night Partner\" by Land of taught. Then, he goes back to the 2000s with \"Taken With You\" by Renan Isaac. He\'s got a lot of guesses to make.\n\nHe guesses that the first one was released in the late 1990s. Then he goes on to play \"Generation Steam\" by Bilesister, \"Sirens\" by Devandra \"Banhart\", and \"Flying Wig\" by Kate \"Laban\" Tempo. The show is nearing the end of its time. Andrew Whiteman is going to sign off.',NULL,NULL),(66736,124,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/20/Planet Groove - October 20, 2023 at 10:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-20 10:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-26 12:28:51',NULL,'The host starts off the show by introducing us to the various acts he\'s been able to bring to the stage. He introduces us to Chrissy Hines, Pat Benatar, Mall Crimes, and then introduces the Blue Nova Band. He also introduces the other acts on the list, including Linda Ronstadt, Nicolette, and The Nobodies, and a guy named Gary Clark, Jr. We learn that these acts are all going to be totally different from the rest of the acts in the show.',NULL,NULL),(66741,167,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/pvxba4/October_20th_2023_Funky_Fridaysa5qji.mp3','2023-10-20 17:00:07',431961989,'2023-11-22 01:11:16',NULL,'The Funky Fridays crew starts off with a song about racial inequality, which they call \"Black Shoes.\" Next up is a cover of \"The Beatles,\" a song by singer and songwriter Keisha \"Wint\" Wint. The group also plays an album by jazz musician Ramsey Lewis, who put out several albums during the period. The band will also play an hour-long set by Charles Stepney, an arranger, conductor, and composer. Next up are \"Lost Soul Behind Bars,\" a group of musicians who used to be in prison, and \"The Ironsides,\" a band that put out a new album. The next song is \"The Days of Sand,\" an instrumental track.',NULL,NULL),(66742,182,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/qqaemp/Oct_18_2023bcrp1.mp3','2023-10-20 16:41:39',145130056,'2023-11-22 00:46:46',NULL,'This week, the host of No Beat Radio, Manesh, introduces his guests. He starts off by introducing Felix, a Cuban electronic artist who runs a label, and also a curator.\n\nHe invites listeners to listen to a preview of the week\'s music. The show begins with a song by Felix, who is the founder of a record label, called Gagarin. He will be followed by new tracks by Jane B. , Petra Den, and Josh Cole. He also introduces some of his favorite artists. He announces that he will be playing a series of shows this week. The first show will feature Anadol, a Turkish artist. He\'ll also be playing with Gilliband, Iver, and Model Actress. The second show will be a mix of music and dance. He says he\'ll start with Turkish artist Anadol. Then he\'s going to play with the GilliBand. The third show will have a different genre of music. Manesh says he will play a track by Iver. The next show will also have a new track by the Model Actress, and the fourth will have some music by Anadol\'s band. The fifth show will introduce some new artists. Manhes',NULL,NULL),(66746,186,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/mh56hn/October_19th_2023_Higher_Groundamgnc.mp3','2023-10-20 16:57:33',287962512,'2023-11-22 00:30:11',NULL,'The second hour of this program is set aside for music. It will be a mix of new music and old favorites. The music starts off with a song called \"Sunset Dreams\" by Jo Alto, followed by an album called \"Bad With Names\" by Rob Alto. Rob Alto tells the crowd that he is on the way to the club and asks the audience if they are ready to show. He repeats the song \"Great Rudolf Eiseley\" and then asks if they want to hear a Justin Bieber song. He then plays one more song and then goes off to pick up some records from the club.',NULL,NULL),(66749,257,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/yf2jer/October_19_2023_Psychedelic_Stoner_Rock77o13.mp3','2023-10-20 17:40:46',287962512,'20