2023 at 20:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-23 20:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-23 03:06:54',NULL,'Blues Around the block is back and this time it\'s hosted by David Gogo. He gives us a shout-out to the band that\'s been playing in the background, the Yawn-Spear-Band. The Yawn Spear-Band is the band playing the blues.',NULL,NULL),(67138,84,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/23/Blues Around the Block - October 23, 2023 at 19:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-23 19:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-23 06:06:29',NULL,'Mac Dee is a new guy on the block. He\'s got his own little show called \"Blues Around the Block\" and he\'s a musician. He starts off by thanking everyone for tuning in. He also gives a little rundown of what\'s been going on with the show.',NULL,NULL),(67139,82,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/23/Big Sis Radio - October 23, 2023 at 17:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-23 17:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-23 02:30:23',NULL,'The crew is excited to kick off their show with some new music from Winnipeg. This time it\'s from a band called The Drums, who\'s got a new track called \"Comedy by Sasha Kaye\" for the show.\n\nThen they hear two tracks from Johnny, the latest from the drums. The first track on Johnny is \"I\'m still scared and i select\" and the second track is \"Inhospitable\" and \"So are we\" from Mitzki. The third track is called \"I can\'t find anyone by ecstasy\" and they also hear two songs off the drums latest record, \"I am Still Scared and i Select\". The crew also hears a song from Hemlock called \"Carriage\" and a song called \"A Little History\" from the band Holorado, who released their first album in a bag and came out with a track called Juliet that reached gold status.\n\nThis is a big deal because the band was the first band to play a concert in a vinyl format and it was a big hit. So the crew went to a store called Elsie\'s to get two copies of Juliet. And then Meno, the lead singer of Holorado came in to chat with the crew. He',NULL,NULL),(67149,86,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/23/The Deep House Project - October 23, 2023 at 22:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-23 22:00:00',86507648,'2023-10-31 05:10:19',NULL,'In this episode of the Deep House project, host Scott Brown and his crew set out to raise money for Silence Sounds, a local organization dedicated to preserving the arts in the community. They invite listeners to pledge $10 a month to the organization for a year. Scott introduces them to the program, which runs every Tuesday at 8pm on the CFRU 93.3 FM station. The program begins with a dance track by a German artist named Levenmankind. The song begins by saying, \"It\'s not about you, and me, so hold on, wait for a day /To feel out where its gonna be.\" The song goes on to say, \"The luck is with Me, the world still stops hidden, I still breathe there\'s something to your eyes / Oh no I know it\'s for so long.\" The artist then says, \"I\'ve got to get you up and move on.\" He tells the listeners that he has a crush on them and he wants to show them how much he wants them to love him. The music starts off with a remix of Milk & Bones\' \"P-Back\" by Blue Hawaii, and then the band Moose and The Scarf comes out with their song \"Won\'t',NULL,'Deep House project host Scott Brown pledges $10 a month to Silence Sounds, a local arts organization'),(67150,85,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/23/Ripcord Radio - October 23, 2023 at 21:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-23 21:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-23 02:10:27',NULL,'The show starts off with a bunch of music from the past. It\'s mostly from bands that once played in the same city. The first song is from a band called MFD, who played in Washington, DC in the late \'80s. Next, it\'s from the band Government Issue, who disbanded in 1989.\n\nThe band\'s last song was \"I See Your Face On Rainy Days\" from their 2006 album. The band also released an EP called Storm in the fall of last year. The EP was produced by Tom Lyle, who was a member of Government Issue