ing out of shoes.',NULL,NULL),(67730,163,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/w7b3rc/CriticsCircle_28102023bjm77.mp3','2023-10-28 14:01:43',NULL,'2023-11-17 23:20:44',NULL,'The show begins with Phil Taylor, the host of the Cairns Critics Circle, introducing a special guest: Eric Wolf, an actor, playwright and artistic director of the Eldridge Theatre, a magician, and theater administrator and coordinator of the Red Sandscastle Theatre. Wolf is currently in his play, \"Doc-Wuther-Glooms-Here-There-Be-Monsters,\" which he calls \"a cautionary tale of \'monsters\' with \'magic, mayhem, and ghoulish tendencies\'.\" Wolf describes the play as a \"tale of monsters with \'weird tendencies\'\" and says that he loved it.\n\nHe explains that his first show was a one-man show, \"The Strange and Eeerie Memoirs\" about Billy-Werther-Gulliver, which was a \"supernatural\" play about puberty. At the time, Rod Beattie was a well-known playwright in the area and he was a good actor, so he wanted to do his own play. He had no idea about puppetry, and so he built all of the characters out of them. In the audience feedback, he found that the puppet enhanced the horror of the play, making it \"a horror play in ways he hadn\'t intended.\"',NULL,NULL),(67745,136,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/28/A Dog’s Breakfast - October 28, 2023 at 10:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-28 10:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-17 23:10:37',NULL,'The listeners are introduced to a new artist named Marianne Trudel, who is best known for her work with the likes of Rezonon, John Hollenbaugh, and Hot Chip. The group then moves on to two other artists who recently played at a festival in the city of Guelph: Ajay Bomsenwan, who played from his \"fractions and blood,\" and Hafez Modushtein, who came in as an \"absentee\" from the badada. The program ends with a visit to Oliver Schroer, who had recorded street sounds from his pilgrimage through Spain. The show closes with a shout-out to everyone who has been a part of the 