rom the Los Angeles band Nice Blitz. The song comes from an EP called Not Lockdown. The first song we hear is from an album called All Serious Seriousness Aside. The second song is about a fictional murderer. The third song is a',NULL,NULL),(68009,86,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/30/The Deep House Project - October 30, 2023 at 22:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-30 22:00:00',86638720,'2023-10-31 04:56:55',NULL,'The show kicks off with a music selection from the 90s. It\'s called Future Shock and it\'s a horror movie set in a virtual reality world. It also has a book and a short movie about how people get stressed and paralyzed by too much change. The music is all about going back and forth in time. Way back, way back. Way way back, Way back! Way back... Way back. The group then goes back in time to listen to a song called Spooky Cowboy, which sounds very much like a mass-produced costume. The song basically says, \"I\'m not a cowboy, I\'ve got a plan. I\'ll never be wrong.\"',NULL,'Future Shock is a horror movie set in a virtual reality world. Way back, way back'),(68019,80,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/31/CFRU Playlist - October 31, 2023 at 06:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-31 06:00:00',86638720,'2023-10-31 14:06:18',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(68020,78,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/31/Morning Soul Shake-Up! - October 31, 2023 at 08:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-31 08:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-14 23:56:30',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(68021,87,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/30/Back in the USSR - October 30, 2023 at 23:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-30 23:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-14 22:49:56',NULL,'In this Dispatches, the human rights journalist and author of the book, The Return of the Detainee, discusses Israel\'s recent war in the Gaza Strip with journalist and documentary maker, Abi Martin. She also discusses her latest work, which is called \"Gaza Frights For Freedom,\" which was released four years ago and continues to be an important part of