week they can respond to the first piece they heard with their own selections. The show is sort of like a game of Who\'s Who in the music world. The two of them pick a song cycle and then they play the song that they heard the week before. The song cycle is called \"United Fruit Company.\" It was written by a Greek composer named Mikis Teodolians. It was one of many pieces written by Neruda that were set to music during the period of military rule in Greece from 1967 to 1974.',NULL,NULL),(68657,146,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/05/The Kookoo Bananas Variety Hour - November 5, 2023 at 10:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-05 10:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-08 14:17:16',NULL,'We start off this new episode with a song about robots. It\'s called \"Computers! Robots have Computers inside them basically two different things though.\" The first song is from Disney World. It was written by a group called the Sherman Brothers. They wrote songs for all the Disney theme parks. The song is called \"Everything Is Awesome\" and it\'s one of the most popular songs of all time. The second song that we\'re going to hear is a song by a guy called \"Jerry Paper\" . The guy\'s got a song called \"Fuzzy Logic\" , which is about being able to create something in the world that isn\'t just a yes or no. The world is like this. The cover of Jerry Paper\'s album is awesome. We\'ll start this song off with \"Lampan Fuzzy Logic,\" which sounds like a talking robot. It sounds like the voice of a German-speaking robot. Jerry Paper has a song for the kids called \"Jingles,\" which is also about a robot. The idea of a robot taking over the whole world is so awesome that it was actually the first song on the radio. It came from a game called \"Um Jamma Lamm','Rowan shares his favorite songs from Disney World, the Jungle Book, and a video game. Rowan also shares a song about how computers will take over the world. The song is called Fuzzy Logic and was written by the Sherman Brothers who also wrote