fortable space. The final track is a song from his old radio station in Buffalo, New York, that was so well received that it was one of the most played tracks on the station.',NULL,'The New York DJ Reveals His New Home in a New York City Show '),(68817,81,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/06/The Sentinel’s Marvellous Kaleidoscope - November 6, 2023 at 15:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-06 15:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-10 11:00:53',NULL,'The opening track of this week\'s Turo Island Sound Show is a mix of experimental music from around the world. It is a mixture of progressive fusion, alternative styles, and other discoveries. The narrator says he would like to pay respect to local indigenous communities and recognize that the music is heard across treaty territories. He also acknowledges that many of the music styles originated from Black culture, and he thanks the Black community for their contribution to alternative music. The first track of the week is a song by the singer-songwriter of the Czech Republic, Golden State. She has just released an album on Bandcamp. The second track is an electropop track by the artist from Vancouver, Her Head Is a House. The third track is a grime track by Beverly Glenn and his album Ones Ahead. The fourth track is by Helios Kenneth, an ambient project. The fifth track is one by Lawrence Ann from Montreal. The sixth track is called Vites, an experimental track on an album called Ornament Sea',NULL,'The Turo Island Sound Show: A mix of experimental music from around the world (11 minute read)'),(68827,83,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/06/to know the land - November 6, 2023 at 18:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-06 18:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-10 10:49:33',NULL,'The narrator says he grew up in the area of the Chesapeake Bay and the Appalachian Mountains. He describes the region as a \"middle zone\" where there are \"a lot of interesting geologically speaking, but also we sit in the middle zone\" . The narrator tells us that he