he various characters in the show and explains the concept of the blue eyes, which are the eyes of a man\'s face. This is a reference to the \"blue match\" in the English language that refers to the blue color of a person\'s eyes, as opposed to the yellow color of an English man\'S face. He also describes the show\'s theme, \"Christmas spirits,\" as a way of \"stirring all creatures.\"',NULL,'The Creepy Halloween Hootenanny Part 2 (Sponsor)'),(68932,1453,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/07/Silver Screen Dream Machine - November 7, 2023 at 15:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-07 15:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-10 01:33:55',NULL,'The show starts off with a musical comedy trio called The Arrogant worms from their 2002 concert film Three worms in an Orchestra. It\'s an orchestral version of \"The Last Saskatchewan Pirate,\" which is about a pirate captain who stole fertilizer from a ship in the Norwegian harbor. The song is a bit of a tongue-in-cheek take on life. The band also makes a surprise appearance in the animated film \"Hans Zimmer,\" which was released in the mid-1990s. On October 28 th , the world lost Matthew Perry who played the role of \"Chandler Bing\" on the long running sitcom Friends from 1994 until its end in 2004. He died suddenly in his tub. The show then turns to the 2000 crime comedy Oz Gets A Surprise, which stars Matthew Perry as Oz-Ozzina alongside Bruce Willis. The score is by Randy Edelman. Then we hear the opening credits of \"Almost Heroes,\" a 1998 film directed by Chris Farley and starring Matthew Perry and Chris Vanston as explorers in the 1800\'s. And then we hear a mix of the soundtrack to \"Friends,\" the sitcom which has made Matthew Perry famous. And finally, the show closes with a set of covers of four songs by Van Parks. The',NULL,'The Last Saskatchewan Pirate, The Arrogant Worms, and Matthew Perry\'s Death in a Tub '),(68933,3033,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/07/A Multilingual Affair - November 7, 2023 at 16:00 - CFRU 93