talks about how he was \"boy crazy\" when he turned 17 and how he learned to behave himself when he celebrated his birthday.',NULL,NULL),(69308,1437,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/14/Democracy Now - November 14, 2023 at 11:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-14 11:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-14 20:57:31','2023-11-14 19:07:22','The United Nations warns that the largest hospital in the Gaza Strip is in danger of becoming a cemetery. Anthony Lowenstein reports that Israel is exporting the technology of its occupation to the rest of the world.\n\nA London-based journalist, Ahmed Al-Nawba, has been forced to resign after signing a letter criticizing Israel, and another journalist, Jamie Kalis, has also been forced out of the New York Times after signing the same letter. The war grinds on. The UN says that no fuel will be allowed into the besieged territory by Wednesday. Meanwhile, the president of the United States, Joe Biden, has called on the Israeli military to stop its attacks on civilians. Biden\'s remarks came after doctors Without Borders reported that Israeli troops fired at medical teams and ambulances to the hospital. Others reported that they\'d also been hit by gunfire from drones. Israel says it has a command structure below the hospital but denies that it exists.',NULL,NULL),(69317,125,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/14/Power Up! with Electrified Voltage - November 14, 2023 at 14:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-14 14:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-16 08:26:24','2023-11-14 21:07:20','This week on the Power Up program, the listeners are treated to some of the best music from Canada, Australia, the Philippines, Norway, and the U.S. We start off by hearing a song from Chester, then we hear a song called \"Fire\" from the Australian band Wild Ride, then a song by Celia Carlson, then from the Norwegians we hear \"I Don\'t care if you\'re beautiful\" from her \"Beauty for the Blind\" EP, and finally from the Filipinos we hear another song by the band Tribe. The song is called \"The Way you Make Me Feel.\" Then we hear the song \"Where it Begins\" from \"Voodoo Tribe.\n\n\" Finally, we hear Adrian Raso\'s song \"Revenge of Ganesh,\" which is a long piece that\'s been recorded over the past 20 years. This is from his debut album SuperSonic Music Man, which was released in 1999. Now we hear Atilane\'s songs, starting with \"Telegramma,\" from her latest EP MeidoEmor Iveda, then \"The Doves,\" an English band that was active from 1998-2010.',NULL,NULL),(69318,1783,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/14/Under the Needle - November 14, 2023 at 13:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-14 13:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-16 08:13:00','2023-11-14 21:08:03','The show is called \"Live on KEXP\" and it\'ll be the second time it\'s been called that. It\'s this time, we\'re talking about a band called \"Spirit Award.\" They\'re a band that\'s making a lot of noise in the Seattle music scene. The band\'s lead singer, Daniel Lyon, is a singer-guitarist, songwriter, and producer. He\'s also a member of the band, and they\'re releasing their latest album, \"The Fear,\" on Share It. The first album was called \"Never Ending\" because it took so long to finish. The second album was a little different, though, called \"The Lunatic House,\" because it wasn\'t going to be as depressing as the first one.\n\nIt was more like a \"release of pent up emotion and energy\" . KEXP\'s DJ, Cheryl Waters, asks about the new album. The new album is like a release, and it feels like you\'ve let the past go, and you\'re opening new doors and new opportunities. He tells her that the new record is kind of like letting it come and go, like he has a little bit of a trance-',NULL,NULL),(69319,1453,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/14/Silver Screen Dream Machine - November 14, 2023 at 15:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-14 15:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-16 03:44:41','2023-11-14 23:07:57','The show opens with a tribute to Canadian music icon Robbie Robertson. He was one of Martin Scorsese\'s most trusted collaborators, and he composed the music for many of his films. The show starts off with a piece from his score for the upcoming film, Killers Of The Flower Moon.\n\nIt is called \"From the Soundtrack To Season 2 of The Run The World TV Soundtrack series released this yr that was Rob Glasper with \"What Love Can Do Featuring vocals by EmilyKing\" and \"Shame On Us\" . Next we hear music from the Canadian drama Sleeping Giants screenplay, a score from Chris Thornborough, and music from Sin City, a 2005 anthology film that was based on a comic book series.\n\nFrom the 2004 comedy Shaun Of The Dead, a film starring English duo Simon and Nick Frost, and Ash, a song from Coldplay, we hear the music of the pop stars.',NULL,NULL),(69320,3033,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/14/A Multilingual Affair - November 14, 2023 at 16:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-14 16:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-15 15:53:13','2023-11-14 23:08:23','The speaker begins by saying that she\'s here to inspire. She\'s talking about ego and love, which she describes as a \"self-reflection\" exercise. The speaker says that people should know that they\'re beautiful and that they don\'t have to do anything for the world to be a good place to be.\n\nShe says that she doesn\'t care if people think they have the right to live in the world, but that when they\'ve had a bad experience, she\'ll take responsibility for it and apologize. She also says that the music will help inspire the listeners. She has a good cry before the show, so she hopes that the listeners will be able to see her and then help her to heal from her experience. She then says that Charlotte de Panda is approaching.',NULL,NULL),(69321,91,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/14/Tuesday at 5 - November 14, 2023 at 17:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-14 17:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-15 15:40:06','2023-11-15 01:06:34','On Tuesday at 5pm, you can listen to this program or stream it from the CFRU archives. The program o