ssage From The Responsible Gambling Council.',NULL,NULL),(69330,80,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/15/CFRU Playlist - November 15, 2023 at 07:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-15 07:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-15 15:06:09','2023-11-15 15:06:09',NULL,NULL,NULL),(69331,207,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/ka8nx2/Music_w_db_Hawkes_Nov_15_2023_podcast6ij61.mp3','2023-11-15 15:04:08',289494203,'2023-11-16 07:34:51','2023-11-15 17:05:56','The program begins with the former programming director of the station, DB, talking about how important it is that the station continues to exist. He says that back when the station was known as CKLN and CRY, it was a part of the team, but now it is a full-fledged independent station.\n\nHe explains that they are trying to convince listeners to make a donation of $4 to help them continue their work. They have 26,300 favorite shows on the station and that means that every one of those listeners would reach their goal. If every person who listens to the station donated $4, they would reach the goal. Now that sounds impossible, but it\'s actually possible.\n\nIf you\'re a member of the organization, you can donate $89.50. If you listen to the program on the air, you\'ll hear a special guest: Michael Stor, who\'s also a fan of the program. He thanks the station for being a big supporter of the festival, and he thanks the listeners for supporting the station. The last song is a call to confidence.',NULL,NULL),(69332,99,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/15/The Stillness & The Dancing - November 15, 2023 at 10:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-15 10:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-16 07:23:05','2023-11-15 17:06:37','The show starts off with two pieces of music: one by M. Crook, another by Oxherding and a third by John Swank. The first piece is a collaboration between the two artists. The second is a new release from John Swank, called Sounding and Fathoms, which is out on lighten-up sounds. The third piece is from Adrian Lane, who\'s been friends with the show for a long time. Adrian has released a new collection of music on his label, Cheetra Records.\n\nThe show opens with a new track from Adrian, called AFamiliar Journey. Then it\'s time for a tour of some of the new music releases on the label, Outgrowth, Illumina, Lost Tribe Sound, and Skyphone. This is all from artists who have released their latest albums in the past few days. A lot of artists do listening parties where they invite listeners to chat with them about their latest releases.',NULL,NULL),(69333,99,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/15/The Stillness & The Dancing - November 15, 2023 at 09:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-15 09:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-16 07:10:27','2023-11-15 17:06:38','In this program, we hear from the host of the underground music show The Stillness and the Dancing, Joel Cuthbert. He\'s been through some medical treatments in Toronto and back home in Guelph, so he\'s recording some music for the show.\n\nHe says he is doing reasonably well, and thanks to his medical treatment, he\'ll be able to enjoy life in the city. He also thanks his listeners for their support, and he gives a shout-out to the artists who have reached out to him. The first track on the show is a new release from the Green Kingdom, an artist who has been making music for a long time.\n\nThis is their latest release, called \"Ether Hymns,\" and it\'s out November 11. The song is called \"Gathering Clouds\" and it says, \"In the literary sense, ether in the sense of the word can be defined like the clear sky.\" In making this music, Cuthbert often thought about how music is brought into existence and how it moves from one place to another. He notes that music is ephemeral, and that the music itself is always moving from place to place. So this show is all about the interwebs.',NULL,NULL),(69335,100,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/15/We Know Some Stuff + CFRU playlist - November 15, 2023 at 12:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-15 12:00:00',86507648,'2