on of women and organized schools for women, which helped support their families. In 1956, they started the Palestine National Liberation Movement, also known as the Popular Front for the Liberation of Palestine, in the Gaza workshop. Equality 7521 tells the story of how he met with the other leaders of the Palestinian National Front.\n\nHe explains that for nine years, they were very secret about their military activities, but on January 1, 1965, they launched their first military operation in occupied Palestine. The people wanted to join them. They contacted the other political parties, but they rejected their ideas, saying that they cannot liberate their land, that the war should be short- and decisive, and that they should not worry about their revolution. Both the Israelis and the Arabs sent secret police to arrest their commanders. All governments feared the revolution',NULL,NULL),(69348,97,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/16/Wild Combination - November 16, 2023 at 01:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-16 01:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-17 09:02:38','2023-11-16 09:06:37','EdVideo is a local organization that offers a variety of creative workshops and educational opportunities for people of all ages. The organization is open to all levels of creative expression. EdVideo\'s goal is to provide a place for people to learn, create, and display their work.',NULL,NULL),(69349,78,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/16/Morning Soul Shake-Up! - November 16, 2023 at 08:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-16 08:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-17 08:51:01','2023-11-16 15:06:24','',NULL,NULL),(69350,110,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/16/Here Today - November 16, 2023 at 07:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-16 07:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-17 08:43:22','2023-11-16 15:06:45','Aaron Badgley, host of the popular CFRU 96.3FM show, takes us back to the present to tell us about some of the latest music. First, he tells us that Paul Manchin has released a new album, Master, which contains 