h Sarah-Dilachy\'s long-form string quartet Long Gradus Part II. This track is one of three that the host has heard on the program. The other two tracks are from Josh-Josh Zubat\'s string quartet. The host says that he\'d like to',NULL,NULL),(69426,154,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/20/This Night Wounds Time - November 20, 2023 at 01:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-20 01:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-20 17:11:39','2023-11-20 09:07:17','This Night Wound\'s Time The show starts off with a geographical spotlight on music from Formosa province in Argentina.The artist is from that province, and there is only a limited amount of music from that area to choose from.So playing only one track from the artist is not an end in itself.The show then pauses for a brief break.\n\nThey will resume their program when they return.They ask listeners if they have something they are trying to fix, but don\'t know what\'s wrong with it.What if you have an art piece that you want to create but are unsure how to begin.Die Out, a community workshop that teaches people how to use tools and equipment, has moved to its new location and hosts weekly maker meetings on Monday nights from 8pm to 9pm.If you would like to tour the workshop or help with one of their community projects, they have a workshop at 700 York road every Monday night from 8:00pm to 9:00pm.\n\nWe invite you to join us on Sunday nights when we travel through the looking glass and follow the sounds wherever it takes us on the show.Alice tells us that the annual general meeting of the University of Guelph will be held on December 14th as a live and virtual',NULL,NULL),(69427,78,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/20/Morning Soul Shake-Up! - November 20, 2023 at 08:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-20 08:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-20 16:42:16','2023-11-20 15:05:59','',NULL,NULL),(69428,110,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/20/Here Today - November 20, 2023 at 07:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-20 07:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-20