w they don\'t always spend enough time on it. The conversation ends with a question about how people should use the word apocalypse to describe their current situation. The narrator thinks that many people already know the meaning of the word, but he thinks that it\'s hard for them to understand what an apocalypse might mean. He wonders if the word itself loses its meaning when people use it so often.',NULL,NULL),(69507,111,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/23/Tales from the Bridge - November 23, 2023 at 09:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-23 09:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-23 17:28:25','2023-11-23 17:06:35','In this episode, the gang discusses the recent episode of Tales From the Bridge, in which Peter Watts and MJ discuss the latest sci-fi movie, The Creator. They also discuss MJ\'s new book, Among Thieves and the Think of Thieves, and her new podcast, Sff Addicts. As they walk across the bridge, a listener asks to hear about the new Star Wars movie, \"The Creator.\n\n\" The group discusses the film\'s effects and its many contradictions. The first thing that jumps out to the listener is the fact that the robots in the movie seem to want to be completely free, but when they get over to New Asia, they\'re clearly set up to be like C3PO. The problem, according to the gang, is that the big robots are designed to be human-like.',NULL,NULL),(69508,182,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/npvyj6/NBR_Nov_22_2023763nq.mp3','2023-11-23 17:37:39',153729566,'2023-11-23 20:07:35','2023-11-23 19:05:31','This week on the No Beat Toronto Radio show, host Minesh welcomes listeners to his show and thanks everyone who has donated to the station. The show opens with a new track from Jim Bravo, who has played with some of his favorite bands including Polite Society and Hollow Earth.\n\nNext up is a new album from Mono Negatives. The band is celebrating 25 years and will be releasing a new one called Spetacular on November 27. The next set of music is a mix of new releases by L\'All. They 