ck from a Marvin Gaye album that came out in 1978, which is about six years after Gaye\'s death. Gaye was in the midst of getting divorced from his wife, and he had to concede half of the album\'s profits to go to her as part of her divorce settlement. He was being sued for \"amended alimony\" and had to go on a European tour to pay for it. The album didn\'t really do well for Motown, though, and it was a disappointment to collectors and fans of his work.\n\nThe Funky Fridays team then plays another track from the album, this one by a band called Philips from Washington, DC. The band was around in the 70s and did a little EP.',NULL,NULL),(69536,175,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/zui6qu/November_23rd_2023_No_Man_s_Land9r8gf.mp3','2023-11-24 19:07:02',287962512,'2023-11-26 02:51:07','2023-11-24 21:05:27','In this week\'s edition of the Community Radio Host\'s Talk, the host thanks listeners for their financial support of the station. He also announces that he\'ll be playing the 25th anniversary edition of his original radio show on the station on Friday, November 24, and invites listeners to join him in a dance to music from his latest album, \"Music is a Journey.\" ',NULL,NULL),(69537,186,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/auh26t/November_23rd_2023_Higher_Ground5zu7b.mp3','2023-11-24 19:14:29',287962512,'2023-11-25 19:12:37','2023-11-24 21:05:38','The host returns to the stage with a selection of new music. He thanks everyone who has been a part of the program and asks them to give a shout-out to the Minnesota man who has helped keep the show going. He then goes on to talk about the latest releases from musicians like Bruno Barrelet, Jimetta Rose, and more. He also talks about a new single from the upcoming album from Jose James, 38.',NULL,NULL),(69538,126,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/24/Viejoteca - November 24, 2023 at 14:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-24 14:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-24 21:06:51','2023-11-24 21:06:51',NULL,NULL,NULL),(69539,126,'https://arc