ngs that don t have swearing, but he doesn\'t remember what he said. We\'ve heard three songs from the album so far, and we\'re going to pick one more song to play at the end of the show.\n\nThe guy named SoCandy is coming up and he\'s also on the show, so the guys decide to give him 25 cents for the song. They also ask him about his new album. He says that he\'d been trying to do more collaborative stuff, and this album was an opportunity to do',NULL,NULL),(69542,170,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/bp4c33/Ruby_Slippers_Nov_24A_mp3_-_2023-11-21_305_PM67rq9.mp3','2023-11-24 23:58:15',111378520,'2023-11-25 18:10:40','2023-11-25 01:05:28','This week\'s program is called \"Ruby Slippers\" and it\'s about to begin. The producer says he\'s the producer of the program, and the name is \"Rhapsody Slippers.\n\n\" He\'s a little worried about how he\'ll sound on the show, but he does manage to pull together a pretty good mix of music that sounds good. There are some songs from the dead south, some tracks from the middle of the pack, and some songs that sound good but aren\'t. The first song is a Paul McEwen track that you might have heard before. The second track is a Ben Russell song called \"Brighter Light,\" the third is a Rob Stewart track called \"Wants,\" and the fourth is a Duran Duran track called the \"All You Need / Is Love,\" which sounds like a song from the \"Duran Duran\" soundtrack.\n\nThe next song is Trashhumanica\'s \"Revenge of Hieronymous,\" a new album that\'s just about to come out. The proceeds from the sales of',NULL,NULL),(69543,187,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/hpekza/DREAMING_-_EPISODE_NOVEMBER_24_2023b2tu0.mp3','2023-11-25 00:03:00',141171969,'2023-11-25 17:02:15','2023-11-25 01:05:38','',NULL,NULL),(69544,135,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/24/Folk Roots Radio - November 24, 2023 at 17:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-24 17:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-25 16:49:46','2023-11-25 01:06:52','This is the second in a series of all-music episodes on