his last album.',NULL,NULL),(69611,57654,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/27/Apollo Suns live on CFRU! - November 27, 2023 at 16:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-27 16:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-28 01:58:44','2023-11-27 23:07:36','The host and his friends are back on the CFRU 98.3 The Explorer with a new song: Vegas Phantom Power. The song is from the album Vegas Formula, and the host is glad it\'s out there. Also, one of the first songs on K-Tel, the third album from artist OX, is called Kung Fu.\n\nThe host is impressed with the ability of artists to change up their music genres so easily. Then, he\'s introduced to a band from Nova Scotia called Human Missile Crisis. They\'re a punk band with a punk vibe. Then he introduces Will Anderson, the lead singer of the band Weed. Weed is a Vancouver-based rock band. Weed has a rotating band of backing bands, which makes it sound like Weed has formed a band. ',NULL,NULL),(69612,82,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/27/Big Sis Radio - November 27, 2023 at 17:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-27 17:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-28 01:56:20','2023-11-28 01:05:56','In this special edition of Big Sis, Cece tells us about the new music being played on the show. First off, he tells us that this show is about supporting people who are experiencing poverty downtown.\n\nHe encourages listeners to push back against the injustices that exist around the world. He tells us the last tracks we listened to on Big Sis were Radio Collection by Ala-mode, Doubt by slowpulp, yearning by subsonic eye, palm owasa-nwok, and I-m-a-dog by faith healer. Next up, he gives us a track from Bri Webbs new album, Run With Me, which is about a period in his life when he was in turmoil and needed to find a way to get his music out there again. He says that the response to his new album was overwhelming. He thinks that Bris story reminds us all that we are all one human collective and that we all suffer from active hatred. This is the 58th show of Big sis.',NULL,NULL),(69613,83,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/27/to know the land - November 27, 2023 at 18:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-27 18:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-28 01:31:45','2023-11-28 01:06:02','Deer Day is here and Byron is the host of the show on 93.3 CFRU in Guelph. He\'s talking about the deer that are in the rut, the time when bucks are looking to mate. He explains that there are lots of deer tracks and signs all around the place. He says that people are out hunting and looking for these signs and tracks. He also says that the weather is cold, which is good because it means the deer are out in the cold.',NULL,NULL),(69614,157,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/wi6vmb/510-33-45-78-nov27-23.mp3','2023-11-28 01:38:15',287463030,'2023-11-28 04:15:33','2023-11-28 03:05:16','The show starts off with a discussion of King, who was a Canadian singer, songwriter, and musician who died in the United States in the early 1900s. He was followed by Deep Purple, King Crimson, King Cole, King Gannam, King and the Howler, and Bill King. King was a frequent guest on the Bill King Show, which was hosted by the late Bill King in Toronto in 1974. The first song on the King CD is \"Albatross\" by Fleetwood Mac. The second song is \"King and the Tubes with TV\" by King Crimson.\n\nThe third song is a song called \"Louis Rial\" by the King Crimson band. The fourth song is called \"Country and Western Hits\" by Jerry Lieber Mike. The fifth song is by Bob King and \"Gordie Howe Song\" which was written by Bob. The last song is an untitled song by King Cole. The song was recorded around the same time as the first two.',NULL,NULL),(69615,84,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/27/Blues Around the Block - November 27, 2023 at 20:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-27 20:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-28 03:51:09','2023-11-28 03:05:59','Mac Dee introduces himself as the host of the weekly blues show, \"Blues Around the Block.\" He welcomes listeners to the show and invites them to listen to the music.\n\nIn the first hour of the show, Mac Dee presents the music of Scott Ellison, Dawn Tyler Watson, Ben Racine, and Ditra Farr. The music of the Recording Alligator includes the Reverend Raven, the Chainsmoking Boys, Tony Joe White and the Charlie White. The song that Mac Dee and the others hear is \"It Takes A Lot to Laugh It Takes A Train to Cry.\" Mac Dee says that he doesn\'t play much of the music from the recording. He says that his favorite song is the one that the others heard.',NULL,NULL),(69616,84,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/27/Blues Around the Block - November 27, 2023 at 19:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-27 19:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-28 03:30:31','2023-11-28 03:06:00','This edition of the Blues Around the block is a continuation of the first edition, which was hosted by Mac Dee. This time around, Mac Dee is joined by his friend and fellow musician, the Hogtown All Stars. The show opens with John Primer\'s \"Hard Times\" and \"Tough Times,\" followed by \"Buddy Guy,\" \"Donald Ray Johnson,\" \"Last Call,\" and \"Down Child.\" Next, the show moves to Paul James\' \"Lost in Blues,\" \"Cut You Loose,\" and the \"Durham County Poets\'\" \"Hand Me Down Blues.\" The program ends with \"Something Ive Done,\" the last song ever recorded by Donald Ray Johnson.',NULL,NULL),(69617,85,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/27/Ripcord Radio - November 27, 2023 at 21:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-27 21:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-28 05:54:35','2023-11-28 05:05:52','The show opens with a shout-out to the listeners of 93.3 CFRU. It\'s a punk rock show with lots of music from the past and present. The first song we hear is from a band called We Believe, who have songs that are fast and dirty. The band\'s first album, Back from the Dead, was reissued in 2021. The band also has a demo from 1982 or 83, which they\'re currently offering as part of their complete discography collection at supremeecho.\n\nThen we hear some European music from Italy, Sweden, and England. We also hear some noisecore from the U.S. and Canada. The next song is from Young Mountain, who played their first Canadian show back in August at the New Friends Fest. Here\'s some more music from Europe. Next up is Superposition Principle, a project by Son of Denny from Poland. Then it\'s Old Pride from England. And finally, it\'ll be Age 16 from Baltimore.',NULL,NULL),(69618,86,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/27/The Deep House Project - November 27, 2023 at 22:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-27 22:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-28 05:34:19','2023-11-28 05:05:57','The Deep House Show opens with a recap of last week\'s show. The show starts off with a song called Feeling Sad by Nick Holder, which inspired the show to play an all-Canada mini-mix. The song features Diana Ross\'s voice from her hit \"Lover Man.\" The show then shifts to a song by Barbara Tucker, \"Beautiful People,\" which inspired them to play music inspired by other songs.\n\nThe next song is from Prophetic soul, \"Pyramid,\" which features a sample from \"The Temptations\" from their song \"Ant Too Proud To Beg.\" The next songs are from DJ Cozy, \"Pickup,\" and \"Jai Wolf,\" which reminds him of \"a few years back.\" The last track of the evening is from the Oles, \"Salvation,\" which will be their final track.',NULL,NULL),(69619,87,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/27/Back in the USSR - November 27, 2023 at 23:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-27 23:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-28 07:49:15','2023-11-28 07:06:21','',NULL,NULL),(69620,1447,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/28/Rainbow Country - November 28, 2023 at 00:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-28 00:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-28 07:30:47','2023-11-28 07:07:30','This week on the show, Conchita and her friends, Cora and Hard Cora, appear on the program to discuss their new book, \"Gay Talk,\" which is about their physical and emotional selves. The girls\' names are Barbie Q, and they are known as the \"B-Girls.\" The show is hosted by Mark Tara and produced by Conchita.',NULL,NULL),(69621,1447,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/28/Rainbow Country - November 28, 2023 at 01:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-28 01:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-28 09:27:41','2023-11-28 09:07:09','This is the first song on the Steve Grand tour, and it\'s called \"Rainbow Country.\" It\'s a tribute to all the music that he\'s loved throughout his life, whether it be classic disco, 80s house music, or even more recent independent artists like Grand himself. The song is called \"Everything I Own,\" \"Generations of Love,\" \"The Crying Game,\" \"Walking,\" \"Pink Champagne,\" and \"Don\'t Let The Light In,\" and it comes from Grand\'s latest album, \"Not The End of Me,\" which hit #2 on the Billboard Hot 100 chart and # 7 on the Independent',NULL,NULL),(69622,80,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/28/CFRU Playlist - November 28, 2023 at 06:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-28 06:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-28 13:05:53','2023-11-28 13:05:53',NULL,NULL,NULL),(69623,78,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/28/Morning Soul Shake-Up! - November 28, 2023 at 08:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-28 08:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-28 15:50:45','2023-11-28 15:06:10','This program is all about soul music. It\'s all about the community and how it\'s a great place to live. It starts off with a long description of the community, and then it moves on to a description of soul music and how you can sing along to it. It all ends with a shout-out to the people who are listening to the program.',NULL,NULL),(69624,110,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/28/Here Today - November 28, 2023 at 07:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-28 07:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-28 15:28:33','2023-11-28 15:06:33','On this edition of Know The Land, Byron tells listeners that deer day is here. He explains that the deer are in the rut and that there are lots of deer tracks and signs all around the place. He says that it\'s exciting for him to go out into the wild and track the deer 