owed by Mandingut\'s song from his second album in 2015, Suedlad, Vol. 3, and then by a song from Chile by Canifrou from her latest album, Aheesis. Then Regina changing her name from Indus Creed to Indus Creed, then Elusive from Australia, then Smile from their latest album Set Me on Fire, then Rock Machine from India, then finally by Minglewood from Nova Scotia, then Antihero from London, then Long Way From Texas from their second album Unpretty, then Blind Guardian from Singapore, then Theater of Pain by Blind Guardian, and finally Lizzie Mercier D\'Eclue from France, who died of cancer at age 47.',NULL,NULL),(69630,1783,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/28/Under the Needle - November 28, 2023 at 13:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-28 13:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-28 21:28:16','2023-11-28 21:07:29','This week on the show, we have an episode with a special guest: Jeremy Dutcher from the Tobic Nation in New Brunswick. He is a multi instrumentalist and a Juno Award winner for his latest album, Motewola nuuk, which is out on October 6th. This is a special episode of the show because it\'s part of a partnership between KEXP and Seedcast to share stories from artists like Jeremy.\n\nIt feels really good to have an artist like Jeremy share his knowledge of his people and language with the audience. It was a really powerful moment. KEXP DJ Teodros and Jessica Ramirez of Seedcast come on stage. They\'re joined by Dutcher. He starts this show with a song from his debut called SagaMaweed before he gets into a new song called Skijinuk. The song means Indian land. It just came out, and he\'s super stoked to share it with you. The second song is called Take My Hand. It means Hand in the Hand. The third song is Skijinuweeguuk. It\'sa song from the Halusa Nation, a group of artists that are all about raising awareness of the plight of indigenous peoples.\n\nThis song got sent to the Prime Minister back in Canada. You can listen to this song on the Seedcast where you can also find more stories like this. If you\'re on KEXP right now, check out the Sound and Vision Podcast, where Emily Fox talks about',NULL,NULL),(69631,155,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/7jdgfp/DrMouth_CIUTshow_nov28_2023_fullmix.mp3','2023-11-28 22:13:34',285835328,'2023-11-29 00:29:18','2023-11-28 23:05:24','The narrator tells us that the community radio station, CIUT FM, needs more money to operate. James Brown comes on stage and tells us all that he\'s doing fine. He\'s had a good laugh, though, and he tells the listeners to donate money to the station now.',NULL,NULL),(69632,296,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/cstxh9/show_11252b7smn.mp3','2023-11-28 22:06:41',87330760,'2023-11-29 00:09:48','2023-11-28 23:05:46','This is the third-face on the community radio station, CIUT. This week they\'re doing a song-a-day challenge, where they\'ll play a song from one of their old shows and ask listeners to remember it for all of their friends. The challenge is to spot the song for listeners who\'ve never heard the show before. If you can do that, you can donate to their fall-fundraising drive.\n\nThe guys say that they\'ve been thinking about all of the great things of their time, like the rings on Mr. President\'s finger, the rings in his feet, the cheese grater in his house, and all the cheese in his government cheese and ham sandwiches. They\'re all fit for life in their skinny house. So if you like the songs of the time, please consider donating to the men\'s fund-raising drive, too. They also have a new song for you. It\'s called \"The Celebration,\" and it\'s a love song about celebrating one\'s life. In other words, the song is all about celebrating the fact that you\'re alive.',NULL,NULL),(69633,1453,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/28/Silver Screen Dream Machine - November 28, 2023 at 15:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-28 15:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-28 23:51:51','2023-11-28 23:07:08','It\'s another episode of the Silver Dream Machine, a show about movies. This time, it\'s from the music of John Frian and Adam Sandler\'s comedy Punch Drunk Love. The music from I Like Movies and Steel Magnolias also make an appearance. The first song is from Lightburn\'s score from the Canadian film 2022 and the second is from Breon and Breon\' score from Anderson\'s 2002 comedy Punch-Drunk Love.\n\nNow it turns to an old time radio piece from the Marx Brothers compilation, The 1989 Shows. This is an old-school radio piece that\'s part of a movie parade. The piece is a promo from the classic comedy Dux Soup. The movie is a comedy about a troupe of musical personalities who perform through a loudspeaker. The program begins with a description of the characters. First up is Groucho , a diplomat from Fredonia who is afraid of his shadow.\n\nThen there\'s Harpo, a super spy who shadows too many suspects; then Chico , the war minister who goes nuts every time he goes nuts; then Zeppo , Bob Firefly, the son of Rufus-T. . We switch over to the Paramount studio where the Four-Marx Brothers are shooting their new comedy, DuxSoup. This scene is set in the reception salon of the Fredonia palace, where the former president\'s widow anxiously awaits her newly appointed dictator. The guests are waiting for her, and',NULL,NULL),(69634,3033,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/28/A Multilingual Affair - November 28, 2023 at 16:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-28 16:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-28 23:27:01','2023-11-28 23:07:24','In this chapter, the creator of Silence, a creative space in Guelph, explains the lesson he\'s learned today. He says that finding the lesson is the most important thing to do, because when you find the lesson, you\'ll be able to do whatever it is you need to do. When you\'re done with the lesson and in the other place, it\'ll all be a great experience. The creator says that he\'ll kick the universe\'s butt with some \"great vibes\" from all over, so it\'s a wonderful day.',NULL,NULL),(69635,91,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/28/Tuesday at 5 - November 28, 2023 at 17:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-28 17:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-29 01:47:22','2023-11-29 01:06:06','On Tuesday at 5pm, Bonnie Doome hosts another edition of her program on CFRU-FM 93.3. She introduces her listeners to a new compilation album titled \"Sunny Don\'t go Away,\" a tribute to Newfoundland singer-songwriter, Ron Hines. The songs on the album include the title track \"Where do you get off,\" a song by Barry Canning, and the song \"Sunny\'s Dream\" by Kelly Loder. The lyrics to the song are \"Say goodbye to Ron.\" The songs from the album are also included in the program.',NULL,NULL),(69636,1455,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/28/Down the Rabbit Hole - November 28, 2023 at 18:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-28 18:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-29 01:29:36','2023-11-29 01:07:16','The program begins with a description of the music on the show, which is described as \"down the rabbit hole\" . The first song on the program is a Japanese artist called Toeotei, who is dressed in a kimono with a bunch of other artists. The second song is a song called Helvetia by Bingenruth. The third song is from one of their ambient duos, called Let the moon view planet.\n\nThe fourth song is Destroyer\'s \"Savage Night at the opera\" , which he describes as a \"mix of tragedy but hopeful.\" The fifth song is \"Little Movements and playing no trees\" by Eberhard Weber. The program ends with a discussion of snow, which seems to be a big fan of the guys.',NULL,NULL),(69637,94,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/28/Let’s Get Lost - November 28, 2023 at 20:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-28 20:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-29 03:48:12','2023-11-29 03:06:09','The show opens with a brief description of the program. The program is called \"Let\'s get lost,\" and it is a weekly program that plays music that it loves. It is a very eclectic program, with a lot of older stuff and new stuff that is still in its early stages of discovery.\n\nThe first track on the program is Brain Freeze from Bone Shaker, an album that was released in 2014. The program then moves to a bigger band, Audio One, and then to Myra Melford\'s Fire and Water, a band that is playing on her latest album, Hear the light singing. The band also includes some of her favorites, like Tamika Reed and Mary Halversons, as well as some new players, like Ingrid Labrock and Leslie Mock. The show ends with a short description of a new album, Air, Light and Harmony, by Badgie Pook. The album is a triptych of three albums, all released in chronological order. All three albums feature compositions that resample loops. The third album is all- helmed by the artist Maximilian Turnbull.',NULL,NULL),(69638,1591,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/28/New or Never - November 28, 2023 at 19:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-28 19:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-29 03:27:36','2023-11-29 03:07:20','The program opens with a mix of music that\'s loaded into the automatic music player in the wrong place. Fortunately, the program is now called \"Now or Never\" and will be airing at 11pm. The music starts off with the music from Hotel Decor, which comes from the Chicago-based artist Douglas Andrew McCommiss.\n\nThen, there\'s Vancouver-based singer songwriter Julian Taylor from the Anthology, Volume 1 . And then there are the tracks from the Hillsborough album, which come from the British Columbia-based musician Gabriel Birnam-Ginnbaum. And the music comes from Ocan, a Canadian Afro Cuban jazz group. And finally, the Juno-winning artist Grit comes out with a song called \"I want to be man of me\" .',NULL,NULL),(69639,95,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/28/Humanoid Radio - November 28, 2023 at 22:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-28 22:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-29 05:46:38','2023-11-29 05:06:00','This is the second half of the Humanoid Radio show. It begins with the title track of Nihilsika off of the Source of Babe album. It goes on to include Terror off the Joy album, a track titled Okpothenes, The member Okhil and Ijoema off the Album Late, a Track titled About You, Slow off the Wyltk EP, and a track called Badabing. It ends with the instrumental remix of the track. You are listening to the program on CFRU 93.3.\n\nIt\'s the first time we\'ve heard anything from an alien entity. According to the host, humans have been communicating with other non-human beings since the dawn of time. He tells us that since the first attempt to communicate with them by radio, they\'ve developed their own language. He says that he\'s going to be back the next Tuesday to bring you the best and latest from jazz, experimental music, world and soundscapes.',NULL,NULL),(69640,94,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/28/Let’s Get Lost - November 28, 2023 at 21:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-28 21:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-29 05:27:40','2023-11-29 05:06:01','The program opens with a track from Bill King\'s new album, \"Ivory Town\". The group also discusses James Brandon Lewis\'s Red Lily Quintet and Kate Gentile\'s latest release, \"Find Letter X\". The program ends with a song from Anna Webber\'s \"Shermeep Wints\". The show then moves on to the local business community. If you\'re looking for a way to promote a business event, CFRU has the resources to help you get your message heard.',NULL,NULL),(69641,96,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/28/Cyber Lich’s Gothic Castle - November 28, 2023 at 23:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-28 23:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-29 07:44:03','2023-11-29 07:06:30','',NULL,NULL),(69642,109,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/29/Radia - November 29, 2023 at 00:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-29 00:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-29 07:23:40','2023-11-29 07:06:39','',NULL,NULL),(69643,180,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/xz9m2h/HOWL_-_NOVEMBER_26_2023aa5sk.mp3','2023-11-29 11:43:19',56689813,'2023-11-29 13:31:01','2023-11-29 13:05:25','Hal on the Island is a public service announcement produced by the Hal895FM, a community radio station located 