 it\'s cool that they were able to do all of these covers on their TV show. He also says that Chad Allen played in the band with the same singer, the Guess singer. The two of them were in the',NULL,NULL),(69816,99,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/12/06/The Stillness & The Dancing - December 6, 2023 at 10:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-12-06 10:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-06 17:48:30','2023-12-06 17:06:13','The Stillness and The Dancing takes listeners on a journey through the world of underground music. We start off with a description of the music on the show. The hour starts off with Yuko and then Adrian Lane. Adrian is a composer who can make two appearances.\n\nHe has released a number of new tracks this year, including a track called \"Water Wash Away The Waves\" which will be on the program for the first time. There is also music from a few other underground artists as well, including Olafur Arnold, Gia Margaret, and the Invisible EP from Olafur. The Invisible EP is an older EP, but one that Olafur had been studying or studying lately. The second hour starts with music by Connor Walsh. Connor was a young composer who died young. He had released an older release in 2019, but one he stumbled on when he was listening to the program.\n\nThe music on this show is winter-like music. There are some tracks from Bruno SanFilippo, Jekazik, and others. Adrian Lane is also on the list, as is one of his horn tracks from last year\'s \"Envoy the Birds\" which is on this program. Finally, there is music from another underground artist, Fingalbone, who has been supporting him with an improvised piece.',NULL,NULL),(69817,99,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/12/06/The Stillness & The Dancing - December 6, 2023 at 09:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-12-06 09:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-06 17:28:31','2023-12-06 17:06:14','In this edition of The Dancing Stillness and the Stillness, host Joel Cuthbert goes through a list of the best of the year\'s new music. He begins by saying that he\'ll b