ys that when he tries to help, he starts like a team and doesn\'t give a damn. He tells us that he isn\'t a \"Darlin\' Darlin\' Darell\' Darel\' Dar\'lin\' dar\'l\' Dare\'l, Dar\'ll\' Darly\'s Dar\'Lin\' Dar, Dar-Lin-Darly\'Sid\'L\'Ln\'Ll\'N\'Lle\'Lon\'Lli\'L-Lon-Loni\'Loni\" like the other niggas.\n\nThe narrator then reads a list of the people who remixed the song \"Filly Friends\" by Mikuchu. It was sung by Letie, who also sings, and also by the Ghost Poet, who sings. The other artists who worked on the song are Capital K, Suicide Dogs, Taz, Naked and Boys',NULL,NULL),(69952,2653,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/12/12/Solipsistic Retreat - December 12, 2023 at 09:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-12-12 09:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-12 17:29:33','2023-12-12 17:08:01','This is the second track from the new album, \"Kill Mike.\" It\'s called \"Black Like My Skin,\" and the lyrics are all about how, as a black man, I\'ve always been a \"black in the middle\" .\n\nHe\'s a leader, he says, and he doesn\'t want to be one of those people who\'s just going to sit there and do nothing. He wants to be the leader of the people around him, the one who gives them the message. He says he knows some secrets leaders won\'t know, but he can\'t reveal them because he\'s so smart. He knows people, he knows how to talk to them, he can do whatever he wants with them. He calls them \"apps,\" but they\'re not cool.\n\nHe is a \"beast,\" a \"stack of leek,\" and a \"morehouse man,\" a.k.a. Spike Lee. So, yeah, he is a leader. He tells his listeners to tune in to the music on the next track, \"The Merry Listeners and Guelph,\" because it\'s the last track on the album.',NULL,NULL),(69953,158,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/nvjsyc/The_Radical_Reverend_December_12thbrzah.mp3','2023-12-12 17:15:57',143961989,'2023-12-12 20:09:52','2023-12-12 19:05:19','Radical Reverend Cheri Novo preaches to the congregation in a solilo',NULL,NULL),(69954,90,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/12/12/Bridging T