nd hateful man. The speaker then turns to the music, saying, \"This is my cousin, diani, with ambience, growing like mad, on the charts, and a lovely song.\"',NULL,NULL),(69961,91,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/12/12/Tuesday at 5 - December 12, 2023 at 17:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-12-12 17:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-13 01:48:28','2023-12-13 01:06:08','On Tuesday at 5 Mac Dee hosts a music show on a local station. He starts off by talking about the death of a boomer musician, Chad Allen, who was a founding member and lead singer of the Guess Who. The song \"Shaken All Over\" was one of the first hits of the new wave. The band changed its name to \"Chad Allen and Expressions\" in 1963, and changed again in 1965 to \"The Guess Who\" . In 1966, Allen left the Guess who to sing again with a band called \"Brave Belt\" , which would later become the band \"The Bachman Turner Overdrive\" and then the band Chad Allen and \"The Expressions\" ).',NULL,NULL),(69962,1455,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/12/12/Down the Rabbit Hole - December 12, 2023 at 18:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-12-12 18:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-13 01:30:09','2023-12-13 01:07:07','The host continues his conversation with host by announcing that he\'s about to go live in another room. We\'re back with the host, who\'s got a new song out for us all to hear. This song is from Helena\'s latest album, Suddenly My Mind is Blank. The Underground Guy loves the song, which reminds him a lot of Tron. Next up is a song from Alarain\'s new album, I Killed your Dog. We also get a few tracks from the album, A New Tomorrow, from another underground artist named Zulu.',NULL,NULL),(69963,94,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/12/12/Let’s Get Lost - December 12, 2023 at 20:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-12-12 20:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-13 03:46:52','2023-12-13 03:06:30','Scott introduces his program of weekly jazz-related material. The program starts off with a Van der Mark5 and a live recording of a club in Poland. Sco