oday, but he\'s determined to keep going. He plays some Christmas songs, including Jingle All The Way, which he finds very emotional. He also plays some other Christmas songs. He even plays a song about a girl named Jilly. He ends the show with a song called \"Merry Christmas Carol.',NULL,NULL),(70162,122,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/12/21/Forever Deaf - December 21, 2023 at 23:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-12-21 23:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-22 07:27:54','2023-12-22 07:06:53','The host is sitting in his apartment in New York City, reading his latest book, Never Deaf Dean. He can\'t figure out how to explain the loss of his identity without a compass, so he\'s listening to music.\n\nHe starts off the show by playing a song by a band called Sanctuary from a 1986 compilation called Dream the Insurrection. Then he plays a track called Nevermore from a Cold World from December 13, 2017. Then he remembers that the band lost its lead singer in December of last year, a guy named Worrald-Dane. He says that he\'ll be talking to the host whenever he sees him. Then, he plays some songs by bands that he thinks are Muslim bands. He plays a song called Your Prophecy from a band from Israel. He also plays some of the songs from his Harvesters Of Flesh and Bones album. He ends the show with another song called The Undead Swarm from his collection called Billion Passes Burn From the Drowning Into Shadows.',NULL,NULL),(70163,122,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/12/22/Forever Deaf - December 22, 2023 at 01:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-12-22 01:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-22 09:30:19','2023-12-22 09:06:36','This episode of the Perg show is produced by Amora Law, a student at the University of Utah, and her co-host, the musician Operg. The Perg Show is a weekly spoken word program on the campus and community station, CFRU 93. If you are 5 to 18 years old, a team is looking for you to participate in an environmental survey, a journal entry, or a podcast. Or if you are studying youth an