ks the guys if they\'re done with their shopping, and if they can find a parking space in the crazy malls. Romeo wants to see it, so he asks them to take a picture and show him.',NULL,NULL),(70204,143,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/12/23/Mach Vibe Radio - December 23, 2023 at 21:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-12-23 21:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-24 05:30:30','2023-12-24 05:06:34','This week, the UM professors discuss the different types of students who might be interested in participating in a study on the impact of climate change on older adults.\n\nThere are two kinds of students: those who have gone through the disaster and those who are returning to school for the first time since the first disaster. The UM professors want to know how these groups experienced the crisis and how they might use this knowledge to help mitigate future disasters. They also want to learn more about the popular music show, Kleine Gail, which airs on Sundays at noon. If you are between the ages of 5 and 65, a team would like to hear your story. They want to conduct a survey, interview, journal entry, or podcast. The study is being conducted by the UM Office of Research and Ethics and the UM Institutional Review Board.',NULL,NULL),(70205,144,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/12/24/The Underground - December 24, 2023 at 00:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-12-24 00:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-24 07:47:10','2023-12-24 07:06:57','The Underground is on the radio. It\'s a show about the art of doing nothing, which is very different from the art you\'re used to in school. It involves doing everything in the easiest and most relaxed way possible. This is how the Underground teaches us to do everything, even if it\'s not very fun.\n\nHe tells us that if we want to do something, we need to find a way to do it. He also says that there\'s no better place to start than Silence Guelph, a music venue, studio, and art gallery that\'s just waiting to be used. They\'re offering a flat rate of $100 a day to rent out the space. If you want to start a workshop, host a party, or run a conference, you can rent it out.',NULL,NULL),(70206,144,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/12/23/The Underground - December 23, 2023 at 23:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-12-23 23:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-24 07:24:27','2023-12-24 07:06:58','',NULL,NULL),(70207,1627,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/12/24/Jitterbuggin - December 24, 2023 at 02:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-12-24 02:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-24 09:53:06','2023-12-24 09:07:28','The Hip-Stakers are back on the air. Adrian and Jitterbouggin are talking about the holidays. It\'s Christmas Eve and it\'s been a long night. Jitterbunggin wants to play some songs from his Christmas show. He\'s having technical difficulties with his CD, so he\'s going to play a couple of songs from the Colin James show. The first song is from a new guy named Lindy McQueen. The second song is a cover of \"Grease Marks\" by the Shook Boys.',NULL,NULL),(70208,1627,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/12/24/Jitterbuggin - December 24, 2023 at 01:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-12-24 01:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-24 09:29:53','2023-12-24 09:07:29','The Hipstakers play a Christmas concert and Adrian starts off by playing a song called Jitter-Bitter. The song is about a guy named Colin James who\'s playing a big band. Adrian says he hasn\'t played any big bands in a while, so he\'s psyched to play a song like that.\n\nHe also says that he doesn\'t have a bunch of Christmas music on the air today, so this is a chance to play some of his favorite Christmas songs. The first song is called \"Colin James\" and it has a Christmas theme. The lyrics are about Colin James, the guy who goes back in time to visit his favorite girl, \"Nadine.\" The narrator says that the song is actually a remake of a time machine that was released way back in \'99. It\'s called \"James\" because the song says \"James.\"',NULL,NULL),(70209,145,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/12/24/Visions fugitives - December 24, 2023 at 08:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-12-24 08:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-24 15:30:52','2023-12-24 15:06:57','This week, Fangwei chooses the pieces for the upcoming show, and he\'s still involved in the production. The show is called \"Opus 17,\" and it\'s a classical music program. One of the two students will come up the pieces and the other will respond with his or her own selections. The students will then come up with their own pieces. Now, this program isn\'t going to be about Opus 17.\n\nInstead, the students are going to talk about the word \"palimpsest,\" which is a Latin word meaning \"to scrape\" or \"scrape.\" The word was first used in Greek in the 16th century, but it was also used in the 17th century. So, we\'re talking about the use of writing in the ancient world. Back then, writing was often used multiple times, and even if it was old, the new writing had to be better. That\'s why the word was called palimpsed. But the word is also used to refer to documents that have multiple layers.\n\nSo this is the definition of the word. It\'s from the Greek word palimpsisos, meaning \"scrap,\" which means to scrape or scrape. This word was originally used to say \"to scrap,\" but it also meant \"to be scraped.\" So, the word used to mean \"to have multiple copies of a document.\" It was used by Cicero in Cicero\'s De Republica, which means \"to retain',NULL,NULL),(70210,145,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/12/24/Visions fugitives - December 24, 2023 at 09:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-12-24 09:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-24 17:48:57','2023-12-24 17:06:59','We start off this program with a discussion of the Opus 17, which is a number assigned to a piece by a composer. Some of the pieces that we\'ve heard so far are Opus 17 works, or works that were previously assigned to Opus 17, but are now assigned to the Opus 17 system.\n\nFor example, Thomas Ades has a piece called \"Asyla\" that was originally attributed to Beethoven but is now attributed to Bartok. If Beethoven wrote the piece, it would be a coincidence, but it\'s too remote. We also hear a description of the word \"cicada\" . It\'s an insect that lives on the roof of buildings all over the world.',NULL,NULL),(70211,146,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/12/24/The Kookoo Bananas Variety Hour - December 24, 2023 at 10:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-12-24 10:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-24 17:27:56','2023-12-24 17:07:00','The children are ready to hear the story of a man dressed in a red coat, a big white goatee, and a flyer. He is a man with a red beard and a giant white beard. The song is a departure from the traditional Christmas song.\n\nIt is a song about sending Christmas without you, and it is based on the idea that there is never snow or snow without snow. The group sings the song, and Will Carter sings the lyrics. He tells the children that he is coming to wish them all a very Merry Christmas and a Happy New Year.',NULL,NULL),(70212,148,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/12/24/Clan Na Gael - December 24, 2023 at 12:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-12-24 12:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-24 19:27:25','2023-12-24 19:06:54','This is a short break between Christmas and the start of the new school year. It\'s a good time for us to take a breather from all the craziness and talk about all the cool things happening in the world. We\'re talking about music, movies, and the like. We also talk about some new stuff we\'re going to be doing with the National Film Board this winter season. And that\'s just for kicks.',NULL,NULL),(70213,219,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/xf6zd2/ES231220.mp3','2023-12-24 19:44:12',139418733,'2023-12-24 22:07:39','2023-12-24 21:05:37','The second part of the show opens with the announcement that the show is now called Electric Sense. It is co-hosted by Marbellia. The show is about to begin when James Bailey announces that he has forgotten to mention some of the tracks from the previous show.\n\nHe explains that he will play a track from the T