 He offered him a job',NULL,NULL),(70215,148,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/12/24/Clan Na Gael - December 24, 2023 at 13:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-12-24 13:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-24 21:26:19','2023-12-24 21:06:52','',NULL,NULL),(70216,197,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/npc9a7/phil_s_inn_dec_23_236xhyt.mp3','2023-12-24 22:07:21',287962512,'2023-12-24 23:46:38','2023-12-24 23:05:36','',NULL,NULL),(70217,101,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/12/24/Seems Like Old Times - December 24, 2023 at 15:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-12-24 15:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-24 23:34:45','2023-12-24 23:06:14','Art Not Shame is asking for donations to help them expand access to art. Clifton Joseph, the co-founder of Frequency Modulation, praises Campus Radio, CFRU, and Campbell Soup. He explains that audiences of the time knew that the \"best man to play at Christmas time\" was Lionel Barrymore, who played Charles Dickens \"Cranky\" curmie on many shows. On Christmas eve 1939, he had the role of Scrooge in the Campbell Playhouse production, hosted and sponsored by Orson Welles. The Campbell Playhouse was a continuation of the Mercury Theater of late 1930s, which was based on the work of Charles Dickens.\n\nCampbell Soup has been making soups for the past five Christmases, and they have chosen to thank their customers by giving them a Christmas present. The gift they chose five years ago, and the gift they choose each year since, has become a Christmas tradition for many and many families. They prepare the gift and hope that the younger children will be able to hear the carol.',NULL,NULL),(70218,149,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/12/24/La Buena Onda - December 24, 2023 at 16:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-12-24 16:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-24 23:06:52','2023-12-24 23:06:52',NULL,NULL,NULL),(70219,189,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/mdttq5/VFTC_Xmas239ch8e.mp3','2023-12-25 00:00:51',283157942,'2023-12-25 01:46:01','2023-12-25 01:05:28','',NULL,NULL),(70220,149,'https://archive.