eat show for them. He\'s going to play some music from the Celtic harpist, Lance de Valle, and he\'ll be playing some music that\'s been influenced by the harpist\'s Renaissance album. The music is going to start at 5 and end at 8.',NULL,NULL),(70223,108,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/12/24/Wind-Down - December 24, 2023 at 20:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-12-24 20:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-25 03:49:47','2023-12-25 03:06:21','In this short but entertaining program, Tom describes the preparations he has made for Christmas. He and his brother, Dorian, have made a long-standing bet that each Christmas Eve they will pick which song will play on their local station. They play a song called \"The 12 Days of Christmas\" from Bob and Doug\'s Christmas album, which they have compiled into a Christmas CD called \"A Very Special Christmas\" . They also play a Christmas quiz for Doug, which is easy to answer. The CD also contains a Christmas compilation called \"Run DMC with Christmas In Hollis\" , which Tom has found on the street',NULL,NULL),(70224,150,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/12/24/Zombie Jamboree - December 24, 2023 at 19:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-12-24 19:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-25 03:25:55','2023-12-25 03:06:54','',NULL,NULL),(70225,152,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/12/24/Through the Looking Glass - December 24, 2023 at 21:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-12-24 21:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-25 05:46:40','2023-12-25 05:06:42','If you\'re a fan of new music and want to support the arts in your community, you can support the cause by pledging $10 a month to the silent arts. This is a great way to do so without breaking the bank. If you can\'t commit, then there\'s a simple way to support silent arts: you can share a picture of yourself and commit to donate a month\'s worth of your earnings.',NULL,NULL),(70226,153,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/12/24/Backtracks - December 24, 2023 at 22:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-12-24 22:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-25 05:33: