/DrMouth_CIUTshow_Jan2_fullshow.mp3','2024-01-03 14:10:02',283388288,'2024-01-03 15:36:02','2024-01-03 15:05:21','This chapter opens with a description of the Nile River and the magicians who live there. The most famous is Kotep, also known as the \"Scarlet Sorcerer\" because of his scarlet appearance.\n\nKotep was banished by the gods for his sins against black magic. He had a magic formula that could summon his spirit from the past. He was buried with this formula, and legend says that a magician of the future could invoke his powers. This is all for today\'s class, he says. Oh, shit! King Wilkins! I have figured out the inscriptions I\'m ready to try to summon the spirits of great sorcerers from past into today. What\'s a drivel! You need a psychiatrist? Ah, so, you think Im mad? Well, he\'s not a human. He\'s been gathering magical powers to overthrow his enemies. He shows them the \"killed and everlasting empire\" of black magic, and asks who the boss is. It\'s the statue. The Scarlet Sorcerer, he explains, is the man who killed King Wilkins. He has come to life and wants to kill the kids at school.\n\nHe calls out to Susan to stop running away. She does, and he runs off to get help. He sees the kid in the crowd, and calls out for help. The kid looks ugly, and says that the guy in the mask is the \"mightiest magician ever spawned by land of the Pharaohs. And that',NULL,NULL),(70382,174,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/zm84dy/January_3_2024_Global_Rhythmsaqwu1.mp3','2024-01-03 15:27:49',431961989,'2024-01-03 17:29:29','2024-01-03 17:05:23','The program begins with Ken Stauer, the host, telling listeners about the upcoming program. He tells listeners that the program is called \"Global Rhythms\" and that it will be the first edition of the program in the year of 2024. He then introduces the program\'s first artist, a singer, songwriter and musician from New Zealand named Jon Hayas. He also introduces Ken to some of the other artists featured on the program, including Ting Mong, Yuthi, Maca Dread, the Jungle Groove, Dengue fever, Always K, and Dens by Tape Master Lenhart.',NULL,NULL),(70383,195,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/pkc3qi/Dementia13RadioShow_24_01_02.mp3','2024-01-03 17:30:27',230373376,'2024-01-03 19:30:05','2024-01-03 19:05:33','This is the first of a two-part series on the first year of the new millennium. The narrator talks about how the world is moving forward, but that there is still a lot of sadness and strife in the world. He says he is thankful to be in the present, and that he is also thankful for the music he plays on the show, which he calls \"psychedelic rock.\" He wants to play some of the songs that he has heard before, and he decides to play them all in one night.',NULL,NULL),(70384,289,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/bxv4rz/The_Next_Stop_1327q40w.mp3','2024-01-04 04:08:21',271109894,'2024-01-04 05:47:42','2024-01-04 05:05:44','The Next Stop is a music show that airs every two hours on Ciut 89.5FM in Toronto. The show starts with a score from the first ever Godzilla movie, Ifukube, and goes on to play music from all over the world. This year\'s film, Godzilla Minus 1, comes from the music of Naoki Sato, who is inspired by the music from the original movie IfukuBe. The next two hours will be devoted to listening to music from each of the 20th century\'s greatest movies.\n\nWe start off with the first film of the year, Godzilla Sweet 1, followed by the second film, Toby and Girl, followed by another, Montrese with Godzilla, and the third, La Knight. Next, we\'ll hear from Betinho, Roxane, Flora Purim, Eduardo Arujo, Silvina, Opanishe, Barbara, Sassy, and Old Friend. We continue on with Thievery Corp., which will be followed by Jwords.',NULL,NULL),(70385,289,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/mmhsgw/The_Next_Stop_131bt6sw.mp3','2024-01-04 04:01:26',272622165,'2024-01-04 05:30:09','2024-01-04 05:05:44','The Next Stop is a weekly music program airing on CIUT 99.5 FM in Toronto. The program is a mix of funk, soul, pop, and R&B tracks from all over the world.\n\nTonight\'s program is all about the movie City of God, which takes place in the favelas, or slums, in Rio de Janeiro in the late 60\'s and early 80\'s. This is a time period where organized crime was on the rise, and the city was being torn apart by turf wars between two rival factions. The music featured in the film captures the spirit of this era. The score composed by Antonio and Ed Cortes is also included on the program. If you enjoy the music, you can find past episodes on the Next Stop\'s show pages at nextstop.fm and on iTunes. The first track of tonight is called Estoria De Boca from the film. It\'s from Antonio and Edgar and is the first of many tracks that will be heard on the show.\n\nThe next few tracks are from other countries as well. They include Misanga from the Bayana System, Ta Fal To Um Pescando from Uubelen, and Misanga again from the band Ijo Coffee, all from the city of God. Next is a track from the movie called Can I Change my Mind. The last two tracks are also from the same city. Next up is Vida Giottiario from Antonio, Ed, and Vida giottiario again from Antonio.',NULL,NULL),(70386,219,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/ip7zq2/ES240103.mp3','2024-01-04 06:47:51',143313067,'2024-01-04 07:28:17','2024-01-04 07:05:51','The program starts off with James Bailey, the program host, talking about the station he\'s running, which is still Ciut 89.5 FM, which isn\'t too shabby. He thanks everyone who contributed to the station\'s fund-raising drive.\n\nHe also says that he\'ll try to put a link up for the upcoming show on Friday. He\'s heard some new music from Golden and Will, and he\'d like to hear it, too. The first track is called \"wind in trees,\" which sounds like it\'s going to be a thunderstorm. The second is \"Harmonic rain,\" and the third is \"All Lifelong,\" a new organ track from a woman named Callie Malone. The program goes off on a tangent, and we learn that the other two tracks on the program are by two different artists, one called \"Golden,\" the other \"Valley,\" and they\'re all from Christine Ott, who\'s from Strasbourg, France. The third track is a new piece by Malone called \"All lifelong,\" which is coming out soon.',NULL,NULL),(70387,189,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/2hyuaw/vftc_jan3948rn.mp3','2024-01-04 14:31:01',285059520,'2024-01-04 15:32:11','2024-01-04 15:05:33','The Crypt Master opens the show with a tribute to the musicians who have died in the past year. He begins with Earth Wind and Fire who have lost two members since the beginning of the year. Fred White who is the brother of the founding members of the band passed away last year and was followed by drummer Sheldon White who died a few months later. The Yardbirds who lost two musicians this past year also start the show. Guitarist Topom passed away and is replaced by Jeff Beck who is 22 years old. The rest of the show is devoted to the artists who shaped our musical landscape and created the soundtracks to our formative memories.\n\nThe Mersey Beat band who steered the British invasion in the early years of the 20th century, Les Maguire who was the last original member until he died last November, Leon Hughes who was also last until he joined up in heaven last March, Charlie Thomas who was with the Drifters for a decade, and David Crosby who co-wrote one of the most famous songs of all time.',NULL,NULL),(70388,205,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/bhejkh/January_4_2024_Music_At_High_Noon8c30f.mp3','2024-01-04 20:49:44',228091648,'2024-01-04 21:33:15','2024-01-04 21:05:58','The program opens with a song called \"High Noon\" by the band High Noon. The narrator is Mike Tadros, who is the host and producer for the program. The program begins with the song \"See Me Livin\" by Son Roberts, followed by \"Do You Read Me\" by Devin Cuddy, \"We\'ve Got A Lot To Unlearn\" by Thomas Wade, \"Not the Only One\" by Poison Headache, \"Meet Me In the Morning\" by Samantha Martin and \"Delta Sugar\" by Dr. Falada. The music ends with \"Mrs. Moto\" by Mrs. Moto.',NULL,NULL),(70389,1551,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/ctq7s6/jan42024.mp3','2024-01-05 00:26:08',431961989,'2024-01-05 01:32:00','2024-01-05 01:05:44','The second part of the program kicks off with a remix of Ready from Tool Room by Dave and Mark Knight. The program then switches to a back-to-the-future type of program, where the hosts talk about Michael Beebe, a man who recently recovered from a bout of cancer.\n\nThe first track in the program is a mix of new music from Chicago\'s Boo Williams, Chicago-based MC Flipside, and Chicago- based artist Robert Hood. The next track is a remix by Nathan Barato of D\'Angelo\'s \"Flex.\" The program moves into a drum-and-bass situation, where they play a new track by a female artist named Kenya Grace. The show closes with a look back at the music of the past, where we learn that Leave Me Alone was one of the \"surprises\" of 2023. Next up, they\'ll play music from an infamous \"suburban bass record label\" .',NULL,NULL),(70390,161,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/tc6ykg/VientoSur-Jan-6th-2024.mp3','2024-01-05 03:04:37',79151045,'2024-01-05 05:52:30','2024-01-05 05:05:22','',NULL,NULL),(70391,280,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/key643/Episode95_Meet_the_Team6zg80.mp3','2024-01-05 04:16:24',120006034,'2024-01-05 05:38:13','2024-01-05 05:05:47','Seth and his co-host, Alex, return to the studio to chat with Simon and Rosa, the two students who edit the show. They discuss the show\'s production and how difficult it is to edit long, long-winded advertisements. They decide to keep one of them on the show and commission an internal audit after this. They also discuss how they got involved in the show in the first place, when they were looking for other students on campus to volunteer. They say it was a natural fit for them because they listen to the interviews, and they also enjoy hearing about different cultures from around the world.',NULL,NULL),(703